139InputParameters
140FEProblemBase::validParams()
141{
142 InputParameters params = SubProblem::validParams();
143 params.addParam<unsigned int>("null_space_dimension", 0, "The dimension of the nullspace");
144 params.addParam<unsigned int>(
145 "transpose_null_space_dimension", 0, "The dimension of the transpose nullspace");
146 params.addParam<unsigned int>(
147 "near_null_space_dimension", 0, "The dimension of the near nullspace");
148 params.addParam<bool>("solve",
149 true,
150 "Whether or not to actually solve the Nonlinear system. "
151 "This is handy in the case that all you want to do is "
152 "execute AuxKernels, Transfers, etc. without actually "
153 "solving anything");
154 params.addParam<bool>("use_nonlinear",
155 true,
156 "Determines whether to use a Nonlinear vs a "
157 "Eigenvalue system (Automatically determined based "
158 "on executioner)");
159 params.addParam<bool>("error_on_jacobian_nonzero_reallocation",
160 "This causes PETSc to error if it had to reallocate memory in the Jacobian "
161 "matrix due to not having enough nonzeros");
162 params.addParam<bool>("ignore_zeros_in_jacobian",
163 false,
164 "Do not explicitly store zero values in "
165 "the Jacobian matrix if true");
166 params.addParam<bool>("force_restart",
167 false,
168 "EXPERIMENTAL: If true, a sub_app may use a "
169 "restart file instead of using of using the master "
170 "backup file");
171 params.addDeprecatedParam<bool>("skip_additional_restart_data",
172 false,
173 "True to skip additional data in equation system for restart.",
174 "This parameter is no longer used, as we do not load additional "
175 "vectors by default with restart");
176 params.addParam<bool>("skip_nl_system_check",
177 false,
178 "True to skip the NonlinearSystem check for work to do (e.g. Make sure "
179 "that there are variables to solve for).");
180 params.addParam<bool>("allow_initial_conditions_with_restart",
181 false,
182 "True to allow the user to specify initial conditions when restarting. "
183 "Initial conditions can override any restarted field");
184
190 params.addDeprecatedParam<std::vector<SubdomainName>>(
191 "block", {}, "Block IDs for the coordinate systems", "Please use 'Mesh/coord_block' instead");
192 MultiMooseEnum coord_types("XYZ RZ RSPHERICAL", "XYZ");
193 MooseEnum rz_coord_axis("X=0 Y=1", "Y");
194 params.addDeprecatedParam<MultiMooseEnum>("coord_type",
195 coord_types,
196 "Type of the coordinate system per block param",
197 "Please use 'Mesh/coord_type' instead");
198 params.addDeprecatedParam<MooseEnum>("rz_coord_axis",
199 rz_coord_axis,
200 "The rotation axis (X | Y) for axisymetric coordinates",
201 "Please use 'Mesh/rz_coord_axis' instead");
202 params.addParam<bool>(
203 "kernel_coverage_check", true, "Set to false to disable kernel->subdomain coverage check");
204 params.addParam<bool>(
205 "boundary_restricted_node_integrity_check",
206 true,
207 "Set to false to disable checking of boundary restricted nodal object variable dependencies, "
208 "e.g. are the variable dependencies defined on the selected boundaries?");
209 params.addParam<bool>("boundary_restricted_elem_integrity_check",
210 true,
211 "Set to false to disable checking of boundary restricted elemental object "
212 "variable dependencies, e.g. are the variable dependencies defined on the "
213 "selected boundaries?");
214 params.addParam<bool>("material_coverage_check",
215 true,
216 "Set to false to disable material->subdomain coverage check");
217 params.addParam<bool>("fv_bcs_integrity_check",
218 true,
219 "Set to false to disable checking of overlapping Dirichlet and Flux BCs "
220 "and/or multiple DirichletBCs per sideset");
221
222 params.addParam<bool>(
223 "material_dependency_check", true, "Set to false to disable material dependency check");
224 params.addParam<bool>("parallel_barrier_messaging",
225 false,
226 "Displays messaging from parallel "
227 "barrier notifications when executing "
228 "or transferring to/from Multiapps "
229 "(default: false)");
230
231 params.addParam<bool>(
232 "verbose_setup", false, "Set to True to have the problem report on any object created");
233 params.addParam<bool>("verbose_multiapps",
234 false,
235 "Set to True to enable verbose screen printing related to MultiApps");
236
237 params.addParam<FileNameNoExtension>("restart_file_base",
238 "File base name used for restart (e.g. "
239 "<path>/<filebase> or <path>/LATEST to "
240 "grab the latest file available)");
241
242 params.addParam<std::vector<std::vector<TagName>>>(
243 "extra_tag_vectors",
244 {},
245 "Extra vectors to add to the system that can be filled by objects which compute residuals "
246 "and Jacobians (Kernels, BCs, etc.) by setting tags on them. The outer index is for which "
247 "nonlinear system the extra tag vectors should be added for");
248
249 params.addParam<std::vector<std::vector<TagName>>>(
250 "extra_tag_matrices",
251 {},
252 "Extra matrices to add to the system that can be filled "
253 "by objects which compute residuals and Jacobians "
254 "(Kernels, BCs, etc.) by setting tags on them. The outer index is for which "
255 "nonlinear system the extra tag vectors should be added for");
256
257 params.addParam<std::vector<TagName>>(
258 "extra_tag_solutions",
259 {},
260 "Extra solution vectors to add to the system that can be used by "
261 "objects for coupling variable values stored in them.");
262
263 params.addParam<bool>("previous_nl_solution_required",
264 false,
265 "True to indicate that this calculation requires a solution vector for "
266 "storing the previous nonlinear iteration.");
267
268 params.addParam<std::vector<NonlinearSystemName>>(
269 "nl_sys_names", std::vector<NonlinearSystemName>{"nl0"}, "The nonlinear system names");
270
271 params.addParam<bool>("check_uo_aux_state",
272 false,
273 "True to turn on a check that no state presents during the evaluation of "
274 "user objects and aux kernels");
275
276 params.addPrivateParam<MooseMesh *>("mesh");
277
278 params.declareControllable("solve");
279
280 params.addParam<bool>(
281 "allow_invalid_solution",
282 false,
283 "Set to true to allow convergence even though the solution has been marked as 'invalid'");
284 params.addParam<bool>("immediately_print_invalid_solution",
285 false,
286 "Whether or not to report invalid solution warnings at the time the "
287 "warning is produced instead of after the calculation");
288
289 params.addParam<bool>(
290 "identify_variable_groups_in_nl",
291 true,
292 "Whether to identify variable groups in nonlinear systems. This affects dof ordering");
293
294 params.addParamNamesToGroup(
295 "skip_nl_system_check kernel_coverage_check boundary_restricted_node_integrity_check "
296 "boundary_restricted_elem_integrity_check material_coverage_check fv_bcs_integrity_check "
297 "material_dependency_check check_uo_aux_state error_on_jacobian_nonzero_reallocation",
298 "Simulation checks");
299 params.addParamNamesToGroup("use_nonlinear previous_nl_solution_required nl_sys_names "
300 "ignore_zeros_in_jacobian",
301 "Nonlinear system(s)");
302 params.addParamNamesToGroup(
303 "restart_file_base force_restart allow_initial_conditions_with_restart", "Restart");
304 params.addParamNamesToGroup("verbose_setup verbose_multiapps parallel_barrier_messaging",
305 "Verbosity");
306 params.addParamNamesToGroup(
307 "null_space_dimension transpose_null_space_dimension near_null_space_dimension",
308 "Null space removal");
309 params.addParamNamesToGroup("extra_tag_vectors extra_tag_matrices extra_tag_solutions",
310 "Tagging");
311 params.addParamNamesToGroup("allow_invalid_solution immediately_print_invalid_solution",
312 "Solution validity control");
313
314 return params;
315}
316
317FEProblemBase::FEProblemBase(const InputParameters & parameters)
318 : SubProblem(parameters),
319 Restartable(this, "FEProblemBase"),
320 _mesh(*getCheckedPointerParam<MooseMesh *>("mesh")),
321 _req(declareManagedRestartableDataWithContext<RestartableEquationSystems>(
322 "equation_systems", nullptr, _mesh)),
323 _initialized(false),
324 _solve(getParam<bool>("solve")),
325 _transient(false),
326 _time(declareRestartableData<Real>("time")),
327 _time_old(declareRestartableData<Real>("time_old")),
328 _t_step(declareRecoverableData<int>("t_step")),
329 _dt(declareRestartableData<Real>("dt")),
330 _dt_old(declareRestartableData<Real>("dt_old")),
331 _nl_sys_names(getParam<std::vector<NonlinearSystemName>>("nl_sys_names")),
332 _num_nl_sys(_nl_sys_names.size()),
333 _nl(_num_nl_sys, nullptr),
334 _current_nl_sys(nullptr),
335 _aux(nullptr),
336 _coupling(Moose::COUPLING_DIAG),
337 _mesh_divisions(/*threaded=*/true),
338 _material_props(declareRestartableDataWithContext<MaterialPropertyStorage>(
339 "material_props", &_mesh, _material_prop_registry)),
340 _bnd_material_props(declareRestartableDataWithContext<MaterialPropertyStorage>(
341 "bnd_material_props", &_mesh, _material_prop_registry)),
342 _neighbor_material_props(declareRestartableDataWithContext<MaterialPropertyStorage>(
343 "neighbor_material_props", &_mesh, _material_prop_registry)),
344 _reporter_data(_app),
345 // TODO: delete the following line after apps have been updated to not call getUserObjects
346 _all_user_objects(_app.getExecuteOnEnum()),
347 _multi_apps(_app.getExecuteOnEnum()),
348 _transient_multi_apps(_app.getExecuteOnEnum()),
349 _transfers(_app.getExecuteOnEnum(), /*threaded=*/false),
350 _to_multi_app_transfers(_app.getExecuteOnEnum(), /*threaded=*/false),
351 _from_multi_app_transfers(_app.getExecuteOnEnum(), /*threaded=*/false),
352 _between_multi_app_transfers(_app.getExecuteOnEnum(), /*threaded=*/false),
353#ifdef LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
354 _adaptivity(*this),
355 _cycles_completed(0),
356#endif
357 _displaced_mesh(nullptr),
358 _geometric_search_data(*this, _mesh),
359 _mortar_data(*this),
360 _reinit_displaced_elem(false),
361 _reinit_displaced_face(false),
362 _reinit_displaced_neighbor(false),
363 _input_file_saved(false),
364 _has_dampers(false),
365 _has_constraints(false),
366 _snesmf_reuse_base(true),
367 _skip_exception_check(false),
368 _snesmf_reuse_base_set_by_user(false),
369 _has_initialized_stateful(false),
370 _const_jacobian(false),
371 _has_jacobian(false),
372 _needs_old_newton_iter(false),
373 _has_nonlocal_coupling(false),
374 _calculate_jacobian_in_uo(false),
375 _kernel_coverage_check(getParam<bool>("kernel_coverage_check")),
376 _boundary_restricted_node_integrity_check(
377 getParam<bool>("boundary_restricted_node_integrity_check")),
378 _boundary_restricted_elem_integrity_check(
379 getParam<bool>("boundary_restricted_elem_integrity_check")),
380 _material_coverage_check(getParam<bool>("material_coverage_check")),
381 _fv_bcs_integrity_check(getParam<bool>("fv_bcs_integrity_check")),
382 _material_dependency_check(getParam<bool>("material_dependency_check")),
383 _uo_aux_state_check(getParam<bool>("check_uo_aux_state")),
384 _max_qps(std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max()),
385 _max_scalar_order(INVALID_ORDER),
386 _has_time_integrator(false),
387 _has_exception(false),
388 _parallel_barrier_messaging(getParam<bool>("parallel_barrier_messaging")),
389 _verbose_setup(getParam<bool>("verbose_setup")),
390 _verbose_multiapps(getParam<bool>("verbose_multiapps")),
391 _current_execute_on_flag(EXEC_NONE),
392 _control_warehouse(_app.getExecuteOnEnum(), /*threaded=*/false),
393 _is_petsc_options_inserted(false),
394 _line_search(nullptr),
395 _using_ad_mat_props(false),
396 _error_on_jacobian_nonzero_reallocation(
397 isParamValid("error_on_jacobian_nonzero_reallocation")
398 ? getParam<bool>("error_on_jacobian_nonzero_reallocation")
399 : _app.errorOnJacobianNonzeroReallocation()),
400 _ignore_zeros_in_jacobian(getParam<bool>("ignore_zeros_in_jacobian")),
401 _force_restart(getParam<bool>("force_restart")),
402 _allow_ics_during_restart(getParam<bool>("allow_initial_conditions_with_restart")),
403 _skip_nl_system_check(getParam<bool>("skip_nl_system_check")),
404 _fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check(false),
405 _allow_invalid_solution(getParam<bool>("allow_invalid_solution")),
406 _immediately_print_invalid_solution(getParam<bool>("immediately_print_invalid_solution")),
407 _started_initial_setup(false),
408 _has_internal_edge_residual_objects(false),
409 _u_dot_requested(false),
410 _u_dotdot_requested(false),
411 _u_dot_old_requested(false),
412 _u_dotdot_old_requested(false),
413 _has_mortar(false),
414 _num_grid_steps(0),
415 _print_execution_on(),
416 _identify_variable_groups_in_nl(getParam<bool>("identify_variable_groups_in_nl"))
417{
418 // Initialize static do_derivatives member. We initialize this to true so that all the default AD
419 // things that we setup early in the simulation actually get their derivative vectors initalized.
420 // We will toggle this to false when doing residual evaluations
421 ADReal::do_derivatives = true;
422
423 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl_sys_names))
424 _nl_sys_name_to_num[_nl_sys_names[i]] = i;
425 _nonlocal_cm.resize(_nl_sys_names.size());
426 _cm.resize(_nl_sys_names.size());
427
428 _time = 0.0;
429 _time_old = 0.0;
430 _t_step = 0;
431 _dt = 0;
432 _dt_old = _dt;
433
434 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
435
436 _real_zero.resize(n_threads, 0.);
437 _scalar_zero.resize(n_threads);
438 _zero.resize(n_threads);
439 _phi_zero.resize(n_threads);
440 _ad_zero.resize(n_threads);
441 _grad_zero.resize(n_threads);
442 _ad_grad_zero.resize(n_threads);
443 _grad_phi_zero.resize(n_threads);
444 _second_zero.resize(n_threads);
445 _ad_second_zero.resize(n_threads);
446 _second_phi_zero.resize(n_threads);
447 _point_zero.resize(n_threads);
448 _vector_zero.resize(n_threads);
449 _vector_curl_zero.resize(n_threads);
450 _uo_jacobian_moose_vars.resize(n_threads);
451
452 _active_elemental_moose_variables.resize(n_threads);
453
454 _block_mat_side_cache.resize(n_threads);
455 _bnd_mat_side_cache.resize(n_threads);
456 _interface_mat_side_cache.resize(n_threads);
457
458 es().parameters.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
459
460 if (parameters.isParamSetByUser("coord_type"))
461 setCoordSystem(getParam<std::vector<SubdomainName>>("block"),
462 getParam<MultiMooseEnum>("coord_type"));
463 if (parameters.isParamSetByUser("rz_coord_axis"))
464 setAxisymmetricCoordAxis(getParam<MooseEnum>("rz_coord_axis"));
465
466 if (isParamValid("restart_file_base"))
467 {
468 std::string restart_file_base = getParam<FileNameNoExtension>("restart_file_base");
469
470 // This check reverts to old behavior of providing "restart_file_base=" to mean
471 // don't restart... BISON currently relies on this. It could probably be removed.
472 // The new MooseUtils::convertLatestCheckpoint will error out if a checkpoint file
473 // is not found, which I think makes sense. Which means, without this, if you
474 // set "restart_file_base=", you'll get a "No checkpoint file found" error
475 if (restart_file_base.size())
476 {
477 restart_file_base = MooseUtils::convertLatestCheckpoint(restart_file_base);
478 setRestartFile(restart_file_base);
479 }
480 }
481
482 // // Generally speaking, the mesh is prepared for use, and consequently remote elements are deleted
483 // // well before our Problem(s) are constructed. Historically, in MooseMesh we have a bunch of
484 // // needs_prepare type flags that make it so we never call prepare_for_use (and consequently
485 // // delete_remote_elements) again. So the below line, historically, has had no impact. HOWEVER:
486 // // I've added some code in SetupMeshCompleteAction for deleting remote elements post
487 // // EquationSystems::init. If I execute that code without default ghosting, then I get > 40 MOOSE
488 // // test failures, so we clearly have some simulations that are not yet covered properly by
489 // // relationship managers. Until that is resolved, I am going to retain default geometric ghosting
490 // if (!_default_ghosting)
491 // _mesh.getMesh().remove_ghosting_functor(_mesh.getMesh().default_ghosting());
492
493#if !PETSC_RELEASE_LESS_THAN(3, 12, 0)
494 // Main app should hold the default database to handle system petsc options
495 if (!_app.isUltimateMaster())
496 PetscOptionsCreate(&_petsc_option_data_base);
497#endif
498}
499
500const MooseMesh &
501FEProblemBase::mesh(bool use_displaced) const
502{
503 if (use_displaced && !_displaced_problem)
504 mooseWarning("Displaced mesh was requested but the displaced problem does not exist. "
505 "Regular mesh will be returned");
506 return ((use_displaced && _displaced_problem) ? _displaced_problem->mesh() : mesh());
507}
508
509void
510FEProblemBase::createTagVectors()
511{
512 // add vectors and their tags to system
513 auto & vectors = getParam<std::vector<std::vector<TagName>>>("extra_tag_vectors");
514 for (const auto nl_sys_num : index_range(vectors))
515 for (auto & vector : vectors[nl_sys_num])
516 {
517 auto tag = addVectorTag(vector);
518 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addVector(tag, false, GHOSTED);
519 }
520
521 // add matrices and their tags
522 auto & matrices = getParam<std::vector<std::vector<TagName>>>("extra_tag_matrices");
523 for (const auto nl_sys_num : index_range(matrices))
524 for (auto & matrix : matrices[nl_sys_num])
525 {
526 auto tag = addMatrixTag(matrix);
527 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addMatrix(tag);
528 }
529}
530
531void
532FEProblemBase::createTagSolutions()
533{
534 for (auto & vector : getParam<std::vector<TagName>>("extra_tag_solutions"))
535 {
536 auto tag = addVectorTag(vector, Moose::VECTOR_TAG_SOLUTION);
537 for (auto & nl : _nl)
538 nl->addVector(tag, false, GHOSTED);
539 _aux->addVector(tag, false, GHOSTED);
540 }
541
542 if (getParam<bool>("previous_nl_solution_required"))
543 {
544 // We'll populate the zeroth state of the nonlinear iterations with the current solution for
545 // ease of use in doing things like copying solutions backwards. We're just storing pointers in
546 // the solution states containers so populating the zeroth state does not cost us the memory of
547 // a new vector
548 for (const auto i : make_range(0, 2))
549 {
550 for (auto & nl : _nl)
551 nl->needSolutionState(i, Moose::SolutionIterationType::Nonlinear);
552 _aux->needSolutionState(i, Moose::SolutionIterationType::Nonlinear);
553 }
554 }
555
556 auto tag = addVectorTag(Moose::SOLUTION_TAG, Moose::VECTOR_TAG_SOLUTION);
557 for (auto & nl : _nl)
558 nl->associateVectorToTag(*nl->system().current_local_solution.get(), tag);
559 _aux->associateVectorToTag(*_aux->system().current_local_solution.get(), tag);
560}
561
562void
563FEProblemBase::newAssemblyArray(std::vector<std::shared_ptr<NonlinearSystemBase>> & nls)
564{
565 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
566
567 _assembly.resize(n_threads);
568 for (const auto i : make_range(n_threads))
569 {
570 _assembly[i].resize(nls.size());
571 for (const auto j : index_range(nls))
572 _assembly[i][j] = std::make_unique<Assembly>(*nls[j], i);
573 }
574}
575
576void
577FEProblemBase::initNullSpaceVectors(const InputParameters & parameters,
578 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<NonlinearSystemBase>> & nls)
579{
580 TIME_SECTION("initNullSpaceVectors", 5, "Initializing Null Space Vectors");
581
582 unsigned int dimNullSpace = parameters.get<unsigned int>("null_space_dimension");
583 unsigned int dimTransposeNullSpace =
584 parameters.get<unsigned int>("transpose_null_space_dimension");
585 unsigned int dimNearNullSpace = parameters.get<unsigned int>("near_null_space_dimension");
586 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < dimNullSpace; ++i)
587 {
588 std::ostringstream oss;
589 oss << "_" << i;
590 // do not project, since this will be recomputed, but make it ghosted, since the near nullspace
591 // builder might march over all nodes
592 for (auto & nl : nls)
593 nl->addVector("NullSpace" + oss.str(), false, GHOSTED);
594 }
595 _subspace_dim["NullSpace"] = dimNullSpace;
596 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < dimTransposeNullSpace; ++i)
597 {
598 std::ostringstream oss;
599 oss << "_" << i;
600 // do not project, since this will be recomputed, but make it ghosted, since the near nullspace
601 // builder might march over all nodes
602 for (auto & nl : nls)
603 nl->addVector("TransposeNullSpace" + oss.str(), false, GHOSTED);
604 }
605 _subspace_dim["TransposeNullSpace"] = dimTransposeNullSpace;
606 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < dimNearNullSpace; ++i)
607 {
608 std::ostringstream oss;
609 oss << "_" << i;
610 // do not project, since this will be recomputed, but make it ghosted, since the near-nullspace
611 // builder might march over all semilocal nodes
612 for (auto & nl : nls)
613 nl->addVector("NearNullSpace" + oss.str(), false, GHOSTED);
614 }
615 _subspace_dim["NearNullSpace"] = dimNearNullSpace;
616}
617
618FEProblemBase::~FEProblemBase()
619{
620 // Flush the Console stream, the underlying call to Console::mooseConsole
621 // relies on a call to Output::checkInterval that has references to
622 // _time, etc. If it is not flushed here memory problems arise if you have
623 // an unflushed stream and start destructing things.
624 _console << std::flush;
625
626 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
627 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_threads; i++)
628 {
629 _zero[i].release();
630 _phi_zero[i].release();
631 _scalar_zero[i].release();
632 _grad_zero[i].release();
633 _grad_phi_zero[i].release();
634 _second_zero[i].release();
635 _second_phi_zero[i].release();
636 _vector_zero[i].release();
637 _vector_curl_zero[i].release();
638 _ad_zero[i].release();
639 _ad_grad_zero[i].release();
640 _ad_second_zero[i].release();
641 }
642
643#if !PETSC_RELEASE_LESS_THAN(3, 12, 0)
644 if (!_app.isUltimateMaster())
645 PetscOptionsDestroy(&_petsc_option_data_base);
646#endif
647}
648
649void
650FEProblemBase::setCoordSystem(const std::vector<SubdomainName> & blocks,
651 const MultiMooseEnum & coord_sys)
652{
653 TIME_SECTION("setCoordSystem", 5, "Setting Coordinate System");
654 _mesh.setCoordSystem(blocks, coord_sys);
655}
656
657void
658FEProblemBase::setAxisymmetricCoordAxis(const MooseEnum & rz_coord_axis)
659{
660 _mesh.setAxisymmetricCoordAxis(rz_coord_axis);
661}
662
663const ConstElemRange &
664FEProblemBase::getEvaluableElementRange()
665{
666 if (!_evaluable_local_elem_range)
667 {
668 std::vector<const DofMap *> dof_maps(es().n_systems());
669 for (const auto i : make_range(es().n_systems()))
670 {
671 const auto & sys = es().get_system(i);
672 dof_maps[i] = &sys.get_dof_map();
673 }
674 _evaluable_local_elem_range =
675 std::make_unique<ConstElemRange>(_mesh.getMesh().multi_evaluable_elements_begin(dof_maps),
676 _mesh.getMesh().multi_evaluable_elements_end(dof_maps));
677 }
678 return *_evaluable_local_elem_range;
679}
680
681const ConstElemRange &
682FEProblemBase::getNonlinearEvaluableElementRange()
683{
684 if (!_nl_evaluable_local_elem_range)
685 {
686 std::vector<const DofMap *> dof_maps(_nl.size());
687 for (const auto i : index_range(dof_maps))
688 dof_maps[i] = &_nl[i]->dofMap();
689 _nl_evaluable_local_elem_range =
690 std::make_unique<ConstElemRange>(_mesh.getMesh().multi_evaluable_elements_begin(dof_maps),
691 _mesh.getMesh().multi_evaluable_elements_end(dof_maps));
692 }
693
694 return *_nl_evaluable_local_elem_range;
695}
696
697void
698FEProblemBase::initialSetup()
699{
700 TIME_SECTION("initialSetup", 2, "Performing Initial Setup");
701
702 SubProblem::initialSetup();
703
704 if (_app.isRecovering() + _app.isRestarting() + bool(_app.getExReaderForRestart()) > 1)
705 mooseError("Checkpoint recovery and restart and exodus restart are all mutually exclusive.");
706
707 if (_skip_exception_check)
708 mooseWarning("MOOSE may fail to catch an exception when the \"skip_exception_check\" parameter "
709 "is used. If you receive a terse MPI error during execution, remove this "
710 "parameter and rerun your simulation");
711
712 // set state flag indicating that we are in or beyond initialSetup.
713 // This can be used to throw errors in methods that _must_ be called at construction time.
714 _started_initial_setup = true;
715 setCurrentExecuteOnFlag(EXEC_INITIAL);
716
717 // Setup the solution states (current, old, etc) in each system based on
718 // its default and the states requested of each of its variables
719 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
720 {
721 _nl[i]->initSolutionState();
722 if (getDisplacedProblem())
723 getDisplacedProblem()->nlSys(i).initSolutionState();
724 }
725 _aux->initSolutionState();
726 if (getDisplacedProblem())
727 getDisplacedProblem()->auxSys().initSolutionState();
728
729 // always execute to get the max number of DoF per element and node needed to initialize phi_zero
730 // variables
731 dof_id_type global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem = 0;
732 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
733 {
734 auto & nl = *_nl[i];
735 dof_id_type max_var_n_dofs_per_elem;
736 dof_id_type max_var_n_dofs_per_node;
737 {
738 TIME_SECTION("computingMaxDofs", 3, "Computing Max Dofs Per Element");
739
740 MaxVarNDofsPerElem mvndpe(*this, nl);
741 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), mvndpe);
742 max_var_n_dofs_per_elem = mvndpe.max();
743 _communicator.max(max_var_n_dofs_per_elem);
744
745 MaxVarNDofsPerNode mvndpn(*this, nl);
746 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getLocalNodeRange(), mvndpn);
747 max_var_n_dofs_per_node = mvndpn.max();
748 _communicator.max(max_var_n_dofs_per_node);
749 global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem =
750 std::max(global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem, max_var_n_dofs_per_elem);
751 }
752
753 {
754 TIME_SECTION("assignMaxDofs", 5, "Assigning Maximum Dofs Per Elem");
755
756 nl.assignMaxVarNDofsPerElem(max_var_n_dofs_per_elem);
757 auto displaced_problem = getDisplacedProblem();
758 if (displaced_problem)
759 displaced_problem->nlSys(i).assignMaxVarNDofsPerElem(max_var_n_dofs_per_elem);
760
761 nl.assignMaxVarNDofsPerNode(max_var_n_dofs_per_node);
762 if (displaced_problem)
763 displaced_problem->nlSys(i).assignMaxVarNDofsPerNode(max_var_n_dofs_per_node);
764 }
765 }
766
767 {
768 TIME_SECTION("resizingVarValues", 5, "Resizing Variable Values");
769
770 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
771 {
772 _phi_zero[tid].resize(global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem, std::vector<Real>(getMaxQps(), 0.));
773 _grad_phi_zero[tid].resize(global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem,
774 std::vector<RealGradient>(getMaxQps(), RealGradient(0.)));
775 _second_phi_zero[tid].resize(global_max_var_n_dofs_per_elem,
776 std::vector<RealTensor>(getMaxQps(), RealTensor(0.)));
777 }
778 }
779
780 // Set up stateful material property redistribution, if we suspect
781 // it may be necessary later.
782 addAnyRedistributers();
783
784 if (_app.isRestarting() || _app.isRecovering() || _force_restart)
785 {
786 // Only load all of the vectors if we're recovering
787 _req.set().setLoadAllVectors(_app.isRecovering());
788
789 TIME_SECTION("restore", 3, "Restoring from backup");
790
791 // We could have a cached backup when this app is a sub-app and has been given a Backup
792 if (!_app.hasInitialBackup())
793 _app.restore(_app.restartFolderBase(_app.getRestartRecoverFileBase()), _app.isRestarting());
794 else
795 _app.restoreFromInitialBackup(_app.isRestarting());
796
797 if (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
798 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
799 _has_initialized_stateful = true;
800 }
801 else
802 {
803 ExodusII_IO * reader = _app.getExReaderForRestart();
804
805 if (reader)
806 {
807 TIME_SECTION("copyingFromExodus", 3, "Copying Variables From Exodus");
808
809 for (auto & nl : _nl)
810 nl->copyVars(*reader);
811 _aux->copyVars(*reader);
812 }
813 else
814 {
815 if (_nl[0]->hasVarCopy() || _aux->hasVarCopy())
816 mooseError("Need Exodus reader to restart variables but the reader is not available\n"
817 "Use either FileMesh with an Exodus mesh file or FileMeshGenerator with an "
818 "Exodus mesh file and with use_for_exodus_restart equal to true");
819 }
820 }
821
822 // Perform output related setups
823 _app.getOutputWarehouse().initialSetup();
824
825 // Flush all output to _console that occur during construction and initialization of objects
826 _app.getOutputWarehouse().mooseConsole();
827
828 // Build Refinement and Coarsening maps for stateful material projections if necessary
829 if ((_adaptivity.isOn() || _num_grid_steps) &&
830 (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
831 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties()))
832 {
833 if (_has_internal_edge_residual_objects)
834 mooseError("Stateful neighbor material properties do not work with mesh adaptivity");
835
836 _mesh.buildRefinementAndCoarseningMaps(_assembly[0][0].get());
837 }
838
839 if (!_app.isRecovering())
840 {
846 if (_mesh.uniformRefineLevel() > 0 && _app.getExodusFileRestart())
847 {
848 if (!_app.isUltimateMaster())
849 mooseError(
850 "Doing extra refinements when restarting is NOT supported for sub-apps of a MultiApp");
851
852 adaptivity().uniformRefineWithProjection();
853 }
854 }
855
856 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
857
858 // UserObject initialSetup
859 std::set<std::string> depend_objects_ic = _ics.getDependObjects();
860 std::set<std::string> depend_objects_aux = _aux->getDependObjects();
861
862 // This replaces all prior updateDependObjects calls on the old user object warehouses.
863 TheWarehouse::Query uo_query = theWarehouse().query().condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject");
864 std::vector<UserObject *> userobjs;
865 uo_query.queryInto(userobjs);
866 groupUserObjects(
867 theWarehouse(), getAuxiliarySystem(), _app.getExecuteOnEnum(), userobjs, depend_objects_ic);
868
869 for (auto obj : userobjs)
870 obj->initialSetup();
871
872 // check if jacobian calculation is done in userobject
873 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; ++tid)
874 checkUserObjectJacobianRequirement(tid);
875
876 // Check whether nonlocal couling is required or not
877 checkNonlocalCoupling();
878 if (_requires_nonlocal_coupling)
879 setVariableAllDoFMap(_uo_jacobian_moose_vars[0]);
880
881 {
882 TIME_SECTION("initializingFunctions", 5, "Initializing Functions");
883
884 // Call the initialSetup methods for functions
885 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
886 {
887 reinitScalars(tid); // initialize scalars so they are properly sized for use as input into
888 // ParsedFunctions
889 _functions.initialSetup(tid);
890 }
891 }
892
893 {
894 TIME_SECTION("initializingRandomObjects", 5, "Initializing Random Objects");
895
896 // Random interface objects
897 for (const auto & it : _random_data_objects)
898 it.second->updateSeeds(EXEC_INITIAL);
899 }
900
901 if (!_app.isRecovering())
902 {
903 computeUserObjects(EXEC_INITIAL, Moose::PRE_IC);
904
905 {
906 TIME_SECTION("ICiniitalSetup", 5, "Setting Up Initial Conditions");
907
908 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
909 _ics.initialSetup(tid);
910
911 _scalar_ics.initialSetup();
912 }
913
914 projectSolution();
915 }
916
917 // Materials
918 if (_all_materials.hasActiveObjects(0))
919 {
920 TIME_SECTION("materialInitialSetup", 3, "Setting Up Materials");
921
922 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
923 {
924 // Sort the Material objects, these will be actually computed by MOOSE in reinit methods.
925 _materials.sort(tid);
926 _interface_materials.sort(tid);
927
928 // Call initialSetup on all material objects
929 _all_materials.initialSetup(tid);
930
931 // Discrete materials may insert additional dependencies on materials during the initial
932 // setup. Therefore we resolve the dependencies once more, now with the additional
933 // dependencies due to discrete materials.
934 if (_discrete_materials.hasActiveObjects())
935 {
936 _materials.sort(tid);
937 _interface_materials.sort(tid);
938 }
939 }
940
941 if (!_has_initialized_stateful)
942 {
943 TIME_SECTION("computingInitialStatefulProps", 3, "Computing Initial Material Values");
944
945 initElementStatefulProps(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), true);
946
947 if (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
948 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
949 _has_initialized_stateful = true;
950 }
951 }
952
953 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
954 {
955 _internal_side_indicators.initialSetup(tid);
956 _indicators.initialSetup(tid);
957 _markers.sort(tid);
958 _markers.initialSetup(tid);
959 }
960
961#ifdef LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
962
963 if (!_app.isRecovering())
964 {
965 unsigned int n = adaptivity().getInitialSteps();
966 if (n && !_app.isUltimateMaster() && _app.isRestarting())
967 mooseError("Cannot perform initial adaptivity during restart on sub-apps of a MultiApp!");
968
969 initialAdaptMesh();
970 }
971
972#endif // LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
973
974 if (!_app.isRecovering() && !_app.isRestarting())
975 {
976 // During initial setup the solution is copied to the older solution states (old, older, etc)
977 copySolutionsBackwards();
978 }
979
980 if (!_app.isRecovering())
981 {
982 if (haveXFEM())
983 updateMeshXFEM();
984 }
985
986 // Call initialSetup on the nonlinear system
987 for (auto & nl : _nl)
988 nl->initialSetup();
989
990 // Auxilary variable initialSetup calls
991 _aux->initialSetup();
992
993 if (_displaced_problem)
994 // initialSetup for displaced systems
995 _displaced_problem->initialSetup();
996
997 for (auto & nl : _nl)
998 nl->setSolution(*(nl->system().current_local_solution.get()));
999
1000 // Update the nearest node searches (has to be called after the problem is all set up)
1001 // We do this here because this sets up the Element's DoFs to ghost
1002 updateGeomSearch(GeometricSearchData::NEAREST_NODE);
1003
1004 _mesh.updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
1005 if (_displaced_mesh)
1006 _displaced_mesh->updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
1007
1008 // We need to move the mesh in order to build a map between mortar secondary and primary
1009 // interfaces. This map will then be used by the AgumentSparsityOnInterface ghosting functor to
1010 // know which dofs we need ghosted when we call EquationSystems::reinit
1011 if (_displaced_problem && _mortar_data.hasDisplacedObjects())
1012 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
1013
1014 // Possibly reinit one more time to get ghosting correct
1015 reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects();
1016
1017 if (_displaced_mesh)
1018 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
1019
1020 updateGeomSearch(); // Call all of the rest of the geometric searches
1021
1022 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1023 {
1024 auto ti = nl->getTimeIntegrator();
1025
1026 if (ti)
1027 {
1028 TIME_SECTION("timeIntegratorInitialSetup", 5, "Initializing Time Integrator");
1029 ti->initialSetup();
1030 }
1031 }
1032
1033 // HUGE NOTE: MultiApp initialSetup() MUST... I repeat MUST be _after_ main-app restartable data
1034 // has been restored
1035
1036 // Call initialSetup on the MultiApps
1037 if (_multi_apps.hasObjects())
1038 {
1039 TIME_SECTION("initialSetupMultiApps", 2, "Initializing MultiApps", false);
1040 _multi_apps.initialSetup();
1041 }
1042
1043 // Call initialSetup on the transfers
1044 {
1045 TIME_SECTION("initialSetupTransfers", 2, "Initializing Transfers");
1046
1047 _transfers.initialSetup();
1048
1049 // Call initialSetup on the MultiAppTransfers to be executed on TO_MULTIAPP
1050 const auto & to_multi_app_objects = _to_multi_app_transfers.getActiveObjects();
1051 for (const auto & transfer : to_multi_app_objects)
1052 {
1053 transfer->setCurrentDirection(Transfer::DIRECTION::TO_MULTIAPP);
1054 transfer->initialSetup();
1055 }
1056
1057 // Call initialSetup on the MultiAppTransfers to be executed on FROM_MULTIAPP
1058 const auto & from_multi_app_objects = _from_multi_app_transfers.getActiveObjects();
1059 for (const auto & transfer : from_multi_app_objects)
1060 {
1061 transfer->setCurrentDirection(Transfer::DIRECTION::FROM_MULTIAPP);
1062 transfer->initialSetup();
1063 }
1064
1065 // Call initialSetup on the MultiAppTransfers to be executed on BETWEEN_MULTIAPP
1066 const auto & between_multi_app_objects = _between_multi_app_transfers.getActiveObjects();
1067 for (const auto & transfer : between_multi_app_objects)
1068 {
1069 transfer->setCurrentDirection(Transfer::DIRECTION::BETWEEN_MULTIAPP);
1070 transfer->initialSetup();
1071 }
1072 }
1073
1074 if (_boundary_restricted_node_integrity_check)
1075 {
1076 TIME_SECTION("BoundaryRestrictedNodeIntegrityCheck", 5);
1077
1078 // check that variables are defined along boundaries of boundary restricted nodal objects
1079 ConstBndNodeRange & bnd_nodes = *mesh().getBoundaryNodeRange();
1080 BoundaryNodeIntegrityCheckThread bnict(*this, uo_query);
1081 Threads::parallel_reduce(bnd_nodes, bnict);
1082
1083 // Nodal bcs aren't threaded
1084 const auto & node_to_elem_map = _mesh.nodeToActiveSemilocalElemMap();
1085 for (const auto & bnode : bnd_nodes)
1086 {
1087 const auto boundary_id = bnode->_bnd_id;
1088 const Node * const node = bnode->_node;
1089
1090 if (node->processor_id() != this->processor_id())
1091 continue;
1092
1093 // Only check vertices. Variables may not be defined on non-vertex nodes (think first order
1094 // Lagrange on a second order mesh) and user-code can often handle that
1095 const Elem * const an_elem =
1096 _mesh.getMesh().elem_ptr(libmesh_map_find(node_to_elem_map, node->id()).front());
1097 if (!an_elem->is_vertex(an_elem->get_node_index(node)))
1098 continue;
1099
1100 const auto & bnd_name = _mesh.getBoundaryName(boundary_id);
1101
1102 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1103 {
1104 const auto & nodal_bcs = nl->getNodalBCWarehouse();
1105 if (!nodal_bcs.hasBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, 0))
1106 continue;
1107
1108 const auto & bnd_objects = nodal_bcs.getBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, 0);
1109 for (const auto & bnd_object : bnd_objects)
1110 // Skip if this object uses geometric search because coupled variables may be defined on
1111 // paired boundaries instead of the boundary this node is on
1112 if (!bnd_object->requiresGeometricSearch() &&
1113 bnd_object->checkVariableBoundaryIntegrity())
1114 {
1115 std::set<MooseVariableFieldBase *> vars_to_omit = {
1116 &static_cast<MooseVariableFieldBase &>(
1117 const_cast<MooseVariableBase &>(bnd_object->variable()))};
1118
1119 boundaryIntegrityCheckError(
1120 *bnd_object, bnd_object->checkAllVariables(*node, vars_to_omit), bnd_name);
1121 }
1122 }
1123 }
1124 }
1125
1126 if (_boundary_restricted_elem_integrity_check)
1127 {
1128 TIME_SECTION("BoundaryRestrictedElemIntegrityCheck", 5);
1129
1130 // check that variables are defined along boundaries of boundary restricted elemental objects
1131 ConstBndElemRange & bnd_elems = *mesh().getBoundaryElementRange();
1132 BoundaryElemIntegrityCheckThread beict(*this, uo_query);
1133 Threads::parallel_reduce(bnd_elems, beict);
1134 }
1135
1136 if (!_app.isRecovering())
1137 {
1138 execTransfers(EXEC_INITIAL);
1139
1140 bool converged = execMultiApps(EXEC_INITIAL);
1141 if (!converged)
1142 mooseError("failed to converge initial MultiApp");
1143
1144 // We'll backup the Multiapp here
1145 backupMultiApps(EXEC_INITIAL);
1146
1147 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
1148 reinitScalars(tid);
1149
1150 execute(EXEC_INITIAL);
1151
1152 // The FEProblemBase::execute method doesn't call all the systems on EXEC_INITIAL, but it does
1153 // set/unset the current flag. Therefore, this resets the current flag to EXEC_INITIAL so that
1154 // subsequent calls (e.g., executeControls) have the proper flag.
1155 setCurrentExecuteOnFlag(EXEC_INITIAL);
1156 }
1157
1158 // Here we will initialize the stateful properties once more since they may have been updated
1159 // during initialSetup by calls to computeProperties.
1160 //
1161 // It's really bad that we don't allow this during restart. It means that we can't add new
1162 // stateful materials
1163 // during restart. This is only happening because this _has_ to be below initial userobject
1164 // execution.
1165 // Otherwise this could be done up above... _before_ restoring restartable data... which would
1166 // allow you to have
1167 // this happen during restart. I honestly have no idea why this has to happen after initial user
1168 // object computation.
1169 // THAT is something we should fix... so I've opened this ticket: #5804
1170 if (!_app.isRecovering() && !_app.isRestarting() &&
1171 (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
1172 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties()))
1173 {
1174 TIME_SECTION("computeMaterials", 2, "Computing Initial Material Properties");
1175
1176 initElementStatefulProps(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), true);
1177 }
1178
1179 // Control Logic
1180 executeControls(EXEC_INITIAL);
1181
1182 // Scalar variables need to reinited for the initial conditions to be available for output
1183 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
1184 reinitScalars(tid);
1185
1186 if (_displaced_mesh)
1187 _displaced_problem->syncSolutions();
1188
1189 // Writes all calls to _console from initialSetup() methods
1190 _app.getOutputWarehouse().mooseConsole();
1191
1192 if (_requires_nonlocal_coupling)
1193 {
1194 setNonlocalCouplingMatrix();
1195 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; ++tid)
1196 for (auto & assembly : _assembly[tid])
1197 assembly->initNonlocalCoupling();
1198 }
1199
1200 {
1201 TIME_SECTION("lineSearchInitialSetup", 5, "Initializing Line Search");
1202
1203 if (_line_search)
1204 _line_search->initialSetup();
1205 }
1206
1207 // Perform Reporter get/declare check
1208 _reporter_data.check();
1209
1210 // We do this late to allow objects to get late restartable data
1211 if (_app.isRestarting() || _app.isRecovering() || _force_restart)
1212 _app.finalizeRestore();
1213
1214 setCurrentExecuteOnFlag(EXEC_NONE);
1215}
1216
1217void
1218FEProblemBase::checkDuplicatePostprocessorVariableNames()
1219{
1220 for (const auto & pp : _reporter_data.getPostprocessorNames())
1221 if (hasScalarVariable(pp))
1222 mooseError("Postprocessor \"" + pp +
1223 "\" has the same name as a scalar variable in the system.");
1224}
1225
1226void
1227FEProblemBase::timestepSetup()
1228{
1229 SubProblem::timestepSetup();
1230
1231 if (_t_step > 1 && _num_grid_steps)
1232 {
1233 MeshRefinement mesh_refinement(_mesh);
1234 std::unique_ptr<MeshRefinement> displaced_mesh_refinement(nullptr);
1235 if (_displaced_mesh)
1236 displaced_mesh_refinement = std::make_unique<MeshRefinement>(*_displaced_mesh);
1237
1238 for (MooseIndex(_num_grid_steps) i = 0; i < _num_grid_steps; ++i)
1239 {
1240 if (_displaced_problem)
1241 // If the DisplacedProblem is active, undisplace the DisplacedMesh in preparation for
1242 // refinement. We can't safely refine the DisplacedMesh directly, since the Hilbert keys
1243 // computed on the inconsistenly-displaced Mesh are different on different processors,
1244 // leading to inconsistent Hilbert keys. We must do this before the undisplaced Mesh is
1245 // coarsensed, so that the element and node numbering is still consistent. We also have to
1246 // make sure this is done during every step of coarsening otherwise different partitions
1247 // will be generated for the reference and displaced meshes (even for replicated)
1248 _displaced_problem->undisplaceMesh();
1249
1250 mesh_refinement.uniformly_coarsen();
1251 if (_displaced_mesh)
1252 displaced_mesh_refinement->uniformly_coarsen();
1253
1254 // Mark this as an intermediate change because we do not yet want to reinit_systems. E.g. we
1255 // need things to happen in the following order for the undisplaced problem:
1256 // u1) EquationSystems::reinit_solutions. This will restrict the solution vectors and then
1257 // contract the mesh
1258 // u2) MooseMesh::meshChanged. This will update the node/side lists and other
1259 // things which needs to happen after the contraction
1260 // u3) GeometricSearchData::reinit. Once the node/side lists are updated we can perform our
1261 // geometric searches which will aid in determining sparsity patterns
1262 //
1263 // We do these things for the displaced problem (if it exists)
1264 // d1) EquationSystems::reinit. Restrict the displaced problem vector copies and then contract
1265 // the mesh. It's safe to do a full reinit with the displaced because there are no
1266 // matrices that sparsity pattern calculations will be conducted for
1267 // d2) MooseMesh::meshChanged. This will update the node/side lists and other
1268 // things which needs to happen after the contraction
1269 // d3) UpdateDisplacedMeshThread::operator(). Re-displace the mesh using the *displaced*
1270 // solution vector copy because we don't know the state of the reference solution vector.
1271 // It's safe to use the displaced copy because we are outside of a non-linear solve,
1272 // and there is no concern about differences between solution and current_local_solution
1273 // d4) GeometricSearchData::reinit. With the node/side lists updated and the mesh
1274 // re-displaced, we can perform our geometric searches, which will aid in determining the
1275 // sparsity pattern of the matrix held by the libMesh::ImplicitSystem held by the
1276 // NonlinearSystem held by this
1277 meshChangedHelper(/*intermediate_change=*/true);
1278 }
1279
1280 // u4) Now that all the geometric searches have been done (both undisplaced and displaced),
1281 // we're ready to update the sparsity pattern
1282 es().reinit_systems();
1283 }
1284
1285 if (_line_search)
1286 _line_search->timestepSetup();
1287
1288 // Random interface objects
1289 for (const auto & it : _random_data_objects)
1290 it.second->updateSeeds(EXEC_TIMESTEP_BEGIN);
1291
1292 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
1293 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
1294 {
1295 _all_materials.timestepSetup(tid);
1296 _functions.timestepSetup(tid);
1297 }
1298
1299 _aux->timestepSetup();
1300 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1301 nl->timestepSetup();
1302
1303 if (_displaced_problem)
1304 // timestepSetup for displaced systems
1305 _displaced_problem->timestepSetup();
1306
1307 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
1308 {
1309 _internal_side_indicators.timestepSetup(tid);
1310 _indicators.timestepSetup(tid);
1311 _markers.timestepSetup(tid);
1312 }
1313
1314 std::vector<UserObject *> userobjs;
1315 theWarehouse().query().condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject").queryIntoUnsorted(userobjs);
1316 for (auto obj : userobjs)
1317 obj->timestepSetup();
1318
1319 // Timestep setup of output objects
1320 _app.getOutputWarehouse().timestepSetup();
1321
1322 if (_requires_nonlocal_coupling)
1323 if (_nonlocal_kernels.hasActiveObjects() || _nonlocal_integrated_bcs.hasActiveObjects())
1324 _has_nonlocal_coupling = true;
1325}
1326
1327unsigned int
1328FEProblemBase::getMaxQps() const
1329{
1330 if (_max_qps == std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max())
1331 mooseError("Max QPS uninitialized");
1332 return _max_qps;
1333}

1340
1341void
1342FEProblemBase::checkNonlocalCoupling()
1343{
1344 TIME_SECTION("checkNonlocalCoupling", 5, "Checking Nonlocal Coupling");
1345
1346 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
1347 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1348 {
1349 const auto & all_kernels = nl->getKernelWarehouse();
1350 const auto & kernels = all_kernels.getObjects(tid);
1351 for (const auto & kernel : kernels)
1352 {
1353 std::shared_ptr<NonlocalKernel> nonlocal_kernel =
1354 std::dynamic_pointer_cast<NonlocalKernel>(kernel);
1355 if (nonlocal_kernel)
1356 {
1357 if (_calculate_jacobian_in_uo)
1358 _requires_nonlocal_coupling = true;
1359 _nonlocal_kernels.addObject(kernel, tid);
1360 }
1361 }
1362 const MooseObjectWarehouse<IntegratedBCBase> & all_integrated_bcs =
1363 nl->getIntegratedBCWarehouse();
1364 const auto & integrated_bcs = all_integrated_bcs.getObjects(tid);
1365 for (const auto & integrated_bc : integrated_bcs)
1366 {
1367 std::shared_ptr<NonlocalIntegratedBC> nonlocal_integrated_bc =
1368 std::dynamic_pointer_cast<NonlocalIntegratedBC>(integrated_bc);
1369 if (nonlocal_integrated_bc)
1370 {
1371 if (_calculate_jacobian_in_uo)
1372 _requires_nonlocal_coupling = true;
1373 _nonlocal_integrated_bcs.addObject(integrated_bc, tid);
1374 }
1375 }
1376 }
1377}
1378
1379void
1380FEProblemBase::checkUserObjectJacobianRequirement(THREAD_ID tid)
1381{
1382 std::set<const MooseVariableFEBase *> uo_jacobian_moose_vars;
1383 {
1384 std::vector<ShapeElementUserObject *> objs;
1385 theWarehouse()
1386 .query()
1387 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ShapeElementUserObject)
1388 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
1389 .queryInto(objs);
1390
1391 for (const auto & uo : objs)
1392 {
1393 _calculate_jacobian_in_uo = uo->computeJacobianFlag();
1394 const auto & mv_deps = uo->jacobianMooseVariables();
1395 uo_jacobian_moose_vars.insert(mv_deps.begin(), mv_deps.end());
1396 }
1397 }
1398 {
1399 std::vector<ShapeSideUserObject *> objs;
1400 theWarehouse()
1401 .query()
1402 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ShapeSideUserObject)
1403 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
1404 .queryInto(objs);
1405 for (const auto & uo : objs)
1406 {
1407 _calculate_jacobian_in_uo = uo->computeJacobianFlag();
1408 const auto & mv_deps = uo->jacobianMooseVariables();
1409 uo_jacobian_moose_vars.insert(mv_deps.begin(), mv_deps.end());
1410 }
1411 }
1412
1413 _uo_jacobian_moose_vars[tid].assign(uo_jacobian_moose_vars.begin(), uo_jacobian_moose_vars.end());
1414 std::sort(
1415 _uo_jacobian_moose_vars[tid].begin(), _uo_jacobian_moose_vars[tid].end(), sortMooseVariables);
1416}

1418void
1419FEProblemBase::setVariableAllDoFMap(const std::vector<const MooseVariableFEBase *> & moose_vars)
1420{
1421 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < moose_vars.size(); ++i)
1422 {
1423 VariableName var_name = moose_vars[i]->name();
1424 auto & nl = _nl[moose_vars[i]->sys().number()];
1425 nl->setVariableGlobalDoFs(var_name);
1426 _var_dof_map[var_name] = nl->getVariableGlobalDoFs();
1427 }

1429
1430void
1431FEProblemBase::prepare(const Elem * elem, const THREAD_ID tid)
1432{
1433 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
1434 {
1435 _assembly[tid][i]->reinit(elem);
1436 _nl[i]->prepare(tid);
1437
1438 // This method is called outside of residual/Jacobian callbacks during initial condition
1439 // evaluation
1440 if ((!_has_jacobian || !_const_jacobian) && currentlyComputingJacobian())
1441 _assembly[tid][i]->prepareJacobianBlock();
1442 _assembly[tid][i]->prepareResidual();
1443 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling && currentlyComputingJacobian())
1444 _assembly[tid][i]->prepareNonlocal();
1445 }
1446 _aux->prepare(tid);
1447
1448 if (_displaced_problem &&
1449 // _reinit_displaced_neighbor applies to interface type objects which will do computations
1450 // based on both elem and neighbor. Consequently, despite what you might think by its name, we
1451 // must make sure we prepare the displaced elem
1452 (_reinit_displaced_elem || _reinit_displaced_face || _reinit_displaced_neighbor))
1453 {
1454 _displaced_problem->prepare(_displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), tid);
1455 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1456 _displaced_problem->prepareNonlocal(tid);
1457 }
1458}
1459
1460void
1461FEProblemBase::prepareFace(const Elem * elem, const THREAD_ID tid)
1462{
1463 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1464 nl->prepareFace(tid, true);
1465 _aux->prepareFace(tid, false);
1466
1467 if (_displaced_problem && (_reinit_displaced_elem || _reinit_displaced_face))
1468 _displaced_problem->prepareFace(_displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), tid);
1469}
1470
1471void
1472FEProblemBase::prepare(const Elem * elem,
1473 unsigned int ivar,
1474 unsigned int jvar,
1475 const std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
1476 const THREAD_ID tid)
1477{
1478 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
1479 {
1480 _assembly[tid][i]->reinit(elem);
1481 _nl[i]->prepare(tid);
1482 }
1483
1484 _aux->prepare(tid);
1485 const auto current_nl_sys_num = _current_nl_sys->number();
1486 _assembly[tid][current_nl_sys_num]->prepareBlock(ivar, jvar, dof_indices);
1487 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1488 if (_nonlocal_cm[current_nl_sys_num](ivar, jvar) != 0)
1489 {
1490 MooseVariableFEBase & jv = _current_nl_sys->getVariable(tid, jvar);
1491 _assembly[tid][current_nl_sys_num]->prepareBlockNonlocal(
1492 ivar, jvar, dof_indices, jv.allDofIndices());
1493 }
1494
1495 if (_displaced_problem && (_reinit_displaced_elem || _reinit_displaced_face))
1496 {
1497 _displaced_problem->prepare(_displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), ivar, jvar, dof_indices, tid);
1498 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1499 if (_nonlocal_cm[current_nl_sys_num](ivar, jvar) != 0)
1500 {
1501 MooseVariableFEBase & jv = _current_nl_sys->getVariable(tid, jvar);
1502 _displaced_problem->prepareBlockNonlocal(ivar, jvar, dof_indices, jv.allDofIndices(), tid);
1503 }
1504 }
1505}

1622void
1623FEProblemBase::addCachedResidualDirectly(NumericVector<Number> & residual, const THREAD_ID tid)
1624{
1625 if (_current_nl_sys->hasVector(_current_nl_sys->timeVectorTag()))
1626 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->addCachedResidualDirectly(
1627 residual, Assembly::GlobalDataKey{}, getVectorTag(_current_nl_sys->timeVectorTag()));
1628
1629 if (_current_nl_sys->hasVector(_current_nl_sys->nonTimeVectorTag()))
1630 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->addCachedResidualDirectly(
1631 residual, Assembly::GlobalDataKey{}, getVectorTag(_current_nl_sys->nonTimeVectorTag()));
1632
1633 // We do this because by adding the cached residual directly, we cannot ensure that all of the
1634 // cached residuals are emptied after only the two add calls above
1635 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->clearCachedResiduals(Assembly::GlobalDataKey{});
1636
1637 if (_displaced_problem)
1638 _displaced_problem->addCachedResidualDirectly(residual, tid);
1639}

1736void
1737FEProblemBase::addJacobianBlockTags(SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
1738 unsigned int ivar,
1739 unsigned int jvar,
1740 const DofMap & dof_map,
1741 std::vector<dof_id_type> & dof_indices,
1742 const std::set<TagID> & tags,
1743 const THREAD_ID tid)
1744{
1745 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->addJacobianBlockTags(
1746 jacobian, ivar, jvar, dof_map, dof_indices, Assembly::GlobalDataKey{}, tags);
1747
1748 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1749 if (_nonlocal_cm[_current_nl_sys->number()](ivar, jvar) != 0)
1750 {
1751 MooseVariableFEBase & jv = _current_nl_sys->getVariable(tid, jvar);
1752 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->addJacobianBlockNonlocalTags(
1753 jacobian,
1754 ivar,
1755 jvar,
1756 dof_map,
1757 dof_indices,
1758 jv.allDofIndices(),
1759 Assembly::GlobalDataKey{},
1760 tags);
1761 }
1762
1763 if (_displaced_problem)
1764 {
1765 _displaced_problem->addJacobianBlockTags(jacobian, ivar, jvar, dof_map, dof_indices, tags, tid);
1766 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1767 if (_nonlocal_cm[_current_nl_sys->number()](ivar, jvar) != 0)
1768 {
1769 MooseVariableFEBase & jv = _current_nl_sys->getVariable(tid, jvar);
1770 _displaced_problem->addJacobianBlockNonlocal(
1771 jacobian, ivar, jvar, dof_map, dof_indices, jv.allDofIndices(), tags, tid);
1772 }
1773 }
1774}

1849
1850bool
1851FEProblemBase::reinitDirac(const Elem * elem, const THREAD_ID tid)
1852{
1853 std::vector<Point> & points = _dirac_kernel_info.getPoints()[elem].first;
1854
1855 unsigned int n_points = points.size();
1856
1857 if (n_points)
1858 {
1859 if (n_points > _max_qps)
1860 {
1861 _max_qps = n_points;
1862
1867 unsigned int max_qpts = getMaxQps();
1868 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
1869 {
1870 // the highest available order in libMesh is 43
1871 _scalar_zero[tid].resize(FORTYTHIRD, 0);
1872 _zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, 0);
1873 _grad_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
1874 _second_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealTensor(0.));
1875 _vector_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
1876 _vector_curl_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
1877 }
1878 }
1879
1880 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
1881 {
1882 _assembly[tid][i]->reinitAtPhysical(elem, points);
1883 _nl[i]->prepare(tid);
1884 }
1885 _aux->prepare(tid);
1886
1887 reinitElem(elem, tid);
1888 }
1889
1890 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->prepare();
1891 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1892 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->prepareNonlocal();
1893
1894 bool have_points = n_points > 0;
1895 if (_displaced_problem && (_reinit_displaced_elem))
1896 {
1897 have_points |= _displaced_problem->reinitDirac(_displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), tid);
1898 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1899 _displaced_problem->prepareNonlocal(tid);
1900 }
1901
1902 return have_points;
1903}
1904
1905void
1906FEProblemBase::reinitElem(const Elem * elem, const THREAD_ID tid)
1907{
1908 for (auto & nl : _nl)
1909 nl->reinitElem(elem, tid);
1910 _aux->reinitElem(elem, tid);
1911
1912 if (_displaced_problem && _reinit_displaced_elem)
1913 _displaced_problem->reinitElem(_displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), tid);
1914}
1915
1916void
1917FEProblemBase::reinitElemPhys(const Elem * elem,
1918 const std::vector<Point> & phys_points_in_elem,
1919 const THREAD_ID tid)
1920{
1921 mooseAssert(_mesh.queryElemPtr(elem->id()) == elem,
1922 "Are you calling this method with a displaced mesh element?");
1923
1924 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
1925 {
1926 _assembly[tid][i]->reinitAtPhysical(elem, phys_points_in_elem);
1927 _nl[i]->prepare(tid);
1928 _assembly[tid][i]->prepare();
1929 if (_has_nonlocal_coupling)
1930 _assembly[tid][i]->prepareNonlocal();
1931 }
1932 _aux->prepare(tid);
1933
1934 reinitElem(elem, tid);
1935}

2017void
2018FEProblemBase::reinitScalars(const THREAD_ID tid, bool reinit_for_derivative_reordering /*=false*/)
2019{
2020 TIME_SECTION("reinitScalars", 3, "Reinitializing Scalar Variables");
2021

2023 _displaced_problem->reinitScalars(tid, reinit_for_derivative_reordering);

2026 nl->reinitScalars(tid, reinit_for_derivative_reordering);
2027 _aux->reinitScalars(tid, reinit_for_derivative_reordering);
2028
2029 // This is called outside of residual/Jacobian call-backs
2030 for (auto & assembly : _assembly[tid])
2031 assembly->prepareScalar();
2032}

2041
2042void
2043FEProblemBase::reinitNeighbor(const Elem * elem, unsigned int side, const THREAD_ID tid)
2044{
2045 setNeighborSubdomainID(elem, side, tid);
2046
2047 const Elem * neighbor = elem->neighbor_ptr(side);
2048 unsigned int neighbor_side = neighbor->which_neighbor_am_i(elem);
2049
2050 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
2051 {
2052 _assembly[tid][i]->reinitElemAndNeighbor(elem, side, neighbor, neighbor_side);
2053 _nl[i]->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2054 // Called during stateful material property evaluation outside of solve
2055 _assembly[tid][i]->prepareNeighbor();
2056 }
2057 _aux->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2058
2059 BoundaryID bnd_id = 0; // some dummy number (it is not really used for anything, right now)
2060 for (auto & nl : _nl)
2061 {
2062 nl->reinitElemFace(elem, side, bnd_id, tid);
2063 nl->reinitNeighborFace(neighbor, neighbor_side, bnd_id, tid);
2064 }
2065 _aux->reinitElemFace(elem, side, bnd_id, tid);
2066 _aux->reinitNeighborFace(neighbor, neighbor_side, bnd_id, tid);
2067
2068 if (_displaced_problem && _reinit_displaced_neighbor)
2069 {
2070 // There are cases like for cohesive zone modeling without significant sliding where we cannot
2071 // use FEInterface::inverse_map in Assembly::reinitElemAndNeighbor in the displaced problem
2072 // because the physical points coming from the element don't actually lie on the neighbor.
2073 // Moreover, what's the point of doing another physical point inversion in other cases? We only
2074 // care about the reference points which we can just take from the undisplaced computation
2075 const auto & displaced_ref_pts = _assembly[tid][0]->qRuleNeighbor()->get_points();
2076
2077 _displaced_problem->reinitNeighbor(
2078 _displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), side, tid, &displaced_ref_pts);
2079 }
2080}
2081
2082void
2083FEProblemBase::reinitElemNeighborAndLowerD(const Elem * elem,
2084 unsigned int side,
2085 const THREAD_ID tid)
2086{
2087 reinitNeighbor(elem, side, tid);
2088
2089 const Elem * lower_d_elem = _mesh.getLowerDElem(elem, side);
2090 if (lower_d_elem && lower_d_elem->subdomain_id() == Moose::INTERNAL_SIDE_LOWERD_ID)
2091 reinitLowerDElem(lower_d_elem, tid);
2092 else
2093 {
2094 // with mesh refinement, lower-dimensional element might be defined on neighbor side
2095 auto & neighbor = _assembly[tid][0]->neighbor();
2096 auto & neighbor_side = _assembly[tid][0]->neighborSide();
2097 const Elem * lower_d_elem_neighbor = _mesh.getLowerDElem(neighbor, neighbor_side);
2098 if (lower_d_elem_neighbor &&
2099 lower_d_elem_neighbor->subdomain_id() == Moose::INTERNAL_SIDE_LOWERD_ID)
2100 {
2101 auto qps = _assembly[tid][0]->qPointsFaceNeighbor().stdVector();
2102 std::vector<Point> reference_points;
2103 FEInterface::inverse_map(
2104 lower_d_elem_neighbor->dim(), FEType(), lower_d_elem_neighbor, qps, reference_points);
2105 reinitLowerDElem(lower_d_elem_neighbor, tid, &reference_points);
2106 }
2107 }
2108
2109 if (_displaced_problem &&
2110 (_reinit_displaced_elem || _reinit_displaced_face || _reinit_displaced_neighbor))
2111 _displaced_problem->reinitElemNeighborAndLowerD(
2112 _displaced_mesh->elemPtr(elem->id()), side, tid);
2113}
2114
2115void
2116FEProblemBase::reinitNeighborPhys(const Elem * neighbor,
2117 unsigned int neighbor_side,
2118 const std::vector<Point> & physical_points,
2119 const THREAD_ID tid)
2120{
2121 mooseAssert(_mesh.queryElemPtr(neighbor->id()) == neighbor,
2122 "Are you calling this method with a displaced mesh element?");
2123
2124 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
2125 {
2126 // Reinits shape the functions at the physical points
2127 _assembly[tid][i]->reinitNeighborAtPhysical(neighbor, neighbor_side, physical_points);
2128
2129 // Sets the neighbor dof indices
2130 _nl[i]->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2131 }
2132 _aux->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2133
2134 // Resizes Re and Ke
2135 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->prepareNeighbor();
2136
2137 // Compute the values of each variable at the points
2138 for (auto & nl : _nl)
2139 nl->reinitNeighborFace(neighbor, neighbor_side, 0, tid);
2140 _aux->reinitNeighborFace(neighbor, neighbor_side, 0, tid);
2141}
2142
2143void
2144FEProblemBase::reinitNeighborPhys(const Elem * neighbor,
2145 const std::vector<Point> & physical_points,
2146 const THREAD_ID tid)
2147{
2148 mooseAssert(_mesh.queryElemPtr(neighbor->id()) == neighbor,
2149 "Are you calling this method with a displaced mesh element?");
2150
2151 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
2152 {
2153 // Reinits shape the functions at the physical points
2154 _assembly[tid][i]->reinitNeighborAtPhysical(neighbor, physical_points);
2155
2156 // Sets the neighbor dof indices
2157 _nl[i]->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2158 }
2159 _aux->prepareNeighbor(tid);
2160
2161 // Resizes Re and Ke
2162 _assembly[tid][_current_nl_sys->number()]->prepareNeighbor();
2163
2164 // Compute the values of each variable at the points
2165 for (auto & nl : _nl)
2166 nl->reinitNeighbor(neighbor, tid);
2167 _aux->reinitNeighbor(neighbor, tid);
2168}
2169
2170void
2171FEProblemBase::getDiracElements(std::set<const Elem *> & elems)
2172{
2173 // First add in the undisplaced elements
2174 elems = _dirac_kernel_info.getElements();
2175
2176 if (_displaced_problem)
2177 {
2178 std::set<const Elem *> displaced_elements;
2179 _displaced_problem->getDiracElements(displaced_elements);
2180
2181 { // Use the ids from the displaced elements to get the undisplaced elements
2182 // and add them to the list
2183 for (const auto & elem : displaced_elements)
2184 elems.insert(_mesh.elemPtr(elem->id()));
2185 }
2186 }
2187}

2219
2220void
2221FEProblemBase::addFunction(const std::string & type,
2222 const std::string & name,
2223 InputParameters & parameters)
2224{
2225 parallel_object_only();
2226
2227 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
2228
2229 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
2230 {
2231 std::shared_ptr<Function> func = _factory.create<Function>(type, name, parameters, tid);
2232 logAdd("Function", name, type);
2233 _functions.addObject(func, tid);
2234
2235 if (auto * const functor = dynamic_cast<Moose::FunctorBase<Real> *>(func.get()))
2236 {
2237 this->addFunctor(name, *functor, tid);
2238 if (_displaced_problem)
2239 _displaced_problem->addFunctor(name, *functor, tid);
2240 }
2241 else
2242 mooseError("Unrecognized function functor type");
2243 }
2244}
2245
2246bool
2247FEProblemBase::hasFunction(const std::string & name, const THREAD_ID tid)
2248{
2249 return _functions.hasActiveObject(name, tid);
2250}
2251
2252Function &
2253FEProblemBase::getFunction(const std::string & name, const THREAD_ID tid)
2254{
2255 // This thread lock is necessary since this method will create functions
2256 // for all threads if one is missing.
2257 Threads::spin_mutex::scoped_lock lock(get_function_mutex);
2258
2259 if (!hasFunction(name, tid))
2260 {
2261 // If we didn't find a function, it might be a default function, attempt to construct one now
2262 std::istringstream ss(name);
2263 Real real_value;
2264
2265 // First see if it's just a constant. If it is, build a ConstantFunction
2266 if (ss >> real_value && ss.eof())
2267 {
2268 InputParameters params = _factory.getValidParams("ConstantFunction");
2269 params.set<Real>("value") = real_value;
2270 addFunction("ConstantFunction", ss.str(), params);
2271 }
2272 else
2273 {
2274 FunctionParserBase<Real> fp;
2275 std::string vars = "x,y,z,t,NaN,pi,e";
2276 if (fp.Parse(name, vars) == -1) // -1 for success
2277 {
2278 // It parsed ok, so build a MooseParsedFunction
2279 InputParameters params = _factory.getValidParams("ParsedFunction");
2280 params.set<std::string>("expression") = name;
2281 addFunction("ParsedFunction", name, params);
2282 }
2283 }
2284
2285 // Try once more
2286 if (!hasFunction(name, tid))
2287 mooseError("Unable to find function " + name);
2288 }
2289
2290 auto * const ret = dynamic_cast<Function *>(_functions.getActiveObject(name, tid).get());
2291 if (!ret)
2292 mooseError("No function named ", name, " of appropriate type");
2293
2294 return *ret;
2295}
2296
2297void
2298FEProblemBase::addMeshDivision(const std::string & type,
2299 const std::string & name,
2300 InputParameters & parameters)
2301{
2302 parallel_object_only();
2303 parameters.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2304 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
2305 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
2306 {
2307 std::shared_ptr<MeshDivision> func = _factory.create<MeshDivision>(type, name, parameters, tid);
2308 _mesh_divisions.addObject(func, tid);
2309 }
2310}

2315 auto * const ret = dynamic_cast<MeshDivision *>(_mesh_divisions.getActiveObject(name, tid).get());
2316 if (!ret)
2317 mooseError("No MeshDivision object named ", name, " of appropriate type");
2318 return *ret;
2319}

2330 mooseDeprecated("FEProblemBase::getNonlinearSystem() is deprecated, please use "

2392
2393bool
2394FEProblemBase::duplicateVariableCheck(const std::string & var_name,
2395 const FEType & type,
2396 bool is_aux)
2397{
2398 for (auto & nl : _nl)
2399 {
2400 SystemBase * curr_sys_ptr = nl.get();
2401 SystemBase * other_sys_ptr = _aux.get();
2402 std::string error_prefix = "";
2403 if (is_aux)
2404 {
2405 curr_sys_ptr = _aux.get();
2406 other_sys_ptr = nl.get();
2407 error_prefix = "Aux";
2408 }
2409
2410 if (other_sys_ptr->hasVariable(var_name))
2411 mooseError("Cannot have an auxiliary variable and a nonlinear variable with the same name: ",
2412 var_name);
2413
2414 if (curr_sys_ptr->hasVariable(var_name))
2415 {
2416 const Variable & var =
2417 curr_sys_ptr->system().variable(curr_sys_ptr->system().variable_number(var_name));
2418 if (var.type() != type)
2419 mooseError(error_prefix,
2420 "Variable with name '",
2421 var_name,
2422 "' already exists but is of a differing type!");
2423
2424 return true;
2425 }
2426 }
2427
2428 return false;
2429}
2430
2431void
2432FEProblemBase::addVariable(const std::string & var_type,
2433 const std::string & var_name,
2434 InputParameters & params)
2435{
2436 parallel_object_only();
2437
2438 auto fe_type = FEType(Utility::string_to_enum<Order>(params.get<MooseEnum>("order")),
2439 Utility::string_to_enum<FEFamily>(params.get<MooseEnum>("family")));
2440
2441 if (duplicateVariableCheck(var_name, fe_type, /* is_aux = */ false))
2442 return;
2443
2444 params.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2445 params.set<Moose::VarKindType>("_var_kind") = Moose::VarKindType::VAR_NONLINEAR;
2446
2447 const auto & nl_sys_name = params.get<NonlinearSystemName>("nl_sys");
2448 std::istringstream ss(nl_sys_name);
2449 unsigned int nl_sys_num;
2450 if (!(ss >> nl_sys_num) || !ss.eof())
2451 nl_sys_num = libmesh_map_find(_nl_sys_name_to_num, nl_sys_name);
2452
2453 logAdd("Variable", var_name, var_type);
2454 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addVariable(var_type, var_name, params);
2455 if (_displaced_problem)
2456 // MooseObjects need to be unique so change the name here
2457 _displaced_problem->addVariable(var_type, var_name, params, nl_sys_num);
2458
2459 _nl_var_to_sys_num[var_name] = nl_sys_num;
2460}
2461
2462std::pair<bool, unsigned int>
2463FEProblemBase::determineNonlinearSystem(const std::string & var_name,
2464 const bool error_if_not_found) const
2465{
2466 auto nl_map_it = _nl_var_to_sys_num.find(var_name);
2467 const bool var_in_nl = nl_map_it != _nl_var_to_sys_num.end();
2468 if (var_in_nl)
2469 mooseAssert(_nl[nl_map_it->second]->hasVariable(var_name) ||
2470 _nl[nl_map_it->second]->hasScalarVariable(var_name),
2471 "If the variable is in our FEProblem nonlinear system map, then it must be in the "
2472 "nonlinear system we expect");
2473 else if (error_if_not_found)
2474 {
2475 if (_aux->hasVariable(var_name) || _aux->hasScalarVariable(var_name))
2476 mooseError("No nonlinear variable named ",
2477 var_name,
2478 " found. Did you specify an auxiliary variable when you meant to specify a "
2479 "nonlinear variable?");
2480 else
2481 mooseError("Unknown variable '",
2482 var_name,
2483 "'. It does not exist in the nonlinear system(s) or auxiliary system");
2484 }
2485
2486 return std::make_pair(var_in_nl, var_in_nl ? nl_map_it->second : libMesh::invalid_uint);
2487}
2488
2489void
2490FEProblemBase::addKernel(const std::string & kernel_name,
2491 const std::string & name,
2492 InputParameters & parameters)
2493{
2494 parallel_object_only();
2495
2496 const auto nl_sys_num =
2497 determineNonlinearSystem(parameters.varName("variable", name), true).second;
2498 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2499 {
2500 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
2501 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->nlSys(nl_sys_num);
2502 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
2503 }
2504 else
2505 {
2506 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2507 {
2508 // We allow Kernels to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
2509 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
2510 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
2511 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this Kernel.
2512 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2513 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
2514 }
2515
2516 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
2517 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _nl[nl_sys_num].get();
2518 }
2519
2520 logAdd("Kernel", name, kernel_name);
2521 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addKernel(kernel_name, name, parameters);
2522}

2626
2627void
2628FEProblemBase::addConstraint(const std::string & c_name,
2629 const std::string & name,
2630 InputParameters & parameters)
2631{
2632 parallel_object_only();
2633
2634 _has_constraints = true;
2635
2636 auto determine_var_param_name = [&parameters, this]()
2637 {
2638 if (parameters.isParamValid("variable"))
2639 return "variable";
2640 else
2641 {
2642 // must be a mortar constraint
2643 const bool has_secondary_var = parameters.isParamValid("secondary_variable");
2644 const bool has_primary_var = parameters.isParamValid("primary_variable");
2645 if (!has_secondary_var && !has_primary_var)
2646 mooseError(
2647 "Either a 'secondary_variable' or 'primary_variable' parameter must be supplied for '",
2648 parameters.get<std::string>("_object_name"),
2649 "'");
2650 return has_secondary_var ? "secondary_variable" : "primary_variable";
2651 }
2652 };
2653
2654 const auto nl_sys_num =
2655 determineNonlinearSystem(parameters.varName(determine_var_param_name(), name), true).second;
2656
2657 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2658 {
2659 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
2660 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->nlSys(nl_sys_num);
2661 _reinit_displaced_face = true;
2662 }
2663 else
2664 {
2665 // It might _want_ to use a displaced mesh... but we're not so set it to false
2666 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2667 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
2668
2669 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
2670 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _nl[nl_sys_num].get();
2671 }
2672
2673 logAdd("Constraint", name, c_name);
2674 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addConstraint(c_name, name, parameters);
2675}
2676
2677void
2678FEProblemBase::addAuxVariable(const std::string & var_type,
2679 const std::string & var_name,
2680 InputParameters & params)
2681{
2682 parallel_object_only();
2683
2684 auto fe_type = FEType(Utility::string_to_enum<Order>(params.get<MooseEnum>("order")),
2685 Utility::string_to_enum<FEFamily>(params.get<MooseEnum>("family")));
2686
2687 if (duplicateVariableCheck(var_name, fe_type, /* is_aux = */ true))
2688 return;
2689
2690 params.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2691 params.set<Moose::VarKindType>("_var_kind") = Moose::VarKindType::VAR_AUXILIARY;
2692
2693 logAdd("AuxVariable", var_name, var_type);
2694 _aux->addVariable(var_type, var_name, params);
2695 if (_displaced_problem)
2696 // MooseObjects need to be unique so change the name here
2697 _displaced_problem->addAuxVariable(var_type, var_name, params);
2698}
2699
2700void
2701FEProblemBase::addAuxVariable(const std::string & var_name,
2702 const FEType & type,
2703 const std::set<SubdomainID> * const active_subdomains)
2704{
2705 parallel_object_only();
2706
2707 mooseDeprecated("Please use the addAuxVariable(var_type, var_name, params) API instead");
2708
2709 if (duplicateVariableCheck(var_name, type, /* is_aux = */ true))
2710 return;
2711
2712 std::string var_type;
2713 if (type == FEType(0, MONOMIAL))
2714 var_type = "MooseVariableConstMonomial";
2715 else if (type.family == SCALAR)
2716 var_type = "MooseVariableScalar";
2717 else if (type.family == LAGRANGE_VEC || type.family == NEDELEC_ONE ||
2718 type.family == MONOMIAL_VEC || type.family == RAVIART_THOMAS)
2719 var_type = "VectorMooseVariable";
2720 else
2721 var_type = "MooseVariable";
2722
2723 InputParameters params = _factory.getValidParams(var_type);
2724 params.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2725 params.set<Moose::VarKindType>("_var_kind") = Moose::VarKindType::VAR_AUXILIARY;
2726 params.set<MooseEnum>("order") = type.order.get_order();
2727 params.set<MooseEnum>("family") = Moose::stringify(type.family);
2728
2729 if (active_subdomains)
2730 for (const SubdomainID & id : *active_subdomains)
2731 params.set<std::vector<SubdomainName>>("block").push_back(Moose::stringify(id));
2732
2733 logAdd("AuxVariable", var_name, var_type);
2734 _aux->addVariable(var_type, var_name, params);
2735 if (_displaced_problem)
2736 _displaced_problem->addAuxVariable("MooseVariable", var_name, params);
2737}
2738
2739void
2740FEProblemBase::addAuxArrayVariable(const std::string & var_name,
2741 const FEType & type,
2742 unsigned int components,
2743 const std::set<SubdomainID> * const active_subdomains)
2744{
2745 parallel_object_only();
2746
2747 mooseDeprecated("Please use the addAuxVariable(var_type, var_name, params) API instead");
2748
2749 if (duplicateVariableCheck(var_name, type, /* is_aux = */ true))
2750 return;
2751
2752 InputParameters params = _factory.getValidParams("ArrayMooseVariable");
2753 params.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2754 params.set<Moose::VarKindType>("_var_kind") = Moose::VarKindType::VAR_AUXILIARY;
2755 params.set<MooseEnum>("order") = type.order.get_order();
2756 params.set<MooseEnum>("family") = Moose::stringify(type.family);
2757 params.set<unsigned int>("components") = components;
2758
2759 if (active_subdomains)
2760 for (const SubdomainID & id : *active_subdomains)
2761 params.set<std::vector<SubdomainName>>("block").push_back(Moose::stringify(id));
2762
2763 logAdd("Variable", var_name, "ArrayMooseVariable");
2764 _aux->addVariable("ArrayMooseVariable", var_name, params);
2765 if (_displaced_problem)
2766 _displaced_problem->addAuxVariable("ArrayMooseVariable", var_name, params);
2767}
2768
2769void
2770FEProblemBase::addAuxScalarVariable(const std::string & var_name,
2771 Order order,
2772 Real /*scale_factor*/,
2773 const std::set<SubdomainID> * const active_subdomains)
2774{
2775 parallel_object_only();
2776
2777 mooseDeprecated("Please use the addAuxVariable(var_type, var_name, params) API instead");
2778
2779 if (order > _max_scalar_order)
2780 _max_scalar_order = order;
2781
2782 FEType type(order, SCALAR);
2783 if (duplicateVariableCheck(var_name, type, /* is_aux = */ true))
2784 return;
2785
2786 InputParameters params = _factory.getValidParams("MooseVariableScalar");
2787 params.set<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base") = this;
2788 params.set<Moose::VarKindType>("_var_kind") = Moose::VarKindType::VAR_AUXILIARY;
2789
2790 params.set<MooseEnum>("order") = type.order.get_order();
2791 params.set<MooseEnum>("family") = "SCALAR";
2792 params.set<std::vector<Real>>("scaling") = {1};
2793 if (active_subdomains)
2794 for (const SubdomainID & id : *active_subdomains)
2795 params.set<std::vector<SubdomainName>>("block").push_back(Moose::stringify(id));
2796
2797 logAdd("ScalarVariable", var_name, "MooseVariableScalar");
2798 _aux->addVariable("MooseVariableScalar", var_name, params);
2799 if (_displaced_problem)
2800 _displaced_problem->addAuxVariable("MooseVariableScalar", var_name, params);
2801}

2803void
2804FEProblemBase::addAuxKernel(const std::string & kernel_name,
2805 const std::string & name,
2806 InputParameters & parameters)
2807{
2808 parallel_object_only();
2809
2810 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2811 {
2812 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
2813 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->auxSys();
2814 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_nl_sys") = &_displaced_problem->nlSys(0);
2815 if (!parameters.get<std::vector<BoundaryName>>("boundary").empty())
2816 _reinit_displaced_face = true;
2817 else
2818 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
2819 }
2820 else
2821 {
2822 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2823 {
2824 // We allow AuxKernels to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
2825 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
2826 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
2827 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this AuxKernel.
2828 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2829 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
2830 }
2831
2832 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
2833 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _aux.get();
2834 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_nl_sys") = _nl[0].get();
2835 }
2836
2837 logAdd("AuxKernel", name, kernel_name);
2838 _aux->addKernel(kernel_name, name, parameters);
2839}

2948void
