2950 const std::string & name,
2951 InputParameters & parameters)
2952{
2953 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
2954 // FVElementalKernels are computed in the historically finite element threaded loops. They rely
2955 // on Assembly data like _current_elem. When we call reinit on the FEProblemBase we will only
2956 // reinit the DisplacedProblem and its associated Assembly objects if we mark this boolean as
2957 // true
2958 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
2959 addObject<FVKernel>(fv_kernel_name, name, parameters);

3020
3021void
3022FEProblemBase::checkICRestartError(const std::string & ic_name,
3023 const std::string & name,
3024 const VariableName & var_name)
3025{
3026 if (!_allow_ics_during_restart)
3027 {
3028 std::string restart_method = "";
3029 if (_app.isRestarting())
3030 restart_method =
3031 "a checkpoint restart, by IC object '" + ic_name + "' for variable '" + name + "'";
3032 else if (_app.getExReaderForRestart())
3033 {
3034 std::vector<std::string> restarted_vars = _app.getExReaderForRestart()->get_elem_var_names();
3035 const auto nodal_vars = _app.getExReaderForRestart()->get_nodal_var_names();
3036 const auto global_vars = _app.getExReaderForRestart()->get_global_var_names();
3037 restarted_vars.insert(restarted_vars.end(), nodal_vars.begin(), nodal_vars.end());
3038 restarted_vars.insert(restarted_vars.end(), global_vars.begin(), global_vars.end());
3039
3040 if (std::find(restarted_vars.begin(), restarted_vars.end(), var_name) != restarted_vars.end())
3041 restart_method = "an Exodus restart, by IC object '" + ic_name + "' for variable '" + name +
3042 "' that is also being restarted";
3043 }
3044 if (!restart_method.empty())
3045 mooseError(
3046 "Initial conditions have been specified during ",
3047 restart_method,
3048 ".\nThis is only allowed if you specify 'allow_initial_conditions_with_restart' to "
3049 "the [Problem], as initial conditions can override restarted fields");
3050 }
3051}
3052
3053void
3054FEProblemBase::addInitialCondition(const std::string & ic_name,
3055 const std::string & name,
3056 InputParameters & parameters)
3057{
3058 parallel_object_only();
3059
3060 // before we start to mess with the initial condition, we need to check parameters for errors.
3061 parameters.checkParams(name);
3062 const std::string & var_name = parameters.get<VariableName>("variable");
3063
3064 // Forbid initial conditions on a restarted problem, as they would override the restart
3065 checkICRestartError(ic_name, name, var_name);
3066
3067 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
3068
3069 // field IC
3070 if (hasVariable(var_name))
3071 {
3072 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
3073 {
3074 MooseVariableFEBase & var = getVariable(
3075 tid, var_name, Moose::VarKindType::VAR_ANY, Moose::VarFieldType::VAR_FIELD_ANY);
3076 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &var.sys();
3077 std::shared_ptr<InitialConditionBase> ic;
3078 if (dynamic_cast<MooseVariable *>(&var))
3079 ic = _factory.create<InitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters, tid);
3080 else if (dynamic_cast<VectorMooseVariable *>(&var))
3081 ic = _factory.create<VectorInitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters, tid);
3082 else if (dynamic_cast<ArrayMooseVariable *>(&var))
3083 ic = _factory.create<ArrayInitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters, tid);
3084 else if (dynamic_cast<MooseVariableFVReal *>(&var))
3085 ic = _factory.create<InitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters, tid);
3086 else
3087 mooseError("Your FE variable in initial condition ",
3088 name,
3089 " must be either of scalar or vector type");
3090 logAdd("IC", name, ic_name);
3091 _ics.addObject(ic, tid);
3092 }
3093 }
3094
3095 // scalar IC
3096 else if (hasScalarVariable(var_name))
3097 {
3098 MooseVariableScalar & var = getScalarVariable(0, var_name);
3099 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &var.sys();
3100 std::shared_ptr<ScalarInitialCondition> ic =
3101 _factory.create<ScalarInitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters);
3102 logAdd("ScalarIC", name, ic_name);
3103 _scalar_ics.addObject(ic);
3104 }
3105
3106 else
3107 mooseError(
3108 "Variable '", var_name, "' requested in initial condition '", name, "' does not exist.");
3109}
3110
3111void
3112FEProblemBase::addFVInitialCondition(const std::string & ic_name,
3113 const std::string & name,
3114 InputParameters & parameters)
3115{
3116 parallel_object_only();
3117
3118 // before we start to mess with the initial condition, we need to check parameters for errors.
3119 parameters.checkParams(name);
3120 const std::string & var_name = parameters.get<VariableName>("variable");
3121
3122 // Forbid initial conditions on a restarted problem, as they would override the restart
3123 checkICRestartError(ic_name, name, var_name);
3124
3125 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
3126
3127 // field IC
3128 if (hasVariable(var_name))
3129 {
3130 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
3131 {
3132 auto & var = getVariable(
3133 tid, var_name, Moose::VarKindType::VAR_ANY, Moose::VarFieldType::VAR_FIELD_ANY);
3134 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &var.sys();
3135 std::shared_ptr<FVInitialConditionBase> ic;
3136 if (dynamic_cast<MooseVariableFVReal *>(&var))
3137 ic = _factory.create<FVInitialCondition>(ic_name, name, parameters, tid);
3138 else
3139 mooseError(
3140 "Your variable for an FVInitialCondition needs to be an a finite volume variable!");
3141 _fv_ics.addObject(ic, tid);
3142 }
3143 }
3144 else
3145 mooseError("Variable '",
3146 var_name,
3147 "' requested in finite volume initial condition '",
3148 name,
3149 "' does not exist.");
3150}
3151
3152void
3153FEProblemBase::projectSolution()
3154{
3155 TIME_SECTION("projectSolution", 2, "Projecting Initial Solutions")
3156
3157 FloatingPointExceptionGuard fpe_guard(_app);
3158
3159 ConstElemRange & elem_range = *_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange();
3160 ComputeInitialConditionThread cic(*this);
3161 Threads::parallel_reduce(elem_range, cic);
3162
3163 if (haveFV())
3164 {
3165 using ElemInfoRange = StoredRange<MooseMesh::const_elem_info_iterator, const ElemInfo *>;
3166 ElemInfoRange elem_info_range(_mesh.ownedElemInfoBegin(), _mesh.ownedElemInfoEnd());
3167
3168 ComputeFVInitialConditionThread cfvic(*this);
3169 Threads::parallel_reduce(elem_info_range, cfvic);
3170 }
3171
3172 // Need to close the solution vector here so that boundary ICs take precendence
3173 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3174 nl->solution().close();
3175 _aux->solution().close();
3176
3177 // now run boundary-restricted initial conditions
3178 ConstBndNodeRange & bnd_nodes = *_mesh.getBoundaryNodeRange();
3179 ComputeBoundaryInitialConditionThread cbic(*this);
3180 Threads::parallel_reduce(bnd_nodes, cbic);
3181
3182 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3183 nl->solution().close();
3184 _aux->solution().close();
3185
3186 // Also, load values into the SCALAR dofs
3187 // Note: We assume that all SCALAR dofs are on the
3188 // processor with highest ID
3189 if (processor_id() == (n_processors() - 1) && _scalar_ics.hasActiveObjects())
3190 {
3191 const auto & ics = _scalar_ics.getActiveObjects();
3192 for (const auto & ic : ics)
3193 {
3194 MooseVariableScalar & var = ic->variable();
3195 var.reinit();
3196
3197 DenseVector<Number> vals(var.order());
3198 ic->compute(vals);
3199
3200 const unsigned int n_SCALAR_dofs = var.dofIndices().size();
3201 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_SCALAR_dofs; i++)
3202 {
3203 const dof_id_type global_index = var.dofIndices()[i];
3204 var.sys().solution().set(global_index, vals(i));
3205 var.setValue(i, vals(i));
3206 }
3207 }
3208 }
3209
3210 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3211 {
3212 nl->solution().close();
3213 nl->solution().localize(*nl->system().current_local_solution, nl->dofMap().get_send_list());
3214 }
3215
3216 _aux->solution().close();
3217 _aux->solution().localize(*_aux->sys().current_local_solution, _aux->dofMap().get_send_list());
3218}
3219
3220void
3221FEProblemBase::projectInitialConditionOnCustomRange(ConstElemRange & elem_range,
3222 ConstBndNodeRange & bnd_nodes)
3223{
3224 ComputeInitialConditionThread cic(*this);
3225 Threads::parallel_reduce(elem_range, cic);
3226
3227 // Need to close the solution vector here so that boundary ICs take precendence
3228 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3229 nl->solution().close();
3230 _aux->solution().close();
3231
3232 ComputeBoundaryInitialConditionThread cbic(*this);
3233 Threads::parallel_reduce(bnd_nodes, cbic);
3234
3235 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3236 nl->solution().close();
3237 _aux->solution().close();
3238
3239 // Also, load values into the SCALAR dofs
3240 // Note: We assume that all SCALAR dofs are on the
3241 // processor with highest ID
3242 if (processor_id() == (n_processors() - 1) && _scalar_ics.hasActiveObjects())
3243 {
3244 const auto & ics = _scalar_ics.getActiveObjects();
3245 for (const auto & ic : ics)
3246 {
3247 MooseVariableScalar & var = ic->variable();
3248 var.reinit();
3249
3250 DenseVector<Number> vals(var.order());
3251 ic->compute(vals);
3252
3253 const unsigned int n_SCALAR_dofs = var.dofIndices().size();
3254 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_SCALAR_dofs; i++)
3255 {
3256 const dof_id_type global_index = var.dofIndices()[i];
3257 var.sys().solution().set(global_index, vals(i));
3258 var.setValue(i, vals(i));
3259 }
3260 }
3261 }
3262
3263 for (auto & nl : _nl)
3264 {
3265 nl->solution().close();
3266 nl->solution().localize(*nl->system().current_local_solution, nl->dofMap().get_send_list());
3267 }
3268
3269 _aux->solution().close();
3270 _aux->solution().localize(*_aux->sys().current_local_solution, _aux->dofMap().get_send_list());
3271}
3272
3273std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase>
3274FEProblemBase::getMaterial(std::string name,
3275 Moose::MaterialDataType type,
3276 const THREAD_ID tid,
3277 bool no_warn)
3278{
3279 switch (type)
3280 {
3281 case Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA:
3282 name += "_neighbor";
3283 break;
3284 case Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA:
3285 name += "_face";
3286 break;
3287 default:
3288 break;
3289 }
3290
3291 std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> material = _all_materials[type].getActiveObject(name, tid);
3292 if (!no_warn && material->getParam<bool>("compute") && type == Moose::BLOCK_MATERIAL_DATA)
3293 mooseWarning("You are retrieving a Material object (",
3294 material->name(),
3295 "), but its compute flag is set to true. This indicates that MOOSE is "
3296 "computing this property which may not be desired and produce un-expected "
3297 "results.");
3298
3299 return material;
3300}
3301
3302MaterialData &
3303FEProblemBase::getMaterialData(Moose::MaterialDataType type, const THREAD_ID tid)
3304{
3305 switch (type)
3306 {
3307 case Moose::BLOCK_MATERIAL_DATA:
3308 return _material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3309 case Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA:
3310 return _neighbor_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3311 case Moose::BOUNDARY_MATERIAL_DATA:
3312 case Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA:
3313 case Moose::INTERFACE_MATERIAL_DATA:
3314 return _bnd_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3315 }
3316
3317 mooseError("FEProblemBase::getMaterialData(): Invalid MaterialDataType ", type);
3318}

3320void
3321FEProblemBase::addFunctorMaterial(const std::string & functor_material_name,
3322 const std::string & name,
3323 InputParameters & parameters)
3324{
3325 parallel_object_only();
3326
3327 auto add_functor_materials = [&](const auto & parameters, const auto & name)
3328 {
3329 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
3330 {
3331 // Create the general Block/Boundary MaterialBase object
3332 std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> material =
3333 _factory.create<MaterialBase>(functor_material_name, name, parameters, tid);
3334 logAdd("FunctorMaterial", name, functor_material_name);
3335 _all_materials.addObject(material, tid);
3336 _materials.addObject(material, tid);
3337 }
3338 };
3339
3340 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
3341 add_functor_materials(parameters, name);
3342 if (_displaced_problem)
3343 {
3344 auto disp_params = parameters;
3345 disp_params.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
3346 add_functor_materials(disp_params, name + "_displaced");
3347 }
3348}

3355 addMaterialHelper({&_materials}, mat_name, name, parameters);
3356}

3363 addMaterialHelper({&_interface_materials}, mat_name, name, parameters);

3365
3366void
3367FEProblemBase::addMaterialHelper(std::vector<MaterialWarehouse *> warehouses,
3368 const std::string & mat_name,
3369 const std::string & name,
3370 InputParameters & parameters)
3371{
3372 parallel_object_only();
3373
3374 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3375 {
3376 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
3377 _reinit_displaced_elem = _reinit_displaced_face = _reinit_displaced_neighbor = true;
3378 }
3379 else
3380 {
3381 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3382 {
3383 // We allow Materials to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
3384 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
3385 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
3386 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this Material.
3387 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3388 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
3389 }
3390
3391 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
3392 }
3393
3394 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
3395 {
3396 // Create the general Block/Boundary MaterialBase object
3397 std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> material =
3398 _factory.create<MaterialBase>(mat_name, name, parameters, tid);
3399 logAdd("Material", name, mat_name);
3400 bool discrete = !material->getParam<bool>("compute");
3401
3402 // If the object is boundary restricted or if it is a functor material we do not create the
3403 // neighbor and face objects
3404 if (material->boundaryRestricted() || dynamic_cast<FunctorMaterial *>(material.get()))
3405 {
3406 _all_materials.addObject(material, tid);
3407 if (discrete)
3408 _discrete_materials.addObject(material, tid);
3409 else
3410 for (auto && warehouse : warehouses)
3411 warehouse->addObject(material, tid);
3412 }
3413
3414 // Non-boundary restricted require face and neighbor objects
3415 else
3416 {
3417 // TODO: we only need to do this if we have needs for face materials (e.g.
3418 // FV, DG, etc.) - but currently we always do it. Figure out how to fix
3419 // this.
3420
3421 // The name of the object being created, this is changed multiple times as objects are
3422 // created below
3423 std::string object_name;
3424
3425 // Create a copy of the supplied parameters to the setting for "_material_data_type" isn't
3426 // used from a previous tid loop
3427 InputParameters current_parameters = parameters;
3428
3429 // face material
3430 current_parameters.set<Moose::MaterialDataType>("_material_data_type") =
3431 Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA;
3432 object_name = name + "_face";
3433 std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> face_material =
3434 _factory.create<MaterialBase>(mat_name, object_name, current_parameters, tid);
3435
3436 // neighbor material
3437 current_parameters.set<Moose::MaterialDataType>("_material_data_type") =
3438 Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA;
3439 current_parameters.set<bool>("_neighbor") = true;
3440 object_name = name + "_neighbor";
3441 std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> neighbor_material =
3442 _factory.create<MaterialBase>(mat_name, object_name, current_parameters, tid);
3443
3444 // Store the material objects
3445 _all_materials.addObjects(material, neighbor_material, face_material, tid);
3446
3447 if (discrete)
3448 _discrete_materials.addObjects(material, neighbor_material, face_material, tid);
3449 else
3450 for (auto && warehouse : warehouses)
3451 warehouse->addObjects(material, neighbor_material, face_material, tid);
3452
3453 // Names of all controllable parameters for this Material object
3454 const std::string & base = parameters.get<std::string>("_moose_base");
3455 MooseObjectParameterName name(MooseObjectName(base, material->name()), "*");
3456 const auto param_names =
3457 _app.getInputParameterWarehouse().getControllableParameterNames(name);
3458
3459 // Connect parameters of the primary Material object to those on the face and neighbor
3460 // objects
3461 for (const auto & p_name : param_names)
3462 {
3463 MooseObjectParameterName primary_name(MooseObjectName(base, material->name()),
3464 p_name.parameter());
3465 MooseObjectParameterName face_name(MooseObjectName(base, face_material->name()),
3466 p_name.parameter());
3467 MooseObjectParameterName neighbor_name(MooseObjectName(base, neighbor_material->name()),
3468 p_name.parameter());
3469 _app.getInputParameterWarehouse().addControllableParameterConnection(
3470 primary_name, face_name, false);
3471 _app.getInputParameterWarehouse().addControllableParameterConnection(
3472 primary_name, neighbor_name, false);
3473 }
3474 }
3475 }
3476}
3477
3478void
3479FEProblemBase::prepareMaterials(SubdomainID blk_id, const THREAD_ID tid)
3480{
3481 std::set<MooseVariableFEBase *> needed_moose_vars;
3482 std::set<unsigned int> needed_mat_props;
3483
3484 if (_all_materials.hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3485 {
3486 _all_materials.updateVariableDependency(needed_moose_vars, tid);
3487 _all_materials.updateBlockMatPropDependency(blk_id, needed_mat_props, tid);
3488 }
3489
3490 const std::set<BoundaryID> & ids = _mesh.getSubdomainBoundaryIds(blk_id);
3491 for (const auto & id : ids)
3492 {
3493 _materials.updateBoundaryVariableDependency(id, needed_moose_vars, tid);
3494 _materials.updateBoundaryMatPropDependency(id, needed_mat_props, tid);
3495 }
3496
3497 const std::set<MooseVariableFEBase *> & current_active_elemental_moose_variables =
3498 getActiveElementalMooseVariables(tid);
3499 needed_moose_vars.insert(current_active_elemental_moose_variables.begin(),
3500 current_active_elemental_moose_variables.end());
3501
3502 const std::set<unsigned int> & current_active_material_properties =
3503 getActiveMaterialProperties(tid);
3504 needed_mat_props.insert(current_active_material_properties.begin(),
3505 current_active_material_properties.end());
3506
3507 setActiveElementalMooseVariables(needed_moose_vars, tid);
3508 setActiveMaterialProperties(needed_mat_props, tid);
3509}
3510
3511void
3512FEProblemBase::reinitMaterials(SubdomainID blk_id, const THREAD_ID tid, bool swap_stateful)
3513{
3514 if (hasActiveMaterialProperties(tid))
3515 {
3516 auto && elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3517 unsigned int n_points = _assembly[tid][0]->qRule()->n_points();
3518
3519 auto & material_data = _material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3520 material_data.resize(n_points);
3521
3522 // Only swap if requested
3523 if (swap_stateful)
3524 material_data.swap(*elem);
3525
3526 if (_discrete_materials.hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3527 material_data.reset(_discrete_materials.getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3528
3529 if (_materials.hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3530 material_data.reinit(_materials.getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3531 }
3532}
3533
3534void
3535FEProblemBase::reinitMaterialsFace(const SubdomainID blk_id,
3536 const THREAD_ID tid,
3537 const bool swap_stateful,
3538 const std::deque<MaterialBase *> * const reinit_mats)
3539{
3540 if (hasActiveMaterialProperties(tid))
3541 {
3542 auto && elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3543 unsigned int side = _assembly[tid][0]->side();
3544 unsigned int n_points = _assembly[tid][0]->qRuleFace()->n_points();
3545
3546 auto & bnd_material_data = _bnd_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3547 bnd_material_data.resize(n_points);
3548
3549 if (swap_stateful && !bnd_material_data.isSwapped())
3550 bnd_material_data.swap(*elem, side);
3551
3552 if (_discrete_materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3553 bnd_material_data.reset(
3554 _discrete_materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3555
3556 if (reinit_mats)
3557 bnd_material_data.reinit(*reinit_mats);
3558 else if (_materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3559 bnd_material_data.reinit(
3560 _materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3561 }
3562}
3563
3564void
3565FEProblemBase::reinitMaterialsNeighbor(const SubdomainID blk_id,
3566 const THREAD_ID tid,
3567 const bool swap_stateful,
3568 const std::deque<MaterialBase *> * const reinit_mats)
3569{
3570 if (hasActiveMaterialProperties(tid))
3571 {
3572 // NOTE: this will not work with h-adaptivity
3573 // lindsayad: why not?
3574
3575 const Elem * neighbor = _assembly[tid][0]->neighbor();
3576 unsigned int neighbor_side = neighbor->which_neighbor_am_i(_assembly[tid][0]->elem());
3577
3578 mooseAssert(neighbor, "neighbor should be non-null");
3579 mooseAssert(blk_id == neighbor->subdomain_id(),
3580 "The provided blk_id " << blk_id << " and neighbor subdomain ID "
3581 << neighbor->subdomain_id() << " do not match.");
3582
3583 unsigned int n_points = _assembly[tid][0]->qRuleNeighbor()->n_points();
3584
3585 auto & neighbor_material_data = _neighbor_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3586 neighbor_material_data.resize(n_points);
3587
3588 // Only swap if requested
3589 if (swap_stateful)
3590 neighbor_material_data.swap(*neighbor, neighbor_side);
3591
3592 if (_discrete_materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3593 neighbor_material_data.reset(
3594 _discrete_materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3595
3596 if (reinit_mats)
3597 neighbor_material_data.reinit(*reinit_mats);
3598 else if (_materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
3599 neighbor_material_data.reinit(
3600 _materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid));
3601 }
3602}
3603
3604void
3605FEProblemBase::reinitMaterialsBoundary(const BoundaryID boundary_id,
3606 const THREAD_ID tid,
3607 const bool swap_stateful,
3608 const std::deque<MaterialBase *> * const reinit_mats)
3609{
3610 if (hasActiveMaterialProperties(tid))
3611 {
3612 auto && elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3613 unsigned int side = _assembly[tid][0]->side();
3614 unsigned int n_points = _assembly[tid][0]->qRuleFace()->n_points();
3615
3616 auto & bnd_material_data = _bnd_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3617 bnd_material_data.resize(n_points);
3618
3619 if (swap_stateful && !bnd_material_data.isSwapped())
3620 bnd_material_data.swap(*elem, side);
3621
3622 if (_discrete_materials.hasActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid))
3623 bnd_material_data.reset(_discrete_materials.getActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid));
3624
3625 if (reinit_mats)
3626 bnd_material_data.reinit(*reinit_mats);
3627 else if (_materials.hasActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid))
3628 bnd_material_data.reinit(_materials.getActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid));
3629 }
3630}

3632void
3633FEProblemBase::reinitMaterialsInterface(BoundaryID boundary_id,
3634 const THREAD_ID tid,
3635 bool swap_stateful)
3636{
3637 if (hasActiveMaterialProperties(tid))
3638 {
3639 const Elem * const & elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3640 unsigned int side = _assembly[tid][0]->side();
3641 unsigned int n_points = _assembly[tid][0]->qRuleFace()->n_points();
3642
3643 auto & bnd_material_data = _bnd_material_props.getMaterialData(tid);
3644 bnd_material_data.resize(n_points);
3645

3647 bnd_material_data.swap(*elem, side);
3648
3649 if (_interface_materials.hasActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid))
3650 bnd_material_data.reinit(_interface_materials.getActiveBoundaryObjects(boundary_id, tid));

3654void
3655FEProblemBase::swapBackMaterials(const THREAD_ID tid)
3656{
3657 auto && elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3658 _material_props.getMaterialData(tid).swapBack(*elem);
3659}
3660
3661void
3662FEProblemBase::swapBackMaterialsFace(const THREAD_ID tid)
3663{
3664 auto && elem = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3665 unsigned int side = _assembly[tid][0]->side();
3666 _bnd_material_props.getMaterialData(tid).swapBack(*elem, side);
3667}
3668
3669void
3670FEProblemBase::swapBackMaterialsNeighbor(const THREAD_ID tid)
3671{
3672 // NOTE: this will not work with h-adaptivity
3673 const Elem * neighbor = _assembly[tid][0]->neighbor();
3674 unsigned int neighbor_side =
3675 neighbor ? neighbor->which_neighbor_am_i(_assembly[tid][0]->elem()) : libMesh::invalid_uint;
3676
3677 if (!neighbor)
3678 {
3679 if (haveFV())
3680 {
3681 // If neighbor is null, then we're on the neighbor side of a mesh boundary, e.g. we're off
3682 // the mesh in ghost-land. If we're using the finite volume method, then variable values and
3683 // consequently material properties have well-defined values in this ghost region outside of
3684 // the mesh and we really do want to reinit our neighbor materials in this case. Since we're
3685 // off in ghost land it's safe to do swaps with `MaterialPropertyStorage` using the elem and
3686 // elem_side keys
3687 neighbor = _assembly[tid][0]->elem();
3688 neighbor_side = _assembly[tid][0]->side();
3689 mooseAssert(neighbor, "We should have an appropriate value for elem coming from Assembly");
3690 }
3691 else
3692 mooseError("neighbor is null in Assembly!");
3693 }
3694
3695 _neighbor_material_props.getMaterialData(tid).swapBack(*neighbor, neighbor_side);
3696}

3698void
3699FEProblemBase::logAdd(const std::string & system,
3700 const std::string & name,
3701 const std::string & type) const
3702{
3703 if (_verbose_setup)
3704 _console << "[DBG] Adding " << system << " '" << name << "' of type " << type << std::endl;
3705}
3706
3707void
3708FEProblemBase::addObjectParamsHelper(InputParameters & parameters,
3709 const std::string & object_name,
3710 const std::string & var_param_name)
3711{
3712 const auto nl_sys_num =
3713 parameters.isParamValid(var_param_name) &&
3714 determineNonlinearSystem(parameters.varName(var_param_name, object_name)).first
3715 ? determineNonlinearSystem(parameters.varName(var_param_name, object_name)).second
3716 : (unsigned int)0;
3717
3718 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") &&
3719 parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3720 {
3721 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
3722 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->nlSys(nl_sys_num);
3723 }
3724 else
3725 {
3726 // The object requested use_displaced_mesh, but it was overridden
3727 // due to there being no displacements variables in the [Mesh] block.
3728 // If that happened, update the value of use_displaced_mesh appropriately.
3729 if (!_displaced_problem && parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") &&
3730 parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3731 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
3732
3733 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
3734 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _nl[nl_sys_num].get();
3735 }
3736}
3737

3739FEProblemBase::addPostprocessor(const std::string & pp_name,
3740 const std::string & name,
3741 InputParameters & parameters)
3742{
3743 // Check for name collision
3744 if (hasUserObject(name))
3745 mooseError("A UserObject with the name \"",
3746 name,
3747 "\" already exists. You may not add a Postprocessor by the same name.");
3748
3749 addUserObject(pp_name, name, parameters);
3750}

3759 mooseError("A UserObject with the name \"",

3767FEProblemBase::addReporter(const std::string & type,
3768 const std::string & name,

3778
3779void
3780FEProblemBase::addUserObject(const std::string & user_object_name,
3781 const std::string & name,
3782 InputParameters & parameters)
3783{
3784 parallel_object_only();
3785
3786 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<UserObject>> uos;
3787
3788 // Add the _subproblem and _sys parameters depending on use_displaced_mesh
3789 addObjectParamsHelper(parameters, name);
3790
3791 for (const auto tid : make_range(libMesh::n_threads()))
3792 {
3793 // Create the UserObject
3794 std::shared_ptr<UserObject> user_object =
3795 _factory.create<UserObject>(user_object_name, name, parameters, tid);
3796 logAdd("UserObject", name, user_object_name);
3797 uos.push_back(user_object);
3798
3799 if (tid != 0)
3800 user_object->setPrimaryThreadCopy(uos[0].get());
3801
3802 // TODO: delete this line after apps have been updated to not call getUserObjects
3803 _all_user_objects.addObject(user_object, tid);
3804
3805 theWarehouse().add(user_object);
3806
3807 // Attempt to create all the possible UserObject types
3808 auto euo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<ElementUserObject>(user_object);
3809 auto suo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<SideUserObject>(user_object);
3810 auto isuo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<InternalSideUserObject>(user_object);
3811 auto iuob = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<InterfaceUserObjectBase>(user_object);
3812 auto nuo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<NodalUserObject>(user_object);
3813 auto duo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<DomainUserObject>(user_object);
3814 auto guo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<GeneralUserObject>(user_object);
3815 auto tguo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<ThreadedGeneralUserObject>(user_object);
3816 auto muo = std::dynamic_pointer_cast<MortarUserObject>(user_object);
3817
3818 // Account for displaced mesh use
3819 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
3820 {
3821 if (euo || nuo || duo)
3822 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
3823 else if (suo)
3824 // shouldn't we add isuo
3825 _reinit_displaced_face = true;
3826 else if (iuob)
3827 _reinit_displaced_neighbor = true;
3828 }
3829
3830 // These objects only require one thread
3831 if ((guo && !tguo) || muo)
3832 break;
3833 }
3834
3835 // Add as a Functor if it is one
3836 // At the timing of adding this, this is only Postprocessors... but technically it
3837 // should enable any UO that is a Real Functor to be used as one
3838 // The ternary operator used in getting the functor is there because some UOs
3839 // are threaded and some are not. When a UO is not threaded, we need to add
3840 // the functor from thread 0 as the registered functor for all threads
3841 for (const auto tid : make_range(libMesh::n_threads()))
3842 if (const auto functor =
3843 dynamic_cast<Moose::FunctorBase<Real> *>(uos[uos.size() == 1 ? 0 : tid].get()))
3844 {
3845 this->addFunctor(name, *functor, tid);
3846 if (_displaced_problem)
3847 _displaced_problem->addFunctor(name, *functor, tid);
3848 }
3849}
3850
3851const UserObject &
3852FEProblemBase::getUserObjectBase(const std::string & name, const THREAD_ID tid /* = 0 */) const
3853{
3854 std::vector<UserObject *> objs;
3855 theWarehouse()
3856 .query()
3857 .condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject")
3858 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
3859 .condition<AttribName>(name)
3860 .queryInto(objs);
3861 if (objs.empty())
3862 mooseError("Unable to find user object with name '" + name + "'");
3863 mooseAssert(objs.size() == 1, "Should only find one UO");
3864 return *(objs[0]);
3865}
3866
3867const Positions &
3868FEProblemBase::getPositionsObject(const std::string & name) const
3869{
3870 std::vector<Positions *> objs;
3871 theWarehouse()
3872 .query()
3873 .condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject")
3874 .condition<AttribName>(name)
3875 .queryInto(objs);
3876 if (objs.empty())
3877 mooseError("Unable to find Positions object with name '" + name + "'");
3878 mooseAssert(objs.size() == 1, "Should only find one Positions");
3879 return *(objs[0]);
3880}

3882bool
3883FEProblemBase::hasUserObject(const std::string & name) const
3884{
3885 std::vector<UserObject *> objs;
3886 theWarehouse()
3887 .query()
3888 .condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject")
3889 .condition<AttribThread>(0)
3890 .condition<AttribName>(name)
3891 .queryInto(objs);
3892 return !objs.empty();
3893}

3964FEProblemBase::computeIndicatorsAndMarkers()
3965{

3967 computeMarkers();
3968}
3969
3970void
3971FEProblemBase::computeIndicators()
3972{
3973 // Initialize indicator aux variable fields
3974 if (_indicators.hasActiveObjects() || _internal_side_indicators.hasActiveObjects())
3975 {
3976 TIME_SECTION("computeIndicators", 1, "Computing Indicators");
3977
3978 // Internal side indicators may lead to creating a much larger sparsity pattern than dictated by
3979 // the actual finite element scheme (e.g. CFEM)
3980 const auto old_do_derivatives = ADReal::do_derivatives;
3981 ADReal::do_derivatives = false;
3982
3983 std::vector<std::string> fields;
3984
3985 // Indicator Fields
3986 const auto & indicators = _indicators.getActiveObjects();
3987 for (const auto & indicator : indicators)
3988 fields.push_back(indicator->name());
3989
3990 // InternalSideIndicator Fields
3991 const auto & internal_indicators = _internal_side_indicators.getActiveObjects();
3992 for (const auto & internal_indicator : internal_indicators)
3993 fields.push_back(internal_indicator->name());
3994
3995 _aux->zeroVariables(fields);
3996
3997 // compute Indicators
3998 ComputeIndicatorThread cit(*this);
3999 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), cit);
4000 _aux->solution().close();
4001 _aux->update();
4002
4003 ComputeIndicatorThread finalize_cit(*this, true);
4004 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), finalize_cit);
4005 _aux->solution().close();
4006 _aux->update();
4007
4008 ADReal::do_derivatives = old_do_derivatives;
4009 }
4010}
4011
4012void
4013FEProblemBase::computeMarkers()
4014{
4015 if (_markers.hasActiveObjects())
4016 {
4017 TIME_SECTION("computeMarkers", 1, "Computing Markers");
4018
4019 std::vector<std::string> fields;
4020
4021 // Marker Fields
4022 const auto & markers = _markers.getActiveObjects();
4023 for (const auto & marker : markers)
4024 fields.push_back(marker->name());
4025
4026 _aux->zeroVariables(fields);
4027
4028 _adaptivity.updateErrorVectors();
4029
4030 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
4031 {
4032 const auto & markers = _markers.getActiveObjects(tid);
4033 for (const auto & marker : markers)
4034 marker->markerSetup();
4035 }
4036
4037 ComputeMarkerThread cmt(*this);
4038 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), cmt);
4039
4040 _aux->solution().close();
4041 _aux->update();
4042 }
4043}

4061
4062void
4063FEProblemBase::customSetup(const ExecFlagType & exec_type)
4064{
4065 SubProblem::customSetup(exec_type);
4066
4067 if (_line_search)
4068 _line_search->customSetup(exec_type);
4069
4070 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
4071 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
4072 {
4073 _all_materials.customSetup(exec_type, tid);
4074 _functions.customSetup(exec_type, tid);
4075 }
4076
4077 _aux->customSetup(exec_type);
4078 for (auto & nl : _nl)
4079 nl->customSetup(exec_type);
4080
4081 if (_displaced_problem)
4082 _displaced_problem->customSetup(exec_type);
4083
4084 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
4085 {
4086 _internal_side_indicators.customSetup(exec_type, tid);
4087 _indicators.customSetup(exec_type, tid);
4088 _markers.customSetup(exec_type, tid);
4089 }
4090
4091 std::vector<UserObject *> userobjs;
4092 theWarehouse().query().condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject").queryIntoUnsorted(userobjs);
4093 for (auto obj : userobjs)
4094 obj->customSetup(exec_type);
4095
4096 _app.getOutputWarehouse().customSetup(exec_type);
4097}
4098
4099void
4100FEProblemBase::execute(const ExecFlagType & exec_type)
4101{
4102 // Set the current flag
4103 setCurrentExecuteOnFlag(exec_type);
4104
4105 if (exec_type != EXEC_INITIAL)
4106 executeControls(exec_type);
4107
4108 // intentially call this after executing controls because the setups may rely on the controls
4109 // FIXME: we skip the following flags because they have dedicated setup functions in
4110 // SetupInterface and it may not be appropriate to call them here.
4111 if (!(exec_type == EXEC_INITIAL || exec_type == EXEC_TIMESTEP_BEGIN ||
4112 exec_type == EXEC_SUBDOMAIN || exec_type == EXEC_NONLINEAR || exec_type == EXEC_LINEAR))
4113 customSetup(exec_type);
4114
4115 // Samplers; EXEC_INITIAL is not called because the Sampler::init() method that is called after
4116 // construction makes the first Sampler::execute() call. This ensures that the random number
4117 // generator object is the correct state prior to any other object (e.g., Transfers) attempts to
4118 // extract data from the Sampler. That is, if the Sampler::execute() call is delayed to here
4119 // then it is not in the correct state for other objects.
4120 if (exec_type != EXEC_INITIAL)
4121 executeSamplers(exec_type);
4122
4123 // Pre-aux UserObjects
4124 computeUserObjects(exec_type, Moose::PRE_AUX);
4125
4126 // AuxKernels
4127 computeAuxiliaryKernels(exec_type);
4128
4129 // Post-aux UserObjects
4130 computeUserObjects(exec_type, Moose::POST_AUX);
4131
4132 // Return the current flag to None
4133 setCurrentExecuteOnFlag(EXEC_NONE);
4134
4135 if (_uo_aux_state_check && !_checking_uo_aux_state)
4136 {
4137 // we will only check aux variables and postprocessors
4138 // checking more reporter data can be added in the future if needed
4139 std::unique_ptr<NumericVector<Number>> x = _aux->currentSolution()->clone();
4140 DenseVector<Real> pp_values = getReporterData().getAllRealReporterValues();
4141
4142 // call THIS execute one more time for checking the possible states
4143 _checking_uo_aux_state = true;
4144 FEProblemBase::execute(exec_type);
4145 _checking_uo_aux_state = false;
4146
4147 const Real check_tol = 1e-8;
4148
4149 const Real xnorm = x->l2_norm();
4150 *x -= *_aux->currentSolution();
4151 if (x->l2_norm() > check_tol * xnorm)
4152 {
4153 const auto & sys = _aux->system();
4154 const unsigned int n_vars = sys.n_vars();
4155 std::multimap<Real, std::string, std::greater<Real>> ordered_map;
4156 for (const auto i : make_range(n_vars))
4157 {
4158 const Real vnorm = sys.calculate_norm(*x, i, DISCRETE_L2);
4159 ordered_map.emplace(vnorm, sys.variable_name(i));
4160 }
4161
4162 std::ostringstream oss;
4163 for (const auto & [error_norm, var_name] : ordered_map)
4164 oss << " {" << var_name << ", " << error_norm << "},\n";
4165
4166 mooseError("Aux kernels, user objects appear to have states for aux variables on ",
4167 exec_type,
4168 ".\nVariable error norms in descending order:\n",
4169 oss.str());
4170 }
4171
4172 const DenseVector<Real> new_pp_values = getReporterData().getAllRealReporterValues();
4173 if (pp_values.size() != new_pp_values.size())
4174 mooseError("Second execution for uo/aux state check should not change the number of "
4175 "real reporter values");
4176
4177 const Real ppnorm = pp_values.l2_norm();
4178 pp_values -= new_pp_values;
4179 if (pp_values.l2_norm() > check_tol * ppnorm)
4180 {
4181 const auto pp_names = getReporterData().getAllRealReporterFullNames();
4182 std::multimap<Real, std::string, std::greater<Real>> ordered_map;
4183 for (const auto i : index_range(pp_names))
4184 ordered_map.emplace(std::abs(pp_values(i)), pp_names[i]);
4185
4186 std::ostringstream oss;
4187 for (const auto & [error_norm, pp_name] : ordered_map)
4188 oss << " {" << pp_name << ", " << error_norm << "},\n";
4189
4190 mooseError("Aux kernels, user objects appear to have states for real reporter values on ",
4191 exec_type,
4192 ".\nErrors of real reporter values in descending order:\n",
4193 oss.str());
4194 }
4195 }
4196}
4197
4198void
4199FEProblemBase::computeAuxiliaryKernels(const ExecFlagType & type)
4200{
4201 _aux->compute(type);
4202}
4203
4204// Finalize, threadJoin, and update PP values of Elemental/Nodal/Side/InternalSideUserObjects
4205void
4206FEProblemBase::joinAndFinalize(TheWarehouse::Query query, bool isgen)
4207{
4208 std::vector<UserObject *> objs;
4209 query.queryInto(objs);
4210 if (!isgen)
4211 {
4212 // join all threaded user objects (i.e. not regular general user objects) to the primary
4213 // thread
4214 for (auto obj : objs)
4215 if (obj->primaryThreadCopy())
4216 obj->primaryThreadCopy()->threadJoin(*obj);
4217 }
4218
4219 query.condition<AttribThread>(0).queryInto(objs);
4220
4221 // finalize objects and retrieve/store any postprocessor values
4222 for (auto obj : objs)
4223 {
4224 if (isgen && dynamic_cast<ThreadedGeneralUserObject *>(obj))
4225 continue;
4226 if (isgen)
4227 {
4228 // general user objects are not run in their own threaded loop object - so run them here
4229 if (shouldPrintExecution(0))
4230 _console << "[DBG] Initializing, executing & finalizing general UO '" << obj->name()
4231 << "' on " << _current_execute_on_flag.name() << std::endl;
4232 obj->initialize();
4233 obj->execute();
4234 }
4235
4236 obj->finalize();
4237
4238 // These have to be stored piecemeal (with every call to this function) because general
4239 // postprocessors (which run last after other userobjects have been completed) might depend on
4240 // them being stored. This wouldn't be a problem if all userobjects satisfied the dependency
4241 // resolver interface and could be sorted appropriately with the general userobjects, but they
4242 // don't.
4243 auto pp = dynamic_cast<const Postprocessor *>(obj);
4244 if (pp)
4245 {
4246 _reporter_data.finalize(obj->name());
4247 setPostprocessorValueByName(obj->name(), pp->getValue());
4248 }
4249
4250 auto vpp = dynamic_cast<VectorPostprocessor *>(obj);
4251 if (vpp)
4252 _reporter_data.finalize(obj->name());
4253
4254 // Update Reporter data
4255 auto reporter = dynamic_cast<Reporter *>(obj);
4256 if (reporter)
4257 _reporter_data.finalize(obj->name());
4258 }
4259}
4260
4261void
4262FEProblemBase::computeUserObjectByName(const ExecFlagType & type,
4263 const Moose::AuxGroup & group,
4264 const std::string & name)
4265{
4266 const auto old_exec_flag = _current_execute_on_flag;
4267 _current_execute_on_flag = type;
4268 TheWarehouse::Query query = theWarehouse()
4269 .query()
4270 .condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject")
4271 .condition<AttribExecOns>(type)
4272 .condition<AttribName>(name);
4273 computeUserObjectsInternal(type, group, query);
4274 _current_execute_on_flag = old_exec_flag;
4275}
4276
4277void
4278FEProblemBase::computeUserObjects(const ExecFlagType & type, const Moose::AuxGroup & group)
4279{
4280 TheWarehouse::Query query =
4281 theWarehouse().query().condition<AttribSystem>("UserObject").condition<AttribExecOns>(type);
4282 computeUserObjectsInternal(type, group, query);
4283}
4284
4285void
4286FEProblemBase::computeUserObjectsInternal(const ExecFlagType & type,
4287 const Moose::AuxGroup & group,
4288 TheWarehouse::Query & primary_query)
4289{
4290 TIME_SECTION("computeUserObjects", 1, "Computing User Objects");
4291
4292 // Add group to query
4293 if (group == Moose::PRE_IC)
4294 primary_query.condition<AttribPreIC>(true);
4295 else if (group == Moose::PRE_AUX)
4296 primary_query.condition<AttribPreAux>(type);
4297 else if (group == Moose::POST_AUX)
4298 primary_query.condition<AttribPostAux>(type);
4299
4300 // query everything first to obtain a list of execution groups
4301 std::vector<UserObject *> uos;
4302 primary_query.clone().queryIntoUnsorted(uos);
4303 std::set<int> execution_groups;
4304 for (const auto & uo : uos)
4305 execution_groups.insert(uo->getParam<int>("execution_order_group"));
4306
4307 // iterate over execution order groups
4308 for (const auto execution_group : execution_groups)
4309 {
4310 auto query = primary_query.clone().condition<AttribExecutionOrderGroup>(execution_group);
4311
4312 std::vector<GeneralUserObject *> genobjs;
4313 query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::GeneralUserObject).queryInto(genobjs);
4314
4315 std::vector<UserObject *> userobjs;
4316 query.clone()
4317 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ElementUserObject | Interfaces::SideUserObject |
4318 Interfaces::InternalSideUserObject |
4319 Interfaces::InterfaceUserObject | Interfaces::DomainUserObject)
4320 .queryInto(userobjs);
4321
4322 std::vector<UserObject *> tgobjs;
4323 query.clone()
4324 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ThreadedGeneralUserObject)
4325 .queryInto(tgobjs);
4326
4327 std::vector<UserObject *> nodal;
4328 query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::NodalUserObject).queryInto(nodal);
4329
4330 std::vector<MortarUserObject *> mortar;
4331 query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::MortarUserObject).queryInto(mortar);
4332
4333 if (userobjs.empty() && genobjs.empty() && tgobjs.empty() && nodal.empty() && mortar.empty())
4334 continue;
4335
4336 // Start the timer here since we have at least one active user object
4337 std::string compute_uo_tag = "computeUserObjects(" + Moose::stringify(type) + ")";
4338
4339 // Perform Residual/Jacobian setups
4340 if (type == EXEC_LINEAR)
4341 {
4342 for (auto obj : userobjs)
4343 obj->residualSetup();
4344 for (auto obj : nodal)
4345 obj->residualSetup();
4346 for (auto obj : mortar)
4347 obj->residualSetup();
4348 for (auto obj : tgobjs)
4349 obj->residualSetup();
4350 for (auto obj : genobjs)
4351 obj->residualSetup();
4352 }
4353 else if (type == EXEC_NONLINEAR)
4354 {
4355 for (auto obj : userobjs)
4356 obj->jacobianSetup();
4357 for (auto obj : nodal)
4358 obj->jacobianSetup();
4359 for (auto obj : mortar)
4360 obj->jacobianSetup();
4361 for (auto obj : tgobjs)
4362 obj->jacobianSetup();
4363 for (auto obj : genobjs)
4364 obj->jacobianSetup();
4365 }
4366
4367 for (auto obj : userobjs)
4368 obj->initialize();
4369
4370 // Execute Side/InternalSide/Interface/Elemental/DomainUserObjects
4371 if (!userobjs.empty())
4372 {
4373 // non-nodal user objects have to be run separately before the nodal user objects run
4374 // because some nodal user objects (NodalNormal related) depend on elemental user objects
4375 // :-(
4376 ComputeUserObjectsThread cppt(*this, query);
4377 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), cppt);
4378
4379 // There is one instance in rattlesnake where an elemental user object's finalize depends
4380 // on a side user object having been finalized first :-(
4381 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::SideUserObject));
4382 joinAndFinalize(
4383 query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::InternalSideUserObject));
4384 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::InterfaceUserObject));
4385 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ElementUserObject));
4386 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::DomainUserObject));
4387 }
4388
4389 // if any userobject may have written to variables we need to close the aux solution
4390 for (const auto & uo : userobjs)
4391 if (auto euo = dynamic_cast<const ElementUserObject *>(uo);
4392 euo && euo->hasWritableCoupledVariables())
4393 {
4394 _aux->solution().close();
4395 _aux->system().update();
4396 break;
4397 }
4398
4399 // Execute NodalUserObjects
4400 // BISON has an axial reloc elemental user object that has a finalize func that depends on a
4401 // nodal user object's prev value. So we can't initialize this until after elemental objects
4402 // have been finalized :-(
4403 for (auto obj : nodal)
4404 obj->initialize();
4405 if (query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::NodalUserObject).count() > 0)
4406 {
4407 ComputeNodalUserObjectsThread cnppt(*this, query);
4408 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getLocalNodeRange(), cnppt);
4409 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::NodalUserObject));
4410 }
4411
4412 // if any userobject may have written to variables we need to close the aux solution
4413 for (const auto & uo : nodal)
4414 if (auto nuo = dynamic_cast<const NodalUserObject *>(uo);
4415 nuo && nuo->hasWritableCoupledVariables())
4416 {
4417 _aux->solution().close();
4418 _aux->system().update();
4419 break;
4420 }
4421
4422 // Execute MortarUserObjects
4423 {
4424 for (auto obj : mortar)
4425 obj->initialize();
4426 if (!mortar.empty())
4427 {
4428 auto create_and_run_mortar_functors = [this, type, &mortar](const bool displaced)
4429 {
4430 // go over mortar interfaces and construct functors
4431 const auto & mortar_interfaces = getMortarInterfaces(displaced);
4432 for (const auto & mortar_interface : mortar_interfaces)
4433 {
4434 const auto primary_secondary_boundary_pair = mortar_interface.first;
4435 auto mortar_uos_to_execute =
4436 getMortarUserObjects(primary_secondary_boundary_pair.first,
4437 primary_secondary_boundary_pair.second,
4438 displaced,
4439 mortar);
4440 const auto & mortar_generation_object = mortar_interface.second;
4441
4442 auto * const subproblem = displaced
4443 ? static_cast<SubProblem *>(_displaced_problem.get())
4444 : static_cast<SubProblem *>(this);
4445 MortarUserObjectThread muot(mortar_uos_to_execute,
4446 mortar_generation_object,
4447 *subproblem,
4448 *this,
4449 displaced,
4450 subproblem->assembly(0, 0));
4451
4452 auto process_possibly_handleable_exception = [this, type](auto & exception)
4453 {
4454 // When executing on linear we can turn exceptions into residual domain errors, stop
4455 // the solve, and cut the timestep
4456 if (type == EXEC_LINEAR)
4457 setException(exception.what());
4458 else
4459 // Otherwise we don't know what to do
4460 mooseError(
4461 "We caught an exception during computation of mortar user objects outside of "
4462 "residual evaluation. Unfortunately we don't know how to handle this case, "
4463 "so "
4464 "we will abort.");
4465 };
4466 try
4467 {
4468 muot();
4469 }
4470 catch (MooseException & e)
4471 {
4472 process_possibly_handleable_exception(e);
4473 }
4474 catch (libMesh::LogicError & e)
4475 {
4476 process_possibly_handleable_exception(e);
4477 }
4478 catch (MetaPhysicL::LogicError & e)
4479 {
4480 moose::translateMetaPhysicLError(e);
4481 }
4482 checkExceptionAndStopSolve();
4483 }
4484 };
4485
4486 create_and_run_mortar_functors(false);
4487 if (_displaced_problem)
4488 create_and_run_mortar_functors(true);
4489 }
4490 for (auto obj : mortar)
4491 obj->finalize();
4492 }
4493
4494 // Execute threaded general user objects
4495 for (auto obj : tgobjs)
4496 obj->initialize();
4497 std::vector<GeneralUserObject *> tguos_zero;
4498 query.clone()
4499 .condition<AttribThread>(0)
4500 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ThreadedGeneralUserObject)
4501 .queryInto(tguos_zero);
4502 for (auto obj : tguos_zero)
4503 {
4504 std::vector<GeneralUserObject *> tguos;
4505 auto q = query.clone()
4506 .condition<AttribName>(obj->name())
4507 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::ThreadedGeneralUserObject);
4508 q.queryInto(tguos);
4509
4510 ComputeThreadedGeneralUserObjectsThread ctguot(*this);
4511 Threads::parallel_reduce(GeneralUserObjectRange(tguos.begin(), tguos.end()), ctguot);
4512 joinAndFinalize(q);
4513 }
4514
4515 // Execute general user objects
4516 joinAndFinalize(query.clone().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::GeneralUserObject), true);
4517 }
4518}
4519
4520void
4521FEProblemBase::executeControls(const ExecFlagType & exec_type)
4522{
4523 if (_control_warehouse[exec_type].hasActiveObjects())
4524 {
4525 TIME_SECTION("executeControls", 1, "Executing Controls");
4526
4527 DependencyResolver<std::shared_ptr<Control>> resolver;
4528
4529 auto controls_wh = _control_warehouse[exec_type];
4530 // Add all of the dependencies into the resolver and sort them
4531 for (const auto & it : controls_wh.getActiveObjects())
4532 {
4533 // Make sure an item with no dependencies comes out too!
4534 resolver.addItem(it);
4535
4536 std::vector<std::string> & dependent_controls = it->getDependencies();
4537 for (const auto & depend_name : dependent_controls)
4538 {
4539 if (controls_wh.hasActiveObject(depend_name))
4540 {
4541 auto dep_control = controls_wh.getActiveObject(depend_name);
4542 resolver.addEdge(dep_control, it);
4543 }
4544 else
4545 mooseError("The Control \"",
4546 depend_name,
4547 "\" was not created, did you make a "
4548 "spelling mistake or forget to include it "
4549 "in your input file?");
4550 }
4551 }
4552
4553 const auto & ordered_controls = resolver.getSortedValues();
4554
4555 if (!ordered_controls.empty())
4556 {
4557 _control_warehouse.setup(exec_type);
4558 // Run the controls in the proper order
4559 for (const auto & control : ordered_controls)
4560 control->execute();
4561 }
4562 }
4563}
4564
4565void
4566FEProblemBase::executeSamplers(const ExecFlagType & exec_type)
4567{
4568 // TODO: This should be done in a threaded loop, but this should be super quick so for now
4569 // do a serial loop.
4570 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
4571 {
4572 std::vector<Sampler *> objects;
4573 theWarehouse()
4574 .query()
4575 .condition<AttribSystem>("Sampler")
4576 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
4577 .condition<AttribExecOns>(exec_type)
4578 .queryInto(objects);
4579
4580 if (!objects.empty())
4581 {
4582 TIME_SECTION("executeSamplers", 1, "Executing Samplers");
4583 FEProblemBase::objectSetupHelper<Sampler>(objects, exec_type);
4584 FEProblemBase::objectExecuteHelper<Sampler>(objects);
4585 }
4586 }
4587}

4621
4622void
4623FEProblemBase::reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects(const bool mortar_changed)
4624{
4625 TIME_SECTION("reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects",
4626 3,
4627 "Reinitializing Because of Geometric Search Objects");
4628
4629 // Need to see if _any_ processor has ghosted elems or geometry objects.
4630 bool needs_reinit = !_ghosted_elems.empty();
4631 needs_reinit = needs_reinit || !_geometric_search_data._nearest_node_locators.empty() ||
4632 (_mortar_data.hasObjects() && mortar_changed);
4633 needs_reinit =
4634 needs_reinit || (_displaced_problem &&
4635 (!_displaced_problem->geomSearchData()._nearest_node_locators.empty() ||
4636 (_mortar_data.hasDisplacedObjects() && mortar_changed)));
4637 _communicator.max(needs_reinit);
4638
4639 if (needs_reinit)
4640 {
4641 // Call reinit to get the ghosted vectors correct now that some geometric search has been done
4642 es().reinit();
4643
4644 if (_displaced_mesh)
4645 _displaced_problem->es().reinit();
4646 }
4647}

4649void
4650FEProblemBase::addDamper(const std::string & damper_name,
4651 const std::string & name,
4652 InputParameters & parameters)
4653{
4654 parallel_object_only();
4655
4656 const auto nl_sys_num =
4657 parameters.isParamValid("variable")
4658 ? determineNonlinearSystem(parameters.varName("variable", name), true).second
4659 : (unsigned int)0;
4660
4661 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
4662 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _nl[nl_sys_num].get();
4663
4664 _has_dampers = true;
4665 logAdd("Damper", name, damper_name);
4666 _nl[nl_sys_num]->addDamper(damper_name, name, parameters);
4667}

4675
4676void
4677FEProblemBase::addIndicator(const std::string & indicator_name,
4678 const std::string & name,
4679 InputParameters & parameters)
4680{
4681 parallel_object_only();
4682
4683 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4684 {
4685 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
4686 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->auxSys();
4687 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
4688 }
4689 else
4690 {
4691 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4692 {
4693 // We allow Indicators to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
4694 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
4695 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
4696 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this Indicator.
4697 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4698 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
4699 }
4700
4701 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
4702 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _aux.get();
4703 }
4704
4705 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
4706 {
4707 std::shared_ptr<Indicator> indicator =
4708 _factory.create<Indicator>(indicator_name, name, parameters, tid);
4709 logAdd("Indicator", name, indicator_name);
4710 std::shared_ptr<InternalSideIndicator> isi =
4711 std::dynamic_pointer_cast<InternalSideIndicator>(indicator);
4712 if (isi)
4713 _internal_side_indicators.addObject(isi, tid);
4714 else
4715 _indicators.addObject(indicator, tid);
4716 }
4717}

4760{
4761 parallel_object_only();
4762

4765
4766 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4767 {

4770 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
4771 }
4772 else
4773 {
4774 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4775 {
4776 // We allow MultiApps to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
4777 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
4778 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
4779 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this MultiApp.
4780 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
4781 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
4782 }
4783
4784 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
4785 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _aux.get();
4786 }
4787
4788 std::shared_ptr<MultiApp> multi_app = _factory.create<MultiApp>(multi_app_name, name, parameters);
4789 logAdd("MultiApp", name, multi_app_name);
4790 multi_app->setupPositions();
4791
4792 _multi_apps.addObject(multi_app);
4793
4794 // Store TransientMultiApp objects in another container, this is needed for calling computeDT
4795 std::shared_ptr<TransientMultiApp> trans_multi_app =
4796 std::dynamic_pointer_cast<TransientMultiApp>(multi_app);
4797 if (trans_multi_app)
4798 _transient_multi_apps.addObject(trans_multi_app);
4799}

4818
4819void
4820FEProblemBase::execMultiAppTransfers(ExecFlagType type, Transfer::DIRECTION direction)
4821{
4822 bool to_multiapp = direction == MultiAppTransfer::TO_MULTIAPP;
4823 bool from_multiapp = direction == MultiAppTransfer::FROM_MULTIAPP;
4824 std::string string_direction;
4825 if (to_multiapp)
4826 string_direction = " To ";
4827 else if (from_multiapp)
4828 string_direction = " From ";
4829 else
4830 string_direction = " Between ";
4831
4832 const MooseObjectWarehouse<Transfer> & wh = to_multiapp ? _to_multi_app_transfers[type]
4833 : from_multiapp ? _from_multi_app_transfers[type]
4834 : _between_multi_app_transfers;
4835
4836 if (wh.hasActiveObjects())
4837 {
4838 TIME_SECTION("execMultiAppTransfers", 1, "Executing Transfers");
4839
4840 const auto & transfers = wh.getActiveObjects();
4841
4842 if (_verbose_multiapps)
4843 {
4844 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nTransfers on " << Moose::stringify(type) << string_direction
4845 << "MultiApps" << COLOR_DEFAULT << ":" << std::endl;
4846
4847 VariadicTable<std::string, std::string, std::string, std::string> table(
4848 {"Name", "Type", "From", "To"});
4849
4850 // Build Table of Transfer Info
4851 for (const auto & transfer : transfers)
4852 {
4853 auto multiapp_transfer = dynamic_cast<MultiAppTransfer *>(transfer.get());
4854
4855 table.addRow(multiapp_transfer->name(),
4856 multiapp_transfer->type(),
4857 multiapp_transfer->getFromName(),
4858 multiapp_transfer->getToName());
4859 }
4860
4861 // Print it
4862 table.print(_console);
4863 }
4864
4865 for (const auto & transfer : transfers)
4866 {
4867 transfer->setCurrentDirection(direction);
4868 transfer->execute();
4869 }
4870
4871 MooseUtils::parallelBarrierNotify(_communicator, _parallel_barrier_messaging);
4872
4873 if (_verbose_multiapps)
4874 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "Transfers on " << Moose::stringify(type) << " Are Finished\n"
4875 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
4876 }
4877 else if (_multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects().size())
4878 {
4879 if (_verbose_multiapps)
4880 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nNo Transfers on " << Moose::stringify(type) << string_direction
4881 << "MultiApps\n"
4882 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
4883 }
4884}
4885

4888{

4890 return _to_multi_app_transfers[type].getActiveObjects();
4891 else if (direction == MultiAppTransfer::FROM_MULTIAPP)

4895}

4902 else if (direction == MultiAppTransfer::FROM_MULTIAPP)

4918
4919bool
4920FEProblemBase::execMultiApps(ExecFlagType type, bool auto_advance)
4921{
4922 // Active MultiApps
4923 const std::vector<MooseSharedPointer<MultiApp>> & multi_apps =
4924 _multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects();
4925
4926 // Do anything that needs to be done to Apps before transfers
4927 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
4928 multi_app->preTransfer(_dt, _time);
4929
4930 // Execute Transfers _to_ MultiApps
4931 execMultiAppTransfers(type, MultiAppTransfer::TO_MULTIAPP);
4932
4933 // Execute Transfers _between_ Multiapps
4934 execMultiAppTransfers(type, MultiAppTransfer::BETWEEN_MULTIAPP);
4935
4936 // Execute MultiApps
4937 if (multi_apps.size())
4938 {
4939 TIME_SECTION("execMultiApps", 1, "Executing MultiApps", false);
4940
4941 if (_verbose_multiapps)
4942 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nExecuting MultiApps on " << Moose::stringify(type)
4943 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
4944
4945 bool success = true;
4946
4947 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
4948 {
4949 success = multi_app->solveStep(_dt, _time, auto_advance);
4950 // no need to finish executing the subapps if one fails
4951 if (!success)
4952 break;
4953 }
4954
4955 MooseUtils::parallelBarrierNotify(_communicator, _parallel_barrier_messaging);
4956
4957 _communicator.min(success);
4958
4959 if (!success)
4960 return false;
4961
4962 if (_verbose_multiapps)
4963 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "Finished Executing MultiApps on " << Moose::stringify(type) << "\n"
4964 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
4965 }
4966
4967 // Execute Transfers _from_ MultiApps
4968 execMultiAppTransfers(type, MultiAppTransfer::FROM_MULTIAPP);
4969
4970 // If we made it here then everything passed
4971 return true;
4972}

4990}

5002void
5003FEProblemBase::finishMultiAppStep(ExecFlagType type, bool recurse_through_multiapp_levels)
5004{
5005 const auto & multi_apps = _multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects();
5006

5008 {

5011 << std::endl;
5012
5013 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
5014 multi_app->finishStep(recurse_through_multiapp_levels);
5015

5017
5018 if (_verbose_multiapps)

5020 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;

5023
5024void
5025FEProblemBase::backupMultiApps(ExecFlagType type)
5026{
5027 const auto & multi_apps = _multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects();
5028
5029 if (multi_apps.size())
5030 {
5031 TIME_SECTION("backupMultiApps", 5, "Backing Up MultiApp");
5032
5033 if (_verbose_multiapps)
5034 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nBacking Up MultiApps on " << type.name() << COLOR_DEFAULT
5035 << std::endl;
5036
5037 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
5038 multi_app->backup();
5039
5040 MooseUtils::parallelBarrierNotify(_communicator, _parallel_barrier_messaging);
5041
5042 if (_verbose_multiapps)
5043 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "Finished Backing Up MultiApps on " << type.name() << "\n"
5044 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
5045 }
5046}
5047
5048void
5049FEProblemBase::restoreMultiApps(ExecFlagType type, bool force)
5050{
5051 const auto & multi_apps = _multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects();
5052
5053 if (multi_apps.size())
5054 {
5055 if (_verbose_multiapps)
5056 {
5057 if (force)
5058 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nRestoring Multiapps on " << type.name()
5059 << " because of solve failure!" << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
5060 else
5061 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "\nRestoring MultiApps on " << type.name() << COLOR_DEFAULT
5062 << std::endl;
5063 }
5064
5065 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
5066 multi_app->restore(force);
5067
5068 MooseUtils::parallelBarrierNotify(_communicator, _parallel_barrier_messaging);
5069
5070 if (_verbose_multiapps)
5071 _console << COLOR_CYAN << "Finished Restoring MultiApps on " << type.name() << "\n"
5072 << COLOR_DEFAULT << std::endl;
5073 }
5074}
5075
5076Real
5077FEProblemBase::computeMultiAppsDT(ExecFlagType type)
5078{
5079 const auto & multi_apps = _transient_multi_apps[type].getActiveObjects();
5080
5081 Real smallest_dt = std::numeric_limits<Real>::max();
5082
5083 for (const auto & multi_app : multi_apps)
5084 smallest_dt = std::min(smallest_dt, multi_app->computeDT());
5085
5086 return smallest_dt;
5087}
5088
5089void
5090FEProblemBase::execTransfers(ExecFlagType type)
5091{
5092 if (_transfers[type].hasActiveObjects())
5093 {
5094 TIME_SECTION("execTransfers", 3, "Executing Transfers");
5095
5096 const auto & transfers = _transfers[type].getActiveObjects();
5097
5098 for (const auto & transfer : transfers)
5099 transfer->execute();
5100 }
5101}
5102
5103void
5104FEProblemBase::addTransfer(const std::string & transfer_name,
5105 const std::string & name,
5106 InputParameters & parameters)
5107{
5108 parallel_object_only();
5109
5110 if (_displaced_problem && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
5111 {
5112 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = _displaced_problem.get();
5113 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = &_displaced_problem->auxSys();
5114 _reinit_displaced_elem = true;
5115 }
5116 else
5117 {
5118 if (_displaced_problem == nullptr && parameters.get<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
5119 {
5120 // We allow Transfers to request that they use_displaced_mesh,
5121 // but then be overridden when no displacements variables are
5122 // provided in the Mesh block. If that happened, update the value
5123 // of use_displaced_mesh appropriately for this Transfer.
5124 if (parameters.have_parameter<bool>("use_displaced_mesh"))
5125 parameters.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = false;
5126 }
5127
5128 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
5129 parameters.set<SystemBase *>("_sys") = _aux.get();
5130 }
5131
5132 // Handle the "SAME_AS_MULTIAPP" execute option. The get method is used to test for the
5133 // flag so the set by user flag is not reset, calling set with the true flag causes the set
5134 // by user status to be reset, which should only be done if the EXEC_SAME_AS_MULTIAPP is
5135 // being applied to the object.
5136 if (parameters.get<ExecFlagEnum>("execute_on").contains(EXEC_SAME_AS_MULTIAPP))
5137 {
5138 ExecFlagEnum & exec_enum = parameters.set<ExecFlagEnum>("execute_on", true);
5139 std::shared_ptr<MultiApp> multiapp;
5140 if (parameters.isParamValid("multi_app"))
5141 multiapp = getMultiApp(parameters.get<MultiAppName>("multi_app"));
5142 else if (parameters.isParamValid("from_multi_app"))
5143 multiapp = getMultiApp(parameters.get<MultiAppName>("from_multi_app"));
5144 else if (parameters.isParamValid("to_multi_app"))
5145 multiapp = getMultiApp(parameters.get<MultiAppName>("to_multi_app"));
5146 // else do nothing because the user has provided invalid input. They should get a nice error
5147 // about this during transfer construction. This necessitates checking for null in this next
5148 // line, however
5149 if (multiapp)
5150 exec_enum = multiapp->getParam<ExecFlagEnum>("execute_on");
5151 }
5152
5153 // Create the Transfer objects
5154 std::shared_ptr<Transfer> transfer = _factory.create<Transfer>(transfer_name, name, parameters);
5155 logAdd("Transfer", name, transfer_name);
5156
5157 // Add MultiAppTransfer object
5158 std::shared_ptr<MultiAppTransfer> multi_app_transfer =
5159 std::dynamic_pointer_cast<MultiAppTransfer>(transfer);
5160 if (multi_app_transfer)
5161 {
5162 if (multi_app_transfer->directions().contains(MultiAppTransfer::TO_MULTIAPP))
5163 _to_multi_app_transfers.addObject(multi_app_transfer);
5164 if (multi_app_transfer->directions().contains(MultiAppTransfer::FROM_MULTIAPP))
5165 _from_multi_app_transfers.addObject(multi_app_transfer);
5166 if (multi_app_transfer->directions().contains(MultiAppTransfer::BETWEEN_MULTIAPP))
5167 _between_multi_app_transfers.addObject(multi_app_transfer);
5168 }
5169 else
5170 _transfers.addObject(transfer);
5171}

5266System &

5276}

5395
5396void
5397FEProblemBase::addAnyRedistributers()
5398{
5399#ifdef LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
5400 if ((_adaptivity.isOn() || _num_grid_steps) &&
5401 (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
5402 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties()))
5403 {
5404 // Even on a serialized Mesh, we don't keep our material
5405 // properties serialized, so we'll rely on the callback to
5406 // redistribute() to redistribute properties at the same time
5407 // libMesh is redistributing elements.
5408 auto add_redistributer = [this](MooseMesh & mesh,
5409 const std::string & redistributer_name,
5410 const bool use_displaced_mesh)
5411 {
5412 InputParameters redistribute_params = RedistributeProperties::validParams();
5413 redistribute_params.set<MooseApp *>("_moose_app") = &_app;
5414 redistribute_params.set<std::string>("for_whom") = this->name();
5415 redistribute_params.set<MooseMesh *>("mesh") = &mesh;
5416 redistribute_params.set<Moose::RelationshipManagerType>("rm_type") =
5417 Moose::RelationshipManagerType::GEOMETRIC;
5418 redistribute_params.set<bool>("use_displaced_mesh") = use_displaced_mesh;
5419
5420 std::shared_ptr<RedistributeProperties> redistributer =
5421 _factory.create<RedistributeProperties>(
5422 "RedistributeProperties", redistributer_name, redistribute_params);
5423
5424 if (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5425 redistributer->addMaterialPropertyStorage(_material_props);
5426
5427 if (_bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5428 redistributer->addMaterialPropertyStorage(_bnd_material_props);
5429
5430 if (_neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5431 redistributer->addMaterialPropertyStorage(_neighbor_material_props);
5432
5433 mesh.getMesh().add_ghosting_functor(redistributer);
5434 };
5435
5436 add_redistributer(_mesh, "mesh_property_redistributer", false);
5437 if (_displaced_problem)
5438 add_redistributer(_displaced_problem->mesh(), "displaced_mesh_property_redistributer", true);
5439 }
5440#endif // LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
5441}
5442
5443void
5444FEProblemBase::updateMaxQps()
5445{
5446 // Find the maximum number of quadrature points
5447 {
5448 MaxQpsThread mqt(*this);
5449 Threads::parallel_reduce(*_mesh.getActiveLocalElementRange(), mqt);
5450 _max_qps = mqt.max();
5451
5452 // If we have more shape functions or more quadrature points on
5453 // another processor, then we may need to handle those elements
5454 // ourselves later after repartitioning.
5455 _communicator.max(_max_qps);
5456 }
5457
5458 unsigned int max_qpts = getMaxQps();
5459 if (max_qpts > Moose::constMaxQpsPerElem)
5460 mooseError("Max quadrature points per element assumptions made in some code (e.g. Coupleable ",
5461 "and MaterialPropertyInterface classes) have been violated.\n",
5462 "Complain to Moose developers to have constMaxQpsPerElem increased from ",
5463 Moose::constMaxQpsPerElem,
5464 " to ",
5465 max_qpts);
5466 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
5467 {
5468 // the highest available order in libMesh is 43
5469 _scalar_zero[tid].resize(FORTYTHIRD, 0);
5470 _zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, 0);
5471 _ad_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, 0);
5472 _grad_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
5473 _ad_grad_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, ADRealGradient(0));
5474 _second_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealTensor(0.));
5475 _ad_second_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, ADRealTensorValue(0));
5476 _vector_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
5477 _vector_curl_zero[tid].resize(max_qpts, RealGradient(0.));
5478 }
5479}
5480
5481void
5482FEProblemBase::bumpVolumeQRuleOrder(Order order, SubdomainID block)
5483{
5484 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
5485 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5486 _assembly[tid][i]->bumpVolumeQRuleOrder(order, block);
5487
5488 if (_displaced_problem)
5489 _displaced_problem->bumpVolumeQRuleOrder(order, block);
5490
5491 updateMaxQps();
5492}
5493
5494void
5495FEProblemBase::bumpAllQRuleOrder(Order order, SubdomainID block)
5496{
5497 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
5498 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5499 _assembly[tid][i]->bumpAllQRuleOrder(order, block);
5500
5501 if (_displaced_problem)
5502 _displaced_problem->bumpAllQRuleOrder(order, block);
5503
5504 updateMaxQps();
5505}
5506
5507void
5508FEProblemBase::createQRules(QuadratureType type,
5509 Order order,
5510 Order volume_order,
5511 Order face_order,
5512 SubdomainID block,
5513 const bool allow_negative_qweights)
5514{
5515 if (order == INVALID_ORDER)
5516 {
5517 // automatically determine the integration order
5518 order = _nl[0]->getMinQuadratureOrder();
5519 for (const auto i : make_range(std::size_t(1), _nl.size()))
5520 if (order < _nl[i]->getMinQuadratureOrder())
5521 order = _nl[i]->getMinQuadratureOrder();
5522 if (order < _aux->getMinQuadratureOrder())
5523 order = _aux->getMinQuadratureOrder();
5524 }
5525
5526 if (volume_order == INVALID_ORDER)
5527 volume_order = order;
5528
5529 if (face_order == INVALID_ORDER)
5530 face_order = order;
5531
5532 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
5533 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5534 _assembly[tid][i]->createQRules(
5535 type, order, volume_order, face_order, block, allow_negative_qweights);
5536
5537 if (_displaced_problem)
5538 _displaced_problem->createQRules(
5539 type, order, volume_order, face_order, block, allow_negative_qweights);
5540
5541 updateMaxQps();
5542}
5543
5544void
5545FEProblemBase::setCoupling(Moose::CouplingType type)
5546{
5547 if (_trust_user_coupling_matrix)
5548 {
5549 if (_coupling != Moose::COUPLING_CUSTOM)
5550 mooseError("Someone told us (the FEProblemBase) to trust the user coupling matrix, but we "
5551 "haven't been provided a coupling matrix!");
5552
5553 // We've been told to trust the user coupling matrix, so we're going to leave things alone
5554 return;
5555 }
5556
5557 _coupling = type;
5558}
5559
5560void
5561FEProblemBase::setCouplingMatrix(CouplingMatrix * cm, const unsigned int i)
5562{
5563 // TODO: Deprecate method
5564 setCoupling(Moose::COUPLING_CUSTOM);
5565 _cm[i].reset(cm);
5566}
5567
5568void
5569FEProblemBase::setCouplingMatrix(std::unique_ptr<CouplingMatrix> cm, const unsigned int i)
5570{
5571 setCoupling(Moose::COUPLING_CUSTOM);
5572 _cm[i] = std::move(cm);
5573}
5574
5575void
5576FEProblemBase::trustUserCouplingMatrix()
5577{
5578 if (_coupling != Moose::COUPLING_CUSTOM)
5579 mooseError("Someone told us (the FEProblemBase) to trust the user coupling matrix, but we "
5580 "haven't been provided a coupling matrix!");
5581
5582 _trust_user_coupling_matrix = true;
5583}
5584
5585void
5586FEProblemBase::setNonlocalCouplingMatrix()
5587{
5588 TIME_SECTION("setNonlocalCouplingMatrix", 5, "Setting Nonlocal Coupling Matrix");
5589
5590 if (_nl.size() > 1)
5591 mooseError("Nonlocal kernels are weirdly stored on the FEProblem so we don't currently support "
5592 "multiple nonlinear systems with nonlocal kernels.");
5593
5594 for (const auto nl_sys_num : index_range(_nl))
5595 {
5596 auto & nl = _nl[nl_sys_num];
5597 auto & nonlocal_cm = _nonlocal_cm[nl_sys_num];
5598 unsigned int n_vars = nl->nVariables();
5599 nonlocal_cm.resize(n_vars);
5600 const auto & vars = nl->getVariables(0);
5601 const auto & nonlocal_kernel = _nonlocal_kernels.getObjects();
5602 const auto & nonlocal_integrated_bc = _nonlocal_integrated_bcs.getObjects();
5603 for (const auto & ivar : vars)
5604 {
5605 for (const auto & kernel : nonlocal_kernel)
5606 {
5607 for (unsigned int i = ivar->number(); i < ivar->number() + ivar->count(); ++i)
5608 if (i == kernel->variable().number())
5609 for (const auto & jvar : vars)
5610 {
5611 const auto it = _var_dof_map.find(jvar->name());
5612 if (it != _var_dof_map.end())
5613 {
5614 unsigned int j = jvar->number();
5615 nonlocal_cm(i, j) = 1;
5616 }
5617 }
5618 }
5619 for (const auto & integrated_bc : nonlocal_integrated_bc)
5620 {
5621 for (unsigned int i = ivar->number(); i < ivar->number() + ivar->count(); ++i)
5622 if (i == integrated_bc->variable().number())
5623 for (const auto & jvar : vars)
5624 {
5625 const auto it = _var_dof_map.find(jvar->name());
5626 if (it != _var_dof_map.end())
5627 {
5628 unsigned int j = jvar->number();
5629 nonlocal_cm(i, j) = 1;
5630 }
5631 }
5632 }
5633 }
5634 }
5635}
5636
5637bool
5638FEProblemBase::areCoupled(const unsigned int ivar,
5639 const unsigned int jvar,
5640 const unsigned int nl_sys) const
5641{
5642 return (*_cm[nl_sys])(ivar, jvar);
5643}
