5656
5657void
5658FEProblemBase::init()
5659{
5660 if (_initialized)
5661 return;
5662
5663 TIME_SECTION("init", 2, "Initializing");
5664
5665 // call executioner's preProblemInit so that it can do some setups before problem init
5666 _app.getExecutioner()->preProblemInit();
5667
5668 // If we have AD and we are doing global AD indexing, then we should by default set the matrix
5669 // coupling to full. If the user has told us to trust their coupling matrix, then this call will
5670 // not do anything
5671 if (haveADObjects() && Moose::globalADIndexing())
5672 setCoupling(Moose::COUPLING_FULL);
5673
5674 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5675 {
5676 auto & nl = _nl[i];
5677 auto & cm = _cm[i];
5678
5679 unsigned int n_vars = nl->nVariables();
5680 {
5681 TIME_SECTION("fillCouplingMatrix", 3, "Filling Coupling Matrix");
5682
5683 switch (_coupling)
5684 {
5685 case Moose::COUPLING_DIAG:
5686 cm = std::make_unique<CouplingMatrix>(n_vars);
5687 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_vars; i++)
5688 (*cm)(i, i) = 1;
5689 break;
5690
5691 // for full jacobian
5692 case Moose::COUPLING_FULL:
5693 cm = std::make_unique<CouplingMatrix>(n_vars);
5694 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_vars; i++)
5695 for (unsigned int j = 0; j < n_vars; j++)
5696 (*cm)(i, j) = 1;
5697 break;
5698
5699 case Moose::COUPLING_CUSTOM:
5700 // do nothing, _cm was already set through couplingMatrix() call
5701 break;
5702 }
5703 }
5704
5705 nl->dofMap()._dof_coupling = cm.get();
5706
5707 // If there are no variables, make sure to pass a nullptr coupling
5708 // matrix, to avoid warnings about non-nullptr yet empty
5709 // CouplingMatrices.
5710 if (n_vars == 0)
5711 nl->dofMap()._dof_coupling = nullptr;
5712
5713 nl->dofMap().attach_extra_sparsity_function(&extraSparsity, nl.get());
5714 nl->dofMap().attach_extra_send_list_function(&extraSendList, nl.get());
5715 _aux->dofMap().attach_extra_send_list_function(&extraSendList, _aux.get());
5716
5717 if (!_skip_nl_system_check && _solve && n_vars == 0)
5718 mooseError("No variables specified in the FEProblemBase '", name(), "'.");
5719 }
5720
5721 ghostGhostedBoundaries(); // We do this again right here in case new boundaries have been added
5722
5723 // We may have added element/nodes to the mesh in ghostGhostedBoundaries so we need to update
5724 // all of our mesh information. We need to make sure that mesh information is up-to-date before
5725 // EquationSystems::init because that will call through to updateGeomSearch (for sparsity
5726 // augmentation) and if we haven't added back boundary node information before that latter call,
5727 // then we're screwed. We'll get things like "Unable to find closest node!"
5728 _mesh.meshChanged();
5729 if (_displaced_problem)
5730 _displaced_mesh->meshChanged();
5731
5732 // do not assemble system matrix for JFNK solve
5733 for (auto & nl : _nl)
5734 {
5735 if (solverParams()._type == Moose::ST_JFNK)
5736 nl->turnOffJacobian();
5737 nl->init();
5738 }
5739 _aux->init();
5740
5741 // Build the mortar segment meshes, if they haven't been already, for a couple reasons:
5742 // 1) Get the ghosting correct for both static and dynamic meshes
5743 // 2) Make sure the mortar mesh is built for mortar constraints that live on the static mesh
5744 //
5745 // It is worth-while to note that mortar meshes that live on a dynamic mesh will be built
5746 // during residual and Jacobian evaluation because when displacements are solution variables
5747 // the mortar mesh will move and change during the course of a non-linear solve. We DO NOT
5748 // redo ghosting during non-linear solve, so for purpose 1) the below call has to be made
5749 if (!_mortar_data.initialized())
5750 updateMortarMesh();
5751
5752 {
5753 TIME_SECTION("EquationSystems::Init", 2, "Initializing Equation Systems");
5754 es().init();
5755 }
5756
5757 // Now that the equation system and the dof distribution is done, we can generate the
5758 // finite volume-related parts if needed.
5759 if (haveFV())
5760 _mesh.setupFiniteVolumeMeshData();
5761
5762 for (auto & nl : _nl)
5763 nl->update();
5764 _aux->update();
5765
5766 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); ++tid)
5767 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5768 _assembly[tid][i]->init(_cm[i].get());
5769
5770 if (_displaced_problem)
5771 _displaced_problem->init();
5772
5773 _initialized = true;
5774}
5775
5776unsigned int
5777FEProblemBase::nlSysNum(const NonlinearSystemName & nl_sys_name) const
5778{
5779 std::istringstream ss(nl_sys_name);
5780 unsigned int nl_sys_num;
5781 if (!(ss >> nl_sys_num) || !ss.eof())
5782 nl_sys_num = libmesh_map_find(_nl_sys_name_to_num, nl_sys_name);
5783
5784 return nl_sys_num;
5785}
5786
5787void
5788FEProblemBase::solve(const unsigned int nl_sys_num)
5789{
5790 TIME_SECTION("solve", 1, "Solving", false);
5791
5792 setCurrentNonlinearSystem(nl_sys_num);
5793
5794 // This prevents stale dof indices from lingering around and possibly leading to invalid reads
5795 // and writes. Dof indices may be made stale through operations like mesh adaptivity
5796 clearAllDofIndices();
5797 if (_displaced_problem)
5798 _displaced_problem->clearAllDofIndices();
5799
5800#if PETSC_RELEASE_LESS_THAN(3, 12, 0)
5801 Moose::PetscSupport::petscSetOptions(
5802 _petsc_options, _solver_params); // Make sure the PETSc options are setup for this app
5803#else
5804 // Now this database will be the default
5805 // Each app should have only one database
5806 if (!_app.isUltimateMaster())
5807 PetscOptionsPush(_petsc_option_data_base);
5808 // We did not add PETSc options to database yet
5809 if (!_is_petsc_options_inserted)
5810 {
5811 Moose::PetscSupport::petscSetOptions(_petsc_options, _solver_params);
5812 _is_petsc_options_inserted = true;
5813 }
5814#endif
5815 // set up DM which is required if use a field split preconditioner
5816 // We need to setup DM every "solve()" because libMesh destroy SNES after solve()
5817 // Do not worry, DM setup is very cheap
5818 if (_current_nl_sys->haveFieldSplitPreconditioner())
5819 Moose::PetscSupport::petscSetupDM(*_current_nl_sys);
5820
5821 Moose::setSolverDefaults(*this);
5822
5823 // Setup the output system for printing linear/nonlinear iteration information
5824 initPetscOutput();
5825
5826 possiblyRebuildGeomSearchPatches();
5827
5828 // reset flag so that residual evaluation does not get skipped
5829 // and the next non-linear iteration does not automatically fail with
5830 // "DIVERGED_NANORINF", when we throw an exception and stop solve
5831 _fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check = false;
5832
5833 if (_solve)
5834 _current_nl_sys->solve();
5835
5836 if (_solve)
5837 _current_nl_sys->update();
5838
5839 // sync solutions in displaced problem
5840 if (_displaced_problem)
5841 _displaced_problem->syncSolutions();
5842
5843#if !PETSC_RELEASE_LESS_THAN(3, 12, 0)
5844 if (!_app.isUltimateMaster())
5845 PetscOptionsPop();
5846#endif
5847}
5848
5849void
5850FEProblemBase::setException(const std::string & message)
5851{
5852 _has_exception = true;
5853 _exception_message = message;
5854}
5855
5856void
5857FEProblemBase::checkExceptionAndStopSolve(bool print_message)
5858{
5859 if (_skip_exception_check)
5860 return;
5861
5862 TIME_SECTION("checkExceptionAndStopSolve", 5);
5863
5864 // See if any processor had an exception. If it did, get back the
5865 // processor that the exception occurred on.
5866 unsigned int processor_id;
5867
5868 _communicator.maxloc(_has_exception, processor_id);
5869
5870 if (_has_exception)
5871 {
5872 _communicator.broadcast(_exception_message, processor_id);
5873
5874 // Print the message
5875 if (_communicator.rank() == 0 && print_message)
5876 Moose::err << _exception_message << std::endl;
5877
5878 // Stop the solve -- this entails setting
5879 // SNESSetFunctionDomainError() or directly inserting NaNs in the
5880 // residual vector to let PETSc >= 3.6 return DIVERGED_NANORINF.
5881 _current_nl_sys->stopSolve();
5882
5883 // and close Aux system (we MUST do this here; see #11525)
5884 _aux->solution().close();
5885
5886 // We've handled this exception, so we no longer have one.
5887 _has_exception = false;
5888
5889 // Force the next non-linear convergence check to fail (and all further residual evaluation to
5890 // be skipped).
5891 _fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check = true;
5892
5893 // Repropagate the exception, so it can be caught at a higher level, typically
5894 // this is NonlinearSystem::computeResidual().
5895 throw MooseException(_exception_message);
5896 }
5897}

5904 else

5942void
5943FEProblemBase::advanceState()
5944{
5945 TIME_SECTION("advanceState", 5, "Advancing State");
5946
5947 for (auto & nl : _nl)
5948 nl->copyOldSolutions();
5949 _aux->copyOldSolutions();
5950
5951 if (_displaced_problem)
5952 {
5953 for (const auto i : index_range(_nl))
5954 _displaced_problem->nlSys(i).copyOldSolutions();
5955 _displaced_problem->auxSys().copyOldSolutions();
5956 }
5957
5958 _reporter_data.copyValuesBack();
5959
5960 if (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5961 _material_props.shift();
5962
5963 if (_bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5964 _bnd_material_props.shift();
5965
5966 if (_neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
5967 _neighbor_material_props.shift();
5968}

6052
6053Real
6054FEProblemBase::getTimeFromStateArg(const Moose::StateArg & state) const
6055{
6056 if (state.iteration_type != Moose::SolutionIterationType::Time)
6057 // If we are any iteration type other than time (e.g. nonlinear), then temporally we are still
6058 // in the present time
6059 return time();
6060
6061 switch (state.state)
6062 {
6063 case 0:
6064 return time();
6065
6066 case 1:
6067 return timeOld();
6068
6069 default:
6070 mooseError("Unhandled state ", state.state, " in FEProblemBase::getTimeFromStateArg");
6071 }
6072}
6073
6074void
6075FEProblemBase::addTimeIntegrator(const std::string & type,
6076 const std::string & name,
6077 InputParameters & parameters)
6078{
6079 parallel_object_only();
6080
6081 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
6082 logAdd("TimeIntegrator", name, type);
6083 _aux->addTimeIntegrator(type, name + ":aux", parameters);
6084 for (auto & nl : _nl)
6085 nl->addTimeIntegrator(type, name + ":" + nl->name(), parameters);
6086 _has_time_integrator = true;
6087
6088 // add vectors to store u_dot, u_dotdot, udot_old, u_dotdot_old and
6089 // solution vectors older than 2 time steps, if requested by the time
6090 // integrator
6091 _aux->addDotVectors();
6092 for (auto & nl : _nl)
6093 {
6094 nl->addDotVectors();
6095
6096 auto tag_udot = nl->getTimeIntegrator()->uDotFactorTag();
6097 if (!nl->hasVector(tag_udot))
6098 nl->associateVectorToTag(*nl->solutionUDot(), tag_udot);
6099 auto tag_udotdot = nl->getTimeIntegrator()->uDotDotFactorTag();
6100 if (!nl->hasVector(tag_udotdot) && uDotDotRequested())
6101 nl->associateVectorToTag(*nl->solutionUDotDot(), tag_udotdot);
6102 }
6103}
6104
6105void
6106FEProblemBase::addPredictor(const std::string & type,
6107 const std::string & name,
6108 InputParameters & parameters)
6109{
6110 parallel_object_only();
6111
6112 parameters.set<SubProblem *>("_subproblem") = this;
6113 std::shared_ptr<Predictor> predictor = _factory.create<Predictor>(type, name, parameters);
6114 logAdd("Predictor", name, type);
6115
6116 for (auto & nl : _nl)
6117 nl->setPredictor(predictor);
6118}
6119
6120Real
6121FEProblemBase::computeResidualL2Norm()
6122{
6123 TIME_SECTION("computeResidualL2Norm", 2, "Computing L2 Norm of Residual");
6124
6125 if (_nl.size() > 1)
6126 mooseError("Multiple nonlinear systems in the same input are not currently supported when "
6127 "performing fixed point iterations in multi-app contexts");
6128
6129 _current_nl_sys = _nl[0].get();
6130 computeResidual(*_nl[0]->currentSolution(), _nl[0]->RHS(), /*nl_sys=*/0);
6131
6132 return _nl[0]->RHS().l2_norm();
6133}

6144 computeResidual(soln, residual, sys.number());
6145}

6147void
6148FEProblemBase::computeResidual(NonlinearImplicitSystem & sys,
6149 const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6150 NumericVector<Number> & residual)
6151{
6152 mooseDeprecated("Please use computeResidualSys");
6153
6154 computeResidualSys(sys, soln, residual);
6155}
6156
6157void
6158FEProblemBase::computeResidual(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6159 NumericVector<Number> & residual,
6160 const unsigned int nl_sys_num)
6161{
6162 setCurrentNonlinearSystem(nl_sys_num);
6163
6164 // We associate the residual tag with the given residual vector to make sure we
6165 // don't filter it out below
6166 _current_nl_sys->associateVectorToTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6167 const auto & residual_vector_tags = getVectorTags(Moose::VECTOR_TAG_RESIDUAL);
6168
6169 // We filter out tags which do not have associated vectors in the current nonlinear
6170 // system. This is essential to be able to use system-dependent residual tags.
6171 selectVectorTagsFromSystem(*_current_nl_sys, residual_vector_tags, _fe_vector_tags);
6172
6173 computeResidualInternal(soln, residual, _fe_vector_tags);
6174}
6175
6176void
6177FEProblemBase::computeResidualAndJacobian(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6178 NumericVector<Number> & residual,
6179 SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian)
6180{
6181 // vector tags
6182 {
6183 _current_nl_sys->associateVectorToTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6184 const auto & residual_vector_tags = getVectorTags(Moose::VECTOR_TAG_RESIDUAL);
6185
6186 // We filter out tags which do not have associated vectors in the current nonlinear
6187 // system. This is essential to be able to use system-dependent residual tags.
6188 selectVectorTagsFromSystem(*_current_nl_sys, residual_vector_tags, _fe_vector_tags);
6189
6190 setCurrentResidualVectorTags(_fe_vector_tags);
6191 }
6192
6193 // matrix tags
6194 {
6195 _fe_matrix_tags.clear();
6196
6197 auto & tags = getMatrixTags();
6198 for (auto & tag : tags)
6199 _fe_matrix_tags.insert(tag.second);
6200 }
6201
6202 try
6203 {
6204 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(soln);
6205
6206 _current_nl_sys->associateVectorToTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6207 _current_nl_sys->associateMatrixToTag(jacobian, _current_nl_sys->systemMatrixTag());
6208
6209 for (const auto tag : _fe_matrix_tags)
6210 if (_current_nl_sys->hasMatrix(tag))
6211 {
6212 auto & matrix = _current_nl_sys->getMatrix(tag);
6213 matrix.zero();
6214 if (haveADObjects())
6215 // PETSc algorithms require diagonal allocations regardless of whether there is non-zero
6216 // diagonal dependence. With global AD indexing we only add non-zero
6217 // dependence, so PETSc will scream at us unless we artificially add the diagonals.
6218 for (auto index : make_range(matrix.row_start(), matrix.row_stop()))
6219 matrix.add(index, index, 0);
6220 }
6221
6222 _aux->zeroVariablesForResidual();
6223
6224 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
6225
6226 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_LINEAR;
6227
6228 // Random interface objects
6229 for (const auto & it : _random_data_objects)
6230 it.second->updateSeeds(EXEC_LINEAR);
6231
6232 setCurrentlyComputingResidual(true);
6233 setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(true);
6234 setCurrentlyComputingResidualAndJacobian(true);
6235 if (_displaced_problem)
6236 {
6237 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingResidual(true);
6238 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(true);
6239 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingResidualAndJacobian(true);
6240 }
6241
6242 execTransfers(EXEC_LINEAR);
6243
6244 execMultiApps(EXEC_LINEAR);
6245
6246 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6247 reinitScalars(tid);
6248
6249 computeUserObjects(EXEC_LINEAR, Moose::PRE_AUX);
6250
6251 _aux->residualSetup();
6252
6253 if (_displaced_problem)
6254 {
6255 _aux->compute(EXEC_PRE_DISPLACE);
6256 try
6257 {
6258 try
6259 {
6260 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
6261 if (_mortar_data.hasDisplacedObjects())
6262 updateMortarMesh();
6263 }
6264 catch (libMesh::LogicError & e)
6265 {
6266 mooseException("We caught a libMesh error in FEProblemBase: ", e.what());
6267 }
6268 }
6269 catch (MooseException & e)
6270 {
6271 setException(e.what());
6272 }
6273 try
6274 {
6275 // Propagate the exception to all processes if we had one
6276 checkExceptionAndStopSolve();
6277 }
6278 catch (MooseException &)
6279 {
6280 // Just end now. We've inserted our NaN into the residual vector
6281 return;
6282 }
6283 }
6284
6285 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6286 {
6287 _all_materials.residualSetup(tid);
6288 _functions.residualSetup(tid);
6289 }
6290
6291 // Where is the aux system done? Could the non-current nonlinear systems also be done there?
6292 for (auto & nl : _nl)
6293 nl->computeTimeDerivatives();
6294
6295 try
6296 {
6297 _aux->compute(EXEC_LINEAR);
6298 }
6299 catch (MooseException & e)
6300 {
6301 _console << "\nA MooseException was raised during Auxiliary variable computation.\n"
6302 << "The next solve will fail, the timestep will be reduced, and we will try again.\n"
6303 << std::endl;
6304
6305 // We know the next solve is going to fail, so there's no point in
6306 // computing anything else after this. Plus, using incompletely
6307 // computed AuxVariables in subsequent calculations could lead to
6308 // other errors or unhandled exceptions being thrown.
6309 return;
6310 }
6311
6312 computeUserObjects(EXEC_LINEAR, Moose::POST_AUX);
6313
6314 executeControls(EXEC_LINEAR);
6315
6316 _app.getOutputWarehouse().residualSetup();
6317
6318 _safe_access_tagged_vectors = false;
6319 _safe_access_tagged_matrices = false;
6320
6321 _current_nl_sys->computeResidualAndJacobianTags(_fe_vector_tags, _fe_matrix_tags);
6322
6323 _safe_access_tagged_vectors = true;
6324 _safe_access_tagged_matrices = true;
6325
6326 _current_nl_sys->disassociateMatrixFromTag(jacobian, _current_nl_sys->systemMatrixTag());
6327 _current_nl_sys->disassociateVectorFromTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6328
6329 setCurrentlyComputingResidual(false);
6330 setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(false);
6331 setCurrentlyComputingResidualAndJacobian(false);
6332 if (_displaced_problem)
6333 {
6334 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingResidual(false);
6335 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(false);
6336 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingResidualAndJacobian(false);
6337 }
6338
6339 clearCurrentResidualVectorTags();
6340 }
6341 catch (MooseException & e)
6342 {
6343 // If a MooseException propagates all the way to here, it means
6344 // that it was thrown from a MOOSE system where we do not
6345 // (currently) properly support the throwing of exceptions, and
6346 // therefore we have no choice but to error out. It may be
6347 // *possible* to handle exceptions from other systems, but in the
6348 // meantime, we don't want to silently swallow any unhandled
6349 // exceptions here.
6350 mooseError("An unhandled MooseException was raised during residual computation. Please "
6351 "contact the MOOSE team for assistance.");
6352 }
6353
6354 // Reset execution flag as after this point we are no longer on LINEAR
6355 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_NONE;
6356}
6357
6358void
6359FEProblemBase::computeResidualTag(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6360 NumericVector<Number> & residual,
6361 TagID tag)
6362{
6363 try
6364 {
6365 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(soln);
6366
6367 _current_nl_sys->associateVectorToTag(residual, tag);
6368
6369 computeResidualTags({tag});
6370
6371 _current_nl_sys->disassociateVectorFromTag(residual, tag);
6372 }
6373 catch (MooseException & e)
6374 {
6375 // If a MooseException propagates all the way to here, it means
6376 // that it was thrown from a MOOSE system where we do not
6377 // (currently) properly support the throwing of exceptions, and
6378 // therefore we have no choice but to error out. It may be
6379 // *possible* to handle exceptions from other systems, but in the
6380 // meantime, we don't want to silently swallow any unhandled
6381 // exceptions here.
6382 mooseError("An unhandled MooseException was raised during residual computation. Please "
6383 "contact the MOOSE team for assistance.");
6384 }
6385}
6386
6387void
6388FEProblemBase::computeResidualInternal(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6389 NumericVector<Number> & residual,
6390 const std::set<TagID> & tags)
6391{
6392 parallel_object_only();
6393
6394 TIME_SECTION("computeResidualInternal", 1);
6395
6396 try
6397 {
6398 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(soln);
6399
6400 _current_nl_sys->associateVectorToTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6401
6402 computeResidualTags(tags);
6403
6404 _current_nl_sys->disassociateVectorFromTag(residual, _current_nl_sys->residualVectorTag());
6405 }
6406 catch (MooseException & e)
6407 {
6408 // If a MooseException propagates all the way to here, it means
6409 // that it was thrown from a MOOSE system where we do not
6410 // (currently) properly support the throwing of exceptions, and
6411 // therefore we have no choice but to error out. It may be
6412 // *possible* to handle exceptions from other systems, but in the
6413 // meantime, we don't want to silently swallow any unhandled
6414 // exceptions here.
6415 mooseError("An unhandled MooseException was raised during residual computation. Please "
6416 "contact the MOOSE team for assistance.");
6417 }
6418}

6436 }

6440 // that it was thrown from a MOOSE system where we do not
6441 // (currently) properly support the throwing of exceptions, and
6442 // therefore we have no choice but to error out. It may be
6443 // *possible* to handle exceptions from other systems, but in the
6444 // meantime, we don't want to silently swallow any unhandled
6445 // exceptions here.

6447 "contact the MOOSE team for assistance.");
6448 }

6450
6451void
6452FEProblemBase::computeResidualTags(const std::set<TagID> & tags)
6453{
6454 parallel_object_only();
6455
6456 TIME_SECTION("computeResidualTags", 5, "Computing Residual");
6457
6458 ADReal::do_derivatives = false;
6459
6460 setCurrentResidualVectorTags(tags);
6461
6462 _aux->zeroVariablesForResidual();
6463
6464 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
6465
6466 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_LINEAR;
6467
6468 // Random interface objects
6469 for (const auto & it : _random_data_objects)
6470 it.second->updateSeeds(EXEC_LINEAR);
6471
6472 execTransfers(EXEC_LINEAR);
6473
6474 execMultiApps(EXEC_LINEAR);
6475
6476 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6477 reinitScalars(tid);
6478
6479 computeUserObjects(EXEC_LINEAR, Moose::PRE_AUX);
6480
6481 _aux->residualSetup();
6482
6483 if (_displaced_problem)
6484 {
6485 _aux->compute(EXEC_PRE_DISPLACE);
6486 try
6487 {
6488 try
6489 {
6490 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
6491 if (_mortar_data.hasDisplacedObjects())
6492 updateMortarMesh();
6493 }
6494 catch (libMesh::LogicError & e)
6495 {
6496 mooseException("We caught a libMesh error in FEProblemBase: ", e.what());
6497 }
6498 }
6499 catch (MooseException & e)
6500 {
6501 setException(e.what());
6502 }
6503 try
6504 {
6505 // Propagate the exception to all processes if we had one
6506 checkExceptionAndStopSolve();
6507 }
6508 catch (MooseException &)
6509 {
6510 // Just end now. We've inserted our NaN into the residual vector
6511 return;
6512 }
6513 }
6514
6515 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6516 {
6517 _all_materials.residualSetup(tid);
6518 _functions.residualSetup(tid);
6519 }
6520
6521 // Where is the aux system done? Could the non-current nonlinear systems also be done there?
6522 for (auto & nl : _nl)
6523 nl->computeTimeDerivatives();
6524
6525 auto reset_state = [this]()
6526 {
6527 ADReal::do_derivatives = true;
6528 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_NONE;
6529 clearCurrentResidualVectorTags();
6530 };
6531 try
6532 {
6533 _aux->compute(EXEC_LINEAR);
6534 }
6535 catch (MooseException & e)
6536 {
6537 _console << "\nA MooseException was raised during Auxiliary variable computation.\n"
6538 << "The next solve will fail, the timestep will be reduced, and we will try again.\n"
6539 << std::endl;
6540
6541 // We know the next solve is going to fail, so there's no point in
6542 // computing anything else after this. Plus, using incompletely
6543 // computed AuxVariables in subsequent calculations could lead to
6544 // other errors or unhandled exceptions being thrown.
6545 reset_state();
6546 return;
6547 }
6548
6549 computeUserObjects(EXEC_LINEAR, Moose::POST_AUX);
6550
6551 executeControls(EXEC_LINEAR);
6552
6553 _app.getOutputWarehouse().residualSetup();
6554
6555 _safe_access_tagged_vectors = false;
6556 _current_nl_sys->computeResidualTags(tags);
6557 _safe_access_tagged_vectors = true;
6558 reset_state();
6559}

6564 SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian)

6583void
6584FEProblemBase::computeJacobian(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6585 SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
6586 const unsigned int nl_sys_num)
6587{

6589

6591
6592 auto & tags = getMatrixTags();
6593 for (auto & tag : tags)
6594 _fe_matrix_tags.insert(tag.second);
6595
6596 computeJacobianInternal(soln, jacobian, _fe_matrix_tags);
6597}
6598
6599void
6600FEProblemBase::computeJacobianInternal(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6601 SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
6602 const std::set<TagID> & tags)
6603{
6604 TIME_SECTION("computeJacobianInternal", 1);
6605
6606 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(soln);
6607
6608 _current_nl_sys->associateMatrixToTag(jacobian, _current_nl_sys->systemMatrixTag());
6609
6610 computeJacobianTags(tags);
6611
6612 _current_nl_sys->disassociateMatrixFromTag(jacobian, _current_nl_sys->systemMatrixTag());
6613}
6614
6615void
6616FEProblemBase::computeJacobianTags(const std::set<TagID> & tags)
6617{
6618 if (!_has_jacobian || !_const_jacobian)
6619 {
6620 TIME_SECTION("computeJacobianTags", 5, "Computing Jacobian");
6621
6622 for (auto tag : tags)
6623 if (_current_nl_sys->hasMatrix(tag))
6624 {
6625 auto & matrix = _current_nl_sys->getMatrix(tag);
6626 matrix.zero();
6627 if (haveADObjects())
6628 // PETSc algorithms require diagonal allocations regardless of whether there is non-zero
6629 // diagonal dependence. With global AD indexing we only add non-zero
6630 // dependence, so PETSc will scream at us unless we artificially add the diagonals.
6631 for (auto index : make_range(matrix.row_start(), matrix.row_stop()))
6632 matrix.add(index, index, 0);
6633 }
6634
6635 _aux->zeroVariablesForJacobian();
6636
6637 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
6638
6639 // Random interface objects
6640 for (const auto & it : _random_data_objects)
6641 it.second->updateSeeds(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6642
6643 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_NONLINEAR;
6644 _currently_computing_jacobian = true;
6645 if (_displaced_problem)
6646 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(true);
6647
6648 execTransfers(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6649 execMultiApps(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6650
6651 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6652 reinitScalars(tid);
6653
6654 computeUserObjects(EXEC_NONLINEAR, Moose::PRE_AUX);
6655
6656 _aux->jacobianSetup();
6657
6658 if (_displaced_problem)
6659 {
6660 _aux->compute(EXEC_PRE_DISPLACE);
6661 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
6662 }
6663
6664 for (unsigned int tid = 0; tid < n_threads; tid++)
6665 {
6666 _all_materials.jacobianSetup(tid);
6667 _functions.jacobianSetup(tid);
6668 }
6669
6670 // When computing the initial Jacobian for automatic variable scaling we need to make sure
6671 // that the time derivatives have been calculated. So we'll call down to the nonlinear system
6672 // here. Note that if we are not doing this initial Jacobian calculation we will just exit in
6673 // that class to avoid redundant calculation (the residual function also computes time
6674 // derivatives)
6675 _current_nl_sys->computeTimeDerivatives(/*jacobian_calculation =*/true);
6676
6677 _aux->compute(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6678
6679 computeUserObjects(EXEC_NONLINEAR, Moose::POST_AUX);
6680
6681 executeControls(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6682
6683 _app.getOutputWarehouse().jacobianSetup();
6684
6685 _safe_access_tagged_matrices = false;
6686
6687 _current_nl_sys->computeJacobianTags(tags);
6688
6689 // For explicit Euler calculations for example we often compute the Jacobian one time and then
6690 // re-use it over and over. If we're performing automatic scaling, we don't want to use that
6691 // kernel, diagonal-block only Jacobian for our actual matrix when performing solves!
6692 if (!_current_nl_sys->computingScalingJacobian())
6693 _has_jacobian = true;
6694
6695 _currently_computing_jacobian = false;
6696 if (_displaced_problem)
6697 _displaced_problem->setCurrentlyComputingJacobian(false);
6698 _safe_access_tagged_matrices = true;
6699 }
6700
6701 // Reset execute_on flag as after this point we are no longer on NONLINEAR
6702 _current_execute_on_flag = EXEC_NONE;
6703}
6704
6705void
6706FEProblemBase::computeJacobianBlocks(std::vector<JacobianBlock *> & blocks,
6707 const unsigned int nl_sys_num)
6708{
6709 TIME_SECTION("computeTransientImplicitJacobian", 2);
6710 setCurrentNonlinearSystem(nl_sys_num);
6711
6712 if (_displaced_problem)
6713 {
6714 _aux->compute(EXEC_PRE_DISPLACE);
6715 _displaced_problem->updateMesh();
6716 }
6717
6718 _aux->compute(EXEC_NONLINEAR);
6719
6720 _currently_computing_jacobian = true;
6721 _current_nl_sys->computeJacobianBlocks(blocks);
6722 _currently_computing_jacobian = false;
6723}
6724
6725void
6726FEProblemBase::computeJacobianBlock(SparseMatrix<Number> & jacobian,
6727 libMesh::System & precond_system,
6728 unsigned int ivar,
6729 unsigned int jvar)
6730{
6731 JacobianBlock jac_block(precond_system, jacobian, ivar, jvar);
6732 std::vector<JacobianBlock *> blocks = {&jac_block};
6733 mooseAssert(_current_nl_sys, "This should be non-null");
6734 computeJacobianBlocks(blocks, _current_nl_sys->number());
6735}
6736
6737void
6738FEProblemBase::computeBounds(NonlinearImplicitSystem & libmesh_dbg_var(sys),
6739 NumericVector<Number> & lower,
6740 NumericVector<Number> & upper)
6741{
6742 mooseAssert(_current_nl_sys && (sys.number() == _current_nl_sys->number()),
6743 "I expect these system numbers to be the same");
6744
6745 if (!_current_nl_sys->hasVector("lower_bound") || !_current_nl_sys->hasVector("upper_bound"))
6746 return;
6747
6748 TIME_SECTION("computeBounds", 1, "Computing Bounds");
6749
6750 NumericVector<Number> & _lower = _current_nl_sys->getVector("lower_bound");
6751 NumericVector<Number> & _upper = _current_nl_sys->getVector("upper_bound");
6752 _lower.swap(lower);
6753 _upper.swap(upper);
6754 for (THREAD_ID tid = 0; tid < libMesh::n_threads(); tid++)
6755 _all_materials.residualSetup(tid);
6756
6757 _aux->residualSetup();
6758 _aux->compute(EXEC_LINEAR);
6759 _lower.swap(lower);
6760 _upper.swap(upper);
6761
6762 checkExceptionAndStopSolve();
6763}

6776 postfix << "_" << i;

6778 sp.push_back(&_current_nl_sys->getVector(modename));
6779 }
6780}

6811
6812void
6813FEProblemBase::computePostCheck(NonlinearImplicitSystem & sys,
6814 const NumericVector<Number> & old_soln,
6815 NumericVector<Number> & search_direction,
6816 NumericVector<Number> & new_soln,
6817 bool & changed_search_direction,
6818 bool & changed_new_soln)
6819{
6820 mooseAssert(_current_nl_sys && (sys.number() == _current_nl_sys->number()),
6821 "I expect these system numbers to be the same");
6822
6823 // This function replaces the old PetscSupport::dampedCheck() function.
6824 //
6825 // 1.) Recreate code in PetscSupport::dampedCheck() for constructing
6826 // ghosted "soln" and "update" vectors.
6827 // 2.) Call FEProblemBase::computeDamping() with these ghost vectors.
6828 // 3.) Recreate the code in PetscSupport::dampedCheck() to actually update
6829 // the solution vector based on the damping, and set the "changed" flags
6830 // appropriately.
6831
6832 TIME_SECTION("computePostCheck", 2, "Computing Post Check");
6833
6834 // MOOSE's FEProblemBase doesn't update the solution during the
6835 // postcheck, but FEProblemBase-derived classes might.
6836 if (_has_dampers || shouldUpdateSolution())
6837 {
6838 // We need ghosted versions of new_soln and search_direction (the
6839 // ones we get from libmesh/PETSc are PARALLEL vectors. To make
6840 // our lives simpler, we use the same ghosting pattern as the
6841 // system's current_local_solution to create new ghosted vectors.
6842
6843 // Construct zeroed-out clones with the same ghosted dofs as the
6844 // System's current_local_solution.
6845 std::unique_ptr<NumericVector<Number>> ghosted_solution =
6846 sys.current_local_solution->zero_clone(),
6847 ghosted_search_direction =
6848 sys.current_local_solution->zero_clone();
6849
6850 // Copy values from input vectors into clones with ghosted values.
6851 *ghosted_solution = new_soln;
6852 *ghosted_search_direction = search_direction;
6853
6854 if (_has_dampers)
6855 {
6856 // Compute the damping coefficient using the ghosted vectors
6857 Real damping = computeDamping(*ghosted_solution, *ghosted_search_direction);
6858
6859 // If some non-trivial damping was computed, update the new_soln
6860 // vector accordingly.
6861 if (damping < 1.0)
6862 {
6863 new_soln = old_soln;
6864 new_soln.add(-damping, search_direction);
6865 changed_new_soln = true;
6866 }
6867 }
6868
6869 if (shouldUpdateSolution())
6870 {
6871 // Update the ghosted copy of the new solution, if necessary.
6872 if (changed_new_soln)
6873 *ghosted_solution = new_soln;
6874
6875 bool updated_solution = updateSolution(new_soln, *ghosted_solution);
6876 if (updated_solution)
6877 changed_new_soln = true;
6878 }
6879 }
6880
6881 if (vectorTagExists(Moose::PREVIOUS_NL_SOLUTION_TAG))
6882 {
6883 _current_nl_sys->setPreviousNewtonSolution(old_soln);
6884 _aux->setPreviousNewtonSolution();
6885 }
6886
6887 // MOOSE doesn't change the search_direction
6888 changed_search_direction = false;
6889}
6890
6891Real
6892FEProblemBase::computeDamping(const NumericVector<Number> & soln,
6893 const NumericVector<Number> & update)
6894{
6895 // Default to no damping
6896 Real damping = 1.0;
6897
6898 if (_has_dampers)
6899 {
6900 TIME_SECTION("computeDamping", 1, "Computing Damping");
6901
6902 // Save pointer to the current solution
6903 const NumericVector<Number> * _saved_current_solution = _current_nl_sys->currentSolution();
6904
6905 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(soln);
6906 // For now, do not re-compute auxiliary variables. Doing so allows a wild solution increment
6907 // to get to the material models, which may not be able to cope with drastically different
6908 // values. Once more complete dependency checking is in place, auxiliary variables (and
6909 // material properties) will be computed as needed by dampers.
6910 // _aux.compute();
6911 damping = _current_nl_sys->computeDamping(soln, update);
6912
6913 // restore saved solution
6914 _current_nl_sys->setSolution(*_saved_current_solution);
6915 }
6916
6917 return damping;
6918}
6919
6920bool
6921FEProblemBase::shouldUpdateSolution()
6922{
6923 return false;
6924}
6925
6926bool
6927FEProblemBase::updateSolution(NumericVector<Number> & /*vec_solution*/,
6928 NumericVector<Number> & /*ghosted_solution*/)
6929{
6930 return false;
6931}

7025
7026void
7027FEProblemBase::possiblyRebuildGeomSearchPatches()
7028{
7029 if (_displaced_problem) // Only need to do this if things are moving...
7030 {
7031 TIME_SECTION("possiblyRebuildGeomSearchPatches", 5, "Rebuilding Geometric Search Patches");
7032
7033 switch (_mesh.getPatchUpdateStrategy())
7034 {
7035 case Moose::Never:
7036 break;
7037 case Moose::Iteration:
7038 // Update the list of ghosted elements at the start of the time step
7039 _geometric_search_data.updateGhostedElems();
7040 _mesh.updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7041
7042 _displaced_problem->geomSearchData().updateGhostedElems();
7043 _displaced_mesh->updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7044
7045 // The commands below ensure that the sparsity of the Jacobian matrix is
7046 // augmented at the start of the time step using neighbor nodes from the end
7047 // of the previous time step.
7048
7049 reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects();
7050
7051 // This is needed to reinitialize PETSc output
7052 initPetscOutput();
7053
7054 break;
7055
7056 case Moose::Auto:
7057 {
7058 Real max = _displaced_problem->geomSearchData().maxPatchPercentage();
7059 _communicator.max(max);
7060
7061 // If we haven't moved very far through the patch
7062 if (max < 0.4)
7063 break;
7064 }
7065 libmesh_fallthrough();
7066
7067 // Let this fall through if things do need to be updated...
7068 case Moose::Always:
7069 // Flush output here to see the message before the reinitialization, which could take a
7070 // while
7071 _console << "\n\nUpdating geometric search patches\n" << std::endl;
7072
7073 _geometric_search_data.clearNearestNodeLocators();
7074 _mesh.updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7075
7076 _displaced_problem->geomSearchData().clearNearestNodeLocators();
7077 _displaced_mesh->updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7078
7079 reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects();
7080
7081 // This is needed to reinitialize PETSc output
7082 initPetscOutput();
7083 }
7084 }
7085}
7086
7087#ifdef LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
7088void
7089FEProblemBase::initialAdaptMesh()
7090{
7091 unsigned int n = adaptivity().getInitialSteps();
7092 _cycles_completed = 0;
7093 if (n)
7094 {
7095 if (_mesh.meshSubdomains().count(Moose::INTERNAL_SIDE_LOWERD_ID) ||
7096 _mesh.meshSubdomains().count(Moose::BOUNDARY_SIDE_LOWERD_ID))
7097 mooseError("HFEM does not support mesh adaptivity currently.");
7098
7099 TIME_SECTION("initialAdaptMesh", 2, "Performing Initial Adaptivity");
7100
7101 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n; i++)
7102 {
7103 computeIndicators();
7104 computeMarkers();
7105
7106 if (_adaptivity.initialAdaptMesh())
7107 {
7108 meshChanged();
7109
7110 // reproject the initial condition
7111 projectSolution();
7112
7113 _cycles_completed++;
7114 }
7115 else
7116 {
7117 _console << "Mesh unchanged, skipping remaining steps..." << std::endl;
7118 return;
7119 }
7120 }
7121 }
7122}
7123
7124bool
7125FEProblemBase::adaptMesh()
7126{
7127 // reset cycle counter
7128 _cycles_completed = 0;
7129
7130 if (!_adaptivity.isAdaptivityDue())
7131 return false;
7132
7133 TIME_SECTION("adaptMesh", 3, "Adapting Mesh");
7134
7135 unsigned int cycles_per_step = _adaptivity.getCyclesPerStep();
7136
7137 bool mesh_changed = false;
7138
7139 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < cycles_per_step; ++i)
7140 {
7141 if (_mesh.meshSubdomains().count(Moose::INTERNAL_SIDE_LOWERD_ID) ||
7142 _mesh.meshSubdomains().count(Moose::BOUNDARY_SIDE_LOWERD_ID))
7143 mooseError("HFEM does not support mesh adaptivity currently.");
7144
7145 // Markers were already computed once by Executioner
7146 if (_adaptivity.getRecomputeMarkersFlag() && i > 0)
7147 computeMarkers();
7148
7149 bool mesh_changed_this_step;
7150 mesh_changed_this_step = _adaptivity.adaptMesh();
7151
7152 if (mesh_changed_this_step)
7153 {
7154 mesh_changed = true;
7155
7156 meshChangedHelper(true); // This may be an intermediate change
7157 _cycles_completed++;
7158 }
7159 else
7160 {
7161 _console << "Mesh unchanged, skipping remaining steps..." << std::endl;
7162 break;
7163 }
7164
7165 // Show adaptivity progress
7166 _console << std::flush;
7167 }
7168
7169 // We're done with all intermediate changes; now get systems ready
7170 // for real if necessary.
7171 if (mesh_changed)
7172 es().reinit_systems();
7173
7174 return mesh_changed;
7175}
7176#endif // LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
7177
7178void
7179FEProblemBase::initXFEM(std::shared_ptr<XFEMInterface> xfem)
7180{
7181 _xfem = xfem;
7182 _xfem->setMesh(&_mesh);
7183 if (_displaced_mesh)
7184 _xfem->setDisplacedMesh(_displaced_mesh);
7185
7186 auto fill_data = [](auto & storage)
7187 {
7188 std::vector<MaterialData *> data(libMesh::n_threads());
7189 for (const auto tid : make_range(libMesh::n_threads()))
7190 data[tid] = &storage.getMaterialData(tid);
7191 return data;
7192 };
7193 _xfem->setMaterialData(fill_data(_material_props));
7194 _xfem->setBoundaryMaterialData(fill_data(_bnd_material_props));
7195
7196 unsigned int n_threads = libMesh::n_threads();
7197 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < n_threads; ++i)
7198 for (const auto nl_sys_num : index_range(_assembly[i]))
7199 {
7200 _assembly[i][nl_sys_num]->setXFEM(_xfem);
7201 if (_displaced_problem)
7202 _displaced_problem->assembly(i, nl_sys_num).setXFEM(_xfem);
7203 }
7204}
7205
7206bool
7207FEProblemBase::updateMeshXFEM()
7208{
7209 TIME_SECTION("updateMeshXFEM", 5, "Updating XFEM");
7210
7211 bool updated = false;
7212 if (haveXFEM())
7213 {
7214 if (_xfem->updateHeal())
7215 meshChanged();
7216
7217 updated = _xfem->update(_time, _nl, *_aux);
7218 if (updated)
7219 {
7220 meshChanged();
7221 _xfem->initSolution(_nl, *_aux);
7222 restoreSolutions();
7223 }
7224 }
7225 return updated;
7226}
7227
7228void
7229FEProblemBase::meshChanged()
7230{
7231 TIME_SECTION("meshChanged", 3, "Handling Mesh Changes");
7232
7233 this->meshChangedHelper();
7234}
7235
7236void
7237FEProblemBase::meshChangedHelper(bool intermediate_change)
7238{
7239 TIME_SECTION("meshChangedHelper", 5);
7240
7241 if (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
7242 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties())
7243 _mesh.cacheChangedLists(); // Currently only used with adaptivity and stateful material
7244 // properties
7245
7246 // Clear these out because they corresponded to the old mesh
7247 _ghosted_elems.clear();
7248 ghostGhostedBoundaries();
7249
7250 // The mesh changed. We notify the MooseMesh first, because
7251 // callbacks (e.g. for sparsity calculations) triggered by the
7252 // EquationSystems reinit may require up-to-date MooseMesh caches.
7253 _mesh.meshChanged();
7254
7255 // If we're just going to alter the mesh again, all we need to
7256 // handle here is AMR and projections, not full system reinit
7257 if (intermediate_change)
7258 es().reinit_solutions();
7259 else
7260 es().reinit();
7261
7262 // Updating MooseMesh first breaks other adaptivity code, unless we
7263 // then *again* update the MooseMesh caches. E.g. the definition of
7264 // "active" and "local" may have been *changed* by refinement and
7265 // repartitioning done in EquationSystems::reinit().
7266 _mesh.meshChanged();
7267
7268 // If we have finite volume variables, we will need to recompute additional elemental/face
7269 // quantities
7270 if (haveFV() && _mesh.isFiniteVolumeInfoDirty())
7271 _mesh.setupFiniteVolumeMeshData();
7272
7273 // Let the meshChangedInterface notify the mesh changed event before we update the active
7274 // semilocal nodes, because the set of ghosted elements may potentially be updated during a mesh
7275 // changed event.
7276 for (const auto & mci : _notify_when_mesh_changes)
7277 mci->meshChanged();
7278
7279 // Since the Mesh changed, update the PointLocator object used by DiracKernels.
7280 _dirac_kernel_info.updatePointLocator(_mesh);
7281
7282 // Need to redo ghosting
7283 _geometric_search_data.reinit();
7284
7285 if (_displaced_problem)
7286 {
7287 _displaced_problem->meshChanged();
7288 _displaced_mesh->updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7289 }
7290
7291 _mesh.updateActiveSemiLocalNodeRange(_ghosted_elems);
7292
7293 _evaluable_local_elem_range.reset();
7294 _nl_evaluable_local_elem_range.reset();
7295
7296 // Just like we reinitialized our geometric search objects, we also need to reinitialize our
7297 // mortar meshes. Note that this needs to happen after DisplacedProblem::meshChanged because the
7298 // mortar mesh discretization will depend necessarily on the displaced mesh being re-displaced
7299 updateMortarMesh();
7300
7301 reinitBecauseOfGhostingOrNewGeomObjects(/*mortar_changed=*/true);
7302
7303 // We need to create new storage for newly active elements, and copy
7304 // stateful properties from the old elements.
7305 if (_has_initialized_stateful &&
7306 (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties()))
7307 {
7308 if (havePRefinement())
7309 _mesh.buildPRefinementAndCoarseningMaps(_assembly[0][0].get());
7310
7311 // Prolong properties onto newly refined elements' children
7312 {
7313 ProjectMaterialProperties pmp(
7314 /* refine = */ true, *this, _material_props, _bnd_material_props, _assembly);
7315 const auto & range = *_mesh.refinedElementRange();
7316 Threads::parallel_reduce(range, pmp);
7317
7318 // Concurrent erasure from the shared hash map is not safe while we are reading from it in
7319 // ProjectMaterialProperties, so we handle erasure here. Moreover, erasure based on key is
7320 // not thread safe in and of itself because it is a read-write operation. Note that we do not
7321 // do the erasure for p-refinement because the coarse level element is the same as our active
7322 // refined level element
7323 if (!doingPRefinement())
7324 for (const auto & elem : range)
7325 {
7326 _material_props.eraseProperty(elem);
7327 _bnd_material_props.eraseProperty(elem);
7328 _neighbor_material_props.eraseProperty(elem);
7329 }
7330 }
7331
7332 // Restrict properties onto newly coarsened elements
7333 {
7334 ProjectMaterialProperties pmp(
7335 /* refine = */ false, *this, _material_props, _bnd_material_props, _assembly);
7336 const auto & range = *_mesh.coarsenedElementRange();
7337 Threads::parallel_reduce(range, pmp);
7338 // Note that we do not do the erasure for p-refinement because the coarse level element is the
7339 // same as our active refined level element
7340 if (!doingPRefinement())
7341 for (const auto & elem : range)
7342 {
7343 auto && coarsened_children = _mesh.coarsenedElementChildren(elem);
7344 for (auto && child : coarsened_children)
7345 {
7346 _material_props.eraseProperty(child);
7347 _bnd_material_props.eraseProperty(child);
7348 _neighbor_material_props.eraseProperty(child);
7349 }
7350 }
7351 }
7352 }
7353
7354 if (_calculate_jacobian_in_uo)
7355 setVariableAllDoFMap(_uo_jacobian_moose_vars[0]);
7356
7357 _has_jacobian = false; // we have to recompute jacobian when mesh changed
7358
7359 // Since the mesh has changed, we need to make sure that we update any of our
7360 // MOOSE-system specific data. libmesh system data has already been updated
7361 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7362 nl->update(/*update_libmesh_system=*/false);
7363 _aux->update(/*update_libmesh_system=*/false);
7364}
7365
7366void
7367FEProblemBase::notifyWhenMeshChanges(MeshChangedInterface * mci)
7368{
7369 _notify_when_mesh_changes.push_back(mci);
7370}
7371
7372void
7373FEProblemBase::initElementStatefulProps(const ConstElemRange & elem_range, const bool threaded)
7374{
7375 ComputeMaterialsObjectThread cmt(
7376 *this, _material_props, _bnd_material_props, _neighbor_material_props, _assembly);
7377 if (threaded)
7378 Threads::parallel_reduce(elem_range, cmt);
7379 else
7380 cmt(elem_range, true);
7381}
7382
7383void
7384FEProblemBase::checkProblemIntegrity()
7385{
7386 TIME_SECTION("notifyWhenMeshChanges", 5);
7387
7388 // Check for unsatisfied actions
7389 const std::set<SubdomainID> & mesh_subdomains = _mesh.meshSubdomains();
7390
7391 // Check kernel coverage of subdomains (blocks) in the mesh
7392 if (!_skip_nl_system_check && _solve && _kernel_coverage_check)
7393 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7394 nl->checkKernelCoverage(mesh_subdomains);
7395
7396 // Check materials
7397 {
7398#ifdef LIBMESH_ENABLE_AMR
7399 if ((_adaptivity.isOn() || _num_grid_steps) &&
7400 (_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() || _bnd_material_props.hasStatefulProperties() ||
7401 _neighbor_material_props.hasStatefulProperties()))
7402 {
7403 _console << "Using EXPERIMENTAL Stateful Material Property projection with Adaptivity!\n"
7404 << std::flush;
7405 }
7406#endif
7407
7408 std::set<SubdomainID> local_mesh_subs(mesh_subdomains);
7409
7410 if (_material_coverage_check)
7411 {
7416 bool check_material_coverage = false;
7417 std::set<SubdomainID> ids = _all_materials.getActiveBlocks();
7418 for (const auto & id : ids)
7419 {
7420 local_mesh_subs.erase(id);
7421 check_material_coverage = true;
7422 }
7423
7424 // also exclude mortar spaces from the material check
7425 auto && mortar_subdomain_ids = _mortar_data.getMortarSubdomainIDs();
7426 for (auto subdomain_id : mortar_subdomain_ids)
7427 local_mesh_subs.erase(subdomain_id);
7428
7429 // Check Material Coverage
7430 if (check_material_coverage && !local_mesh_subs.empty())
7431 {
7432 std::stringstream extra_subdomain_ids;
7434 std::copy(local_mesh_subs.begin(),
7435 local_mesh_subs.end(),
7436 std::ostream_iterator<unsigned int>(extra_subdomain_ids, " "));
7437
7438 mooseError("The following blocks from your input mesh do not contain an active material: " +
7439 extra_subdomain_ids.str() +
7440 "\nWhen ANY mesh block contains a Material object, "
7441 "all blocks must contain a Material object.\n");
7442 }
7443 }
7444
7445 // Check material properties on blocks and boundaries
7446 checkBlockMatProps();
7447 checkBoundaryMatProps();
7448
7449 // Check that material properties exist when requested by other properties on a given block
7450 const auto & materials = _all_materials.getActiveObjects();
7451 for (const auto & material : materials)
7452 material->checkStatefulSanity();
7453
7454 // auto mats_to_check = _materials.getActiveBlockObjects();
7455 // const auto & discrete_materials = _discrete_materials.getActiveBlockObjects();
7456 // for (const auto & map_it : discrete_materials)
7457 // for (const auto & container_element : map_it.second)
7458 // mats_to_check[map_it.first].push_back(container_element);
7459 if (_material_dependency_check)
7460 checkDependMaterialsHelper(_all_materials.getActiveBlockObjects());
7461 }
7462
7463 checkUserObjects();
7464
7465 // Verify that we don't have any Element type/Coordinate Type conflicts
7466 checkCoordinateSystems();
7467
7468 // If using displacements, verify that the order of the displacement
7469 // variables matches the order of the elements in the displaced
7470 // mesh.
7471 checkDisplacementOrders();
7472
7473 // Check for postprocessor names with same name as a scalar variable
7474 checkDuplicatePostprocessorVariableNames();
7475}
7476
7477void
7478FEProblemBase::checkDisplacementOrders()
7479{
7480 if (_displaced_problem)
7481 {
7482 bool mesh_has_second_order_elements = false;
7483 for (const auto & elem : as_range(_displaced_mesh->activeLocalElementsBegin(),
7484 _displaced_mesh->activeLocalElementsEnd()))
7485 {
7486 if (elem->default_order() == SECOND)
7487 {
7488 mesh_has_second_order_elements = true;
7489 break;
7490 }
7491 }
7492
7493 // We checked our local elements, so take the max over all processors.
7494 _displaced_mesh->comm().max(mesh_has_second_order_elements);
7495
7496 // If the Mesh has second order elements, make sure the
7497 // displacement variables are second-order.
7498 if (mesh_has_second_order_elements)
7499 {
7500 const std::vector<std::string> & displacement_variables =
7501 _displaced_problem->getDisplacementVarNames();
7502
7503 for (const auto & var_name : displacement_variables)
7504 {
7505 MooseVariableFEBase & mv =
7506 _displaced_problem->getVariable(/*tid=*/0,
7507 var_name,
7508 Moose::VarKindType::VAR_ANY,
7509 Moose::VarFieldType::VAR_FIELD_STANDARD);
7510 if (mv.order() != SECOND)
7511 mooseError("Error: mesh has SECOND order elements, so all displacement variables must be "
7512 "SECOND order.");
7513 }
7514 }
7515 }
7516}
7517
7518void
7519FEProblemBase::checkUserObjects()
7520{
7521 // Check user_objects block coverage
7522 std::set<SubdomainID> mesh_subdomains = _mesh.meshSubdomains();
7523 std::set<SubdomainID> user_objects_blocks;
7524
7525 // gather names of all user_objects that were defined in the input file
7526 // and the blocks that they are defined on
7527 std::set<std::string> names;
7528
7529 std::vector<UserObject *> objects;
7530 theWarehouse().query().condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::UserObject).queryInto(objects);
7531
7532 for (const auto & obj : objects)
7533 names.insert(obj->name());
7534
7535 // See if all referenced blocks are covered
7536 std::set<SubdomainID> difference;
7537 std::set_difference(user_objects_blocks.begin(),
7538 user_objects_blocks.end(),
7539 mesh_subdomains.begin(),
7540 mesh_subdomains.end(),
7541 std::inserter(difference, difference.end()));
7542
7543 if (!difference.empty())
7544 {
7545 std::ostringstream oss;
7546 oss << "One or more UserObjects is referencing a nonexistent block:\n";
7547 for (const auto & id : difference)
7548 oss << id << "\n";
7549 mooseError(oss.str());
7550 }
7551}
7552
7553void
7554FEProblemBase::checkDependMaterialsHelper(
7555 const std::map<SubdomainID, std::vector<std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase>>> & materials_map)
7556{
7557 auto & prop_names = _material_props.statefulPropNames();
7558
7559 for (const auto & it : materials_map)
7560 {
7562 std::set<std::string> block_depend_props, block_supplied_props;
7563
7564 for (const auto & mat1 : it.second)
7565 {
7566 const std::set<std::string> & depend_props = mat1->getRequestedItems();
7567 block_depend_props.insert(depend_props.begin(), depend_props.end());
7568
7569 auto & alldeps = mat1->getMatPropDependencies(); // includes requested stateful props
7570 for (auto & dep : alldeps)
7571 {
7572 if (prop_names.count(dep) > 0)
7573 block_depend_props.insert(prop_names.at(dep));
7574 }
7575
7576 // See if any of the active materials supply this property
7577 for (const auto & mat2 : it.second)
7578 {
7579 const std::set<std::string> & supplied_props = mat2->MaterialBase::getSuppliedItems();
7580 block_supplied_props.insert(supplied_props.begin(), supplied_props.end());
7581 }
7582 }
7583
7584 // Add zero material properties specific to this block and unrestricted
7585 block_supplied_props.insert(_zero_block_material_props[it.first].begin(),
7586 _zero_block_material_props[it.first].end());
7587
7588 // Error check to make sure all properties consumed by materials are supplied on this block
7589 std::set<std::string> difference;
7590 std::set_difference(block_depend_props.begin(),
7591 block_depend_props.end(),
7592 block_supplied_props.begin(),
7593 block_supplied_props.end(),
7594 std::inserter(difference, difference.end()));
7595
7596 if (!difference.empty())
7597 {
7598 std::ostringstream oss;
7599 oss << "One or more Material Properties were not supplied on block ";
7600 const std::string & subdomain_name = _mesh.getSubdomainName(it.first);
7601 if (subdomain_name.length() > 0)
7602 oss << subdomain_name << " (" << it.first << ")";
7603 else
7604 oss << it.first;
7605 oss << ":\n";
7606 for (const auto & name : difference)
7607 oss << name << "\n";
7608 mooseError(oss.str());
7609 }
7610 }
7611
7612 // This loop checks that materials are not supplied by multiple Material objects
7613 for (const auto & it : materials_map)
7614 {
7615 const auto & materials = it.second;
7616 std::set<std::string> inner_supplied, outer_supplied;
7617
7618 for (const auto & outer_mat : materials)
7619 {
7620 // Storage for properties for this material (outer) and all other materials (inner)
7621 outer_supplied = outer_mat->getSuppliedItems();
7622 inner_supplied.clear();
7623
7624 // Property to material map for error reporting
7625 std::map<std::string, std::set<std::string>> prop_to_mat;
7626 for (const auto & name : outer_supplied)
7627 prop_to_mat[name].insert(outer_mat->name());
7628
7629 for (const auto & inner_mat : materials)
7630 {
7631 if (outer_mat == inner_mat)
7632 continue;
7633
7634 // Check whether these materials are an AD pair
7635 auto outer_mat_type = outer_mat->type();
7636 auto inner_mat_type = inner_mat->type();
7637 removeSubstring(outer_mat_type, "<RESIDUAL>");
7638 removeSubstring(outer_mat_type, "<JACOBIAN>");
7639 removeSubstring(inner_mat_type, "<RESIDUAL>");
7640 removeSubstring(inner_mat_type, "<JACOBIAN>");
7641 if (outer_mat_type == inner_mat_type && outer_mat_type != outer_mat->type() &&
7642 inner_mat_type != inner_mat->type())
7643 continue;
7644
7645 inner_supplied.insert(inner_mat->getSuppliedItems().begin(),
7646 inner_mat->getSuppliedItems().end());
7647
7648 for (const auto & inner_supplied_name : inner_supplied)
7649 prop_to_mat[inner_supplied_name].insert(inner_mat->name());
7650 }
7651
7652 // Test that a property isn't supplied on multiple blocks
7653 std::set<std::string> intersection;
7654 std::set_intersection(outer_supplied.begin(),
7655 outer_supplied.end(),
7656 inner_supplied.begin(),
7657 inner_supplied.end(),
7658 std::inserter(intersection, intersection.end()));
7659
7660 if (!intersection.empty())
7661 {
7662 std::ostringstream oss;
7663 oss << "The following material properties are declared on block " << it.first
7664 << " by multiple materials:\n";
7665 oss << ConsoleUtils::indent(2) << std::setw(30) << std::left << "Material Property"
7666 << "Material Objects\n";
7667 for (const auto & outer_name : intersection)
7668 {
7669 oss << ConsoleUtils::indent(2) << std::setw(30) << std::left << outer_name;
7670 for (const auto & inner_name : prop_to_mat[outer_name])
7671 oss << inner_name << " ";
7672 oss << '\n';
7673 }
7674
7675 mooseError(oss.str());
7676 break;
7677 }
7678 }
7679 }
7680}
7681
7682void
7683FEProblemBase::checkCoordinateSystems()
7684{
7685 _mesh.checkCoordinateSystems();
7686}

7688void
7689FEProblemBase::setRestartFile(const std::string & file_name)
7690{
7691 if (_app.isRecovering())
7692 {
7693 mooseInfo("Restart file ", file_name, " is NOT being used since we are performing recovery.");
7694 }
7695 else
7696 {
7697 _app.setRestart(true);
7698 _app.setRestartRecoverFileBase(file_name);
7699 mooseInfo("Using ", file_name, " for restart.");
7700 }
7701}
7702
7703std::vector<VariableName>
7704FEProblemBase::getVariableNames()
7705{
7706 std::vector<VariableName> names;
7707
7708 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7709 {
7710 const std::vector<VariableName> & nl_var_names = nl->getVariableNames();
7711 names.insert(names.end(), nl_var_names.begin(), nl_var_names.end());
7712 }
7713
7714 const std::vector<VariableName> & aux_var_names = _aux->getVariableNames();
7715 names.insert(names.end(), aux_var_names.begin(), aux_var_names.end());
7716
7717 return names;
7718}
7719
7720MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason
7721FEProblemBase::checkNonlinearConvergence(std::string & msg,
7722 const PetscInt it,
7723 const Real xnorm,
7724 const Real snorm,
7725 const Real fnorm,
7726 const Real rtol,
7727 const Real divtol,
7728 const Real stol,
7729 const Real abstol,
7730 const PetscInt nfuncs,
7731 const PetscInt max_funcs,
7732 const Real initial_residual_before_preset_bcs,
7733 const Real div_threshold)
7734{
7735 TIME_SECTION("checkNonlinearConvergence", 5, "Checking Nonlinear Convergence");
7736 mooseAssert(_current_nl_sys, "This should be non-null");
7737
7738 nonlinearConvergenceSetup();
7739
7740 if (_fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check)
7741 {
7742 _fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check = false;
7743 return MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_FNORM_NAN;
7744 }
7745
7746 NonlinearSystemBase & system = *_current_nl_sys;
7747 MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::ITERATING;
7748
7749 Real fnorm_old;
7750 // This is the first residual before any iterations have been done,
7751 // but after preset BCs (if any) have been imposed on the solution
7752 // vector. We save it, and use it to detect convergence if
7753 // compute_initial_residual_before_preset_bcs=false.
7754 if (it == 0)
7755 {
7756 system._initial_residual_after_preset_bcs = fnorm;
7757 fnorm_old = fnorm;
7758 _n_nl_pingpong = 0;
7759 }
7760 else
7761 fnorm_old = system._last_nl_rnorm;
7762
7763 // Check for nonlinear residual pingpong.
7764 // Pingpong will always start from a residual increase
7765 if ((_n_nl_pingpong % 2 == 1 && !(fnorm > fnorm_old)) ||
7766 (_n_nl_pingpong % 2 == 0 && fnorm > fnorm_old))
7767 _n_nl_pingpong += 1;
7768 else
7769 _n_nl_pingpong = 0;
7770
7771 std::ostringstream oss;
7772 if (fnorm != fnorm)
7773 {
7774 oss << "Failed to converge, function norm is NaN\n";
7775 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_FNORM_NAN;
7776 }
7777 else if ((it >= _nl_forced_its) && fnorm < abstol)
7778 {
7779 oss << "Converged due to function norm " << fnorm << " < " << abstol << '\n';
7780 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::CONVERGED_FNORM_ABS;
7781 }
7782 else if (nfuncs >= max_funcs)
7783 {
7784 oss << "Exceeded maximum number of function evaluations: " << nfuncs << " > " << max_funcs
7785 << '\n';
7786 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_FUNCTION_COUNT;
7787 }
7788 else if ((it >= _nl_forced_its) && it && fnorm > system._last_nl_rnorm && fnorm >= div_threshold)
7789 {
7790 oss << "Nonlinear solve was blowing up!\n";
7791 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_LINE_SEARCH;
7792 }
7793
7794 if ((it >= _nl_forced_its) && it && reason == MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::ITERATING)
7795 {
7796 // If compute_initial_residual_before_preset_bcs==false, then use the
7797 // first residual computed by PETSc to determine convergence.
7798 Real the_residual = system._compute_initial_residual_before_preset_bcs
7799 ? initial_residual_before_preset_bcs
7800 : system._initial_residual_after_preset_bcs;
7801 if (checkRelativeConvergence(it, fnorm, the_residual, rtol, abstol, oss))
7802 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::CONVERGED_FNORM_RELATIVE;
7803 else if (snorm < stol * xnorm)
7804 {
7805 oss << "Converged due to small update length: " << snorm << " < " << stol << " * " << xnorm
7806 << '\n';
7807 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::CONVERGED_SNORM_RELATIVE;
7808 }
7809 else if (divtol > 0 && fnorm > the_residual * divtol)
7810 {
7811 oss << "Diverged due to initial residual " << the_residual << " > divergence tolerance "
7812 << divtol << " * initial residual " << the_residual << '\n';
7813 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_DTOL;
7814 }
7815 else if (_nl_abs_div_tol > 0 && fnorm > _nl_abs_div_tol)
7816 {
7817 oss << "Diverged due to residual " << fnorm << " > absolute divergence tolerance "
7818 << _nl_abs_div_tol << '\n';
7819 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_DTOL;
7820 }
7821 else if (_n_nl_pingpong > _n_max_nl_pingpong)
7822 {
7823 oss << "Diverged due to maximum nonlinear residual pingpong achieved" << '\n';
7824 reason = MooseNonlinearConvergenceReason::DIVERGED_NL_RESIDUAL_PINGPONG;
7825 }
7826 }
7827
7828 system._last_nl_rnorm = fnorm;
7829 system._current_nl_its = static_cast<unsigned int>(it);
7830
7831 msg = oss.str();
7832 if (_app.multiAppLevel() > 0)
7833 MooseUtils::indentMessage(_app.name(), msg);
7834
7835 return reason;
7836}
7837
7838bool
7839FEProblemBase::checkRelativeConvergence(const PetscInt /*it*/,
7840 const Real fnorm,
7841 const Real the_residual,
7842 const Real rtol,
7843 const Real /*abstol*/,
7844 std::ostringstream & oss)
7845{
7846 if (_fail_next_nonlinear_convergence_check)
7847 return false;
7848 if (fnorm <= the_residual * rtol)
7849 {
7850 oss << "Converged due to function norm " << fnorm << " < relative tolerance (" << rtol << ")\n";
7851 return true;
7852 }
7853 return false;
7854}

7877
7878bool
7879FEProblemBase::needBoundaryMaterialOnSide(BoundaryID bnd_id, const THREAD_ID tid)
7880{
7881 if (_bnd_mat_side_cache[tid].find(bnd_id) == _bnd_mat_side_cache[tid].end())
7882 {
7883 auto & bnd_mat_side_cache = _bnd_mat_side_cache[tid][bnd_id];
7884 bnd_mat_side_cache = false;
7885
7886 if (_aux->needMaterialOnSide(bnd_id))
7887 {
7888 bnd_mat_side_cache = true;
7889 return true;
7890 }
7891 else
7892 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7893 if (nl->needBoundaryMaterialOnSide(bnd_id, tid))
7894 {
7895 bnd_mat_side_cache = true;
7896 return true;
7897 }
7898
7899 if (theWarehouse()
7900 .query()
7901 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
7902 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::SideUserObject)
7903 .condition<AttribBoundaries>(bnd_id)
7904 .count() > 0)
7905 {
7906 bnd_mat_side_cache = true;
7907 return true;
7908 }
7909 }
7910
7911 return _bnd_mat_side_cache[tid][bnd_id];
7912}
7913
7914bool
7915FEProblemBase::needInterfaceMaterialOnSide(BoundaryID bnd_id, const THREAD_ID tid)
7916{
7917 if (_interface_mat_side_cache[tid].find(bnd_id) == _interface_mat_side_cache[tid].end())
7918 {
7919 auto & interface_mat_side_cache = _interface_mat_side_cache[tid][bnd_id];
7920 interface_mat_side_cache = false;
7921
7922 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7923 if (nl->needInterfaceMaterialOnSide(bnd_id, tid))
7924 {
7925 interface_mat_side_cache = true;
7926 return true;
7927 }
7928
7929 if (theWarehouse()
7930 .query()
7931 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
7932 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::InterfaceUserObject)
7933 .condition<AttribBoundaries>(bnd_id)
7934 .count() > 0)
7935 {
7936 interface_mat_side_cache = true;
7937 return true;
7938 }
7939 else if (_interface_materials.hasActiveBoundaryObjects(bnd_id, tid))
7940 {
7941 interface_mat_side_cache = true;
7942 return true;
7943 }
7944 }
7945 return _interface_mat_side_cache[tid][bnd_id];
7946}
7947
7948bool
7949FEProblemBase::needSubdomainMaterialOnSide(SubdomainID subdomain_id, const THREAD_ID tid)
7950{
7951 if (_block_mat_side_cache[tid].find(subdomain_id) == _block_mat_side_cache[tid].end())
7952 {
7953 _block_mat_side_cache[tid][subdomain_id] = false;
7954
7955 for (auto & nl : _nl)
7956 if (nl->needSubdomainMaterialOnSide(subdomain_id, tid))
7957 {
7958 _block_mat_side_cache[tid][subdomain_id] = true;
7959 return true;
7960 }
7961
7962 if (theWarehouse()
7963 .query()
7964 .condition<AttribThread>(tid)
7965 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::InternalSideUserObject)
7966 .condition<AttribSubdomains>(subdomain_id)
7967 .count() > 0)
7968 {
7969 _block_mat_side_cache[tid][subdomain_id] = true;
7970 return true;
7971 }
7972 }
7973
7974 return _block_mat_side_cache[tid][subdomain_id];
7975}

8002
8003void
8004FEProblemBase::addOutput(const std::string & object_type,
8005 const std::string & object_name,
8006 InputParameters & parameters)
8007{
8008 parallel_object_only();
8009
8010 // Get a reference to the OutputWarehouse
8011 OutputWarehouse & output_warehouse = _app.getOutputWarehouse();
8012
8013 // Reject the reserved names for objects not built by MOOSE
8014 if (!parameters.get<bool>("_built_by_moose") && output_warehouse.isReservedName(object_name))
8015 mooseError("The name '", object_name, "' is a reserved name for output objects");
8016
8017 // Check that an object by the same name does not already exist; this must be done before the
8018 // object is created to avoid getting misleading errors from the Parser
8019 if (output_warehouse.hasOutput(object_name))
8020 mooseError("An output object named '", object_name, "' already exists");
8021
8022 // Add a pointer to the FEProblemBase class
8023 parameters.addPrivateParam<FEProblemBase *>("_fe_problem_base", this);
8024
8025 // Create common parameter exclude list
8026 std::vector<std::string> exclude;
8027 if (object_type == "Console")
8028 {
8029 exclude.push_back("execute_on");
8030
8031 // --show-input should enable the display of the input file on the screen
8032 if (_app.getParam<bool>("show_input") && parameters.get<bool>("output_screen"))
8033 parameters.set<ExecFlagEnum>("execute_input_on") = EXEC_INITIAL;
8034 }
8035
8036 // Apply the common parameters loaded with Outputs input syntax
8037 const InputParameters * common = output_warehouse.getCommonParameters();
8038 if (common)
8039 parameters.applyParameters(*common, exclude);
8040
8041 // Set the correct value for the binary flag for XDA/XDR output
8042 if (object_type == "XDR")
8043 parameters.set<bool>("_binary") = true;
8044 else if (object_type == "XDA")
8045 parameters.set<bool>("_binary") = false;
8046
8047 // Adjust the checkpoint suffix if auto recovery was enabled
8048 if (object_name == "auto_recovery_checkpoint")
8049 parameters.set<std::string>("suffix") = "auto_recovery";
8050
8051 // Create the object and add it to the warehouse
8052 std::shared_ptr<Output> output = _factory.create<Output>(object_type, object_name, parameters);
8053 logAdd("Output", object_name, object_type);
8054 output_warehouse.addOutput(output);
8055}

8169
8170void
8171FEProblemBase::getFVMatsAndDependencies(
8172 const SubdomainID blk_id,
8173 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase>> & face_materials,
8174 std::vector<std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase>> & neighbor_materials,
8175 std::set<MooseVariableFieldBase *> & variables,
8176 const THREAD_ID tid)
8177{
8178 if (_materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
8179 {
8180 auto & this_face_mats =
8181 _materials[Moose::FACE_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid);
8182 for (std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> face_mat : this_face_mats)
8183 if (face_mat->ghostable())
8184 {
8185 mooseAssert(!face_mat->hasStatefulProperties(),
8186 "Finite volume materials do not currently support stateful properties.");
8187 face_materials.push_back(face_mat);
8188 auto & var_deps = face_mat->getMooseVariableDependencies();
8189 for (auto * var : var_deps)
8190 {
8191 mooseAssert(
8192 var->isFV(),
8193 "Ghostable materials should only have finite volume variables coupled into them.");
8194 variables.insert(var);
8195 }
8196 }
8197 }
8198
8199 if (_materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].hasActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid))
8200 {
8201 auto & this_neighbor_mats =
8202 _materials[Moose::NEIGHBOR_MATERIAL_DATA].getActiveBlockObjects(blk_id, tid);
8203 for (std::shared_ptr<MaterialBase> neighbor_mat : this_neighbor_mats)
8204 if (neighbor_mat->ghostable())
8205 {
8206 mooseAssert(!neighbor_mat->hasStatefulProperties(),
8207 "Finite volume materials do not currently support stateful properties.");
8208 neighbor_materials.push_back(neighbor_mat);
8209#ifndef NDEBUG
8210 auto & var_deps = neighbor_mat->getMooseVariableDependencies();
8211 for (auto * var : var_deps)
8212 {
8213 mooseAssert(
8214 var->isFV(),
8215 "Ghostable materials should only have finite volume variables coupled into them.");
8216 auto pr = variables.insert(var);
8217 mooseAssert(!pr.second,
8218 "We should not have inserted any new variables dependencies from our "
8219 "neighbor materials that didn't exist for our face materials");
8220 }
8221#endif
8222 }
8223 }
8224}

8234void
8235FEProblemBase::residualSetup()
8236{
8237 SubProblem::residualSetup();
8238 // We need to setup all the nonlinear systems other than our current one which actually called
8239 // this method (so we have to make sure we don't go in a circle)
8240 for (const auto i : make_range(numNonlinearSystems()))
8241 if (i != currentNlSysNum())
8242 _nl[i]->residualSetup();
8243 // We don't setup the aux sys because that's been done elsewhere
8244 if (_displaced_problem)
8245 _displaced_problem->residualSetup();
8246}

8288std::vector<MortarUserObject *>
8289FEProblemBase::getMortarUserObjects(const BoundaryID primary_boundary_id,
8290 const BoundaryID secondary_boundary_id,
8291 const bool displaced,
8292 const std::vector<MortarUserObject *> & mortar_uo_superset)
8293{
8294 std::vector<MortarUserObject *> mortar_uos;
8295 auto * const subproblem = displaced ? static_cast<SubProblem *>(_displaced_problem.get())
8296 : static_cast<SubProblem *>(this);
8297 for (auto * const obj : mortar_uo_superset)
8298 if (obj->onInterface(primary_boundary_id, secondary_boundary_id) &&
8299 (&obj->getSubProblem() == subproblem))
8300 mortar_uos.push_back(obj);
8301
8302 return mortar_uos;
8303}

8306FEProblemBase::getMortarUserObjects(const BoundaryID primary_boundary_id,
8307 const BoundaryID secondary_boundary_id,

8311 theWarehouse()
8312 .query()
8313 .condition<AttribInterfaces>(Interfaces::MortarUserObject)
8314 .queryInto(mortar_uos);
8315 return getMortarUserObjects(primary_boundary_id, secondary_boundary_id, displaced, mortar_uos);
8316}
